)@@G@@@^@@@]      START EDIT PAGE   @[@#@]C     @G@#@]C SUBROUTINE TO PRINT LACF
)@@G@@RGE HEADINGS. THE FIRST 18 CHARACTERS STARTING  @G@#@]C   AT THE ADDRESSCG
)@@G@@ HEAD ARE PRINTED. A MAXIMUM OF 2 LINES PER PAGE IS   @G@#@]C   POSSIBLECH
)@@G@@. THE LINES ARE FORMED BY OVERPRINTING THE CHARACTERS X,H   @G@#@]C   ANCI
)@@G@@D I. T IS A TABLE OF MASKS WHICH IS USED TO FORM EACH LINE OF     @#@#@]CJ
)@@G@@C   CHARACTERS    @[@#@]C     @A@@@]      INTEGER LINE(18), HEAD(3)     CK
)@@G@@@F@@@]      INTEGER  CHAR1/'XXXXXX'/,CHAR2/'HHHHHH'/,CHAR3/'IIIIII'/    CL
)@@G@@@^@@@[      WRITE (6,1000)    @^@#@[1000  FORMAT (/////////)@ @^@#1000  CM
)@@G@@FORMAT (//////////)     @^@@@^1000  FORMAT (/////////)@^@@@[      DO 30 CN
)@@G@@J = 1,7     @ @@@]      CALL CHARLN (CHAR1)     @]@]@[      L = 0 @]@]@[CO
)@@G@@      M = 1 @^@]@[      DO 20 I = 1,18    @ @]@[      K = FLD(L,6,HEAD(MCP
)@@G@@)) + 1@#@]@[      L = L + 6   @ @]@[      IF (L.LE.30) GO TO 20   @]@]@[CQ
)@@G@@      L = 0 @#@]@[      M = M + 1   @G@]@[20    LINE(I) = OR( AND(T(J,K)CR
)@@G@@,CHAR1), AND(COMPL(T(J,K)),'      ') )    @^@@@[      WRITE(6,1005) LINECS
)@@G@@@ @@@[1005  FORMAT(1H ,18(A6,1X))   @ @@@]      CALL CHARLN (CHAR2)     CT
)@@G@@@]@]@[      L = 0 @]@]@[      M = 1 @^@]@[      DO 22 I = 1,18    @ @]@[CU
)@@G@@      K = FLD(L,6,HEAD(M)) + 1@#@]@[      L = L + 6   @ @]@[      IF (L.CV
)@@G@@LE.30) GO TO 22   @]@]@[      L = 0 @#@]@[      M = M + 1   @G@]@[22    CW
)@@G@@LINE(I) = OR( AND(T(J,K),CHAR2), AND(COMPL(T(J,K)),'      ') )    @^@@@[CX
)@@G@@      WRITE(6,1010) LINE@ @@@[1010  FORMAT(1H+,18(A6,1X))   @ @@@]      CY
)@@G@@CALL CHARLN (CHAR3)     @]@]@[      L = 0 @]@]@[      M = 1 @^@]@[      CZ
)@@G@@DO 24 I = 1,18    @ @]@[      K = FLD(L,6,HEAD(M)) + 1@#@]@[      L = L DA
)@@G@@+ 6   @ @]@[      IF (L.LE.30) GO TO 24   @]@]@[      L = 0 @#@]@[      DB
)@@G@@M = M + 1   @G@]@[24    LINE(I) = OR( AND(T(J,K),CHAR3), AND(COMPL(T(J,KDC
)@@G@@)),'      ') )    @^@@@[      WRITE(6,1010) LINE@#@@@[30    CONTINUE    DD
)@@G@@@^@ @[      WRITE (6,1000)    @^@@@       WRITE (6,1015)    @ @@@ 1015  DE
)@@G@@FORMAT (//////////)     @]@@@[      RETURN@@@@@]@ @@@]      SUBROUTINE CDF
)@@G@@HARLN (CHAR)@]@@@]      L = 0 @]@@@]      M = 1 @^@@@]      DO 20 I = 1,DG
)@@G@@18    @ @@@]      K = FLD(L,6,HEAD(M)) + 1@#@@@]      L = L + 6   @ @@@]DH
)@@G@@      IF (L.LE.30) GO TO 20   @]@@@]      L = 0 @#@@@]      M = M + 1   DI
)@@G@@@G@@@]20    LINE(I) = OR( AND(T(J,K),CHAR), AND(COMPL(T(J,K)),'      ') DJ
)@@G@@)     @]@@@]      RETURN@@@@@]@]@@@[      END   ___7777777700/    @G@@@[DK
)@@G@@      DATA (T(I,12),I=1,7)/O777777777700,O770000000000,O770000000000,   DL

)@@G@@ CODE ADDED - MAY 1981  @G@@@:      * LEVEL 3.1: B-OPTION ADDED. WHEN SEGM
)@@G@@T, THE EXPENSIVE SECTOR-1 READ@G@@@:      *            IS DONE FOR ALL FGN
)@@G@@ILES TO GET BACKUP TAPE NOS FOR THE @D@@@:      *            'RELOAD' UTGO
)@@G@@ILITY 'SECBCKUPCHEK'    @@@@@*@ @@@*       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.  @ @@@*GP
)@@G@@       CONFIGURATION SECTION. @A@@@*       SOURCE-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.GQ
)@@G@@@A@@@*       OBJECT-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@ @@@*       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTGR
)@@G@@ION.  @^@@@*       FILE-CONTROL.    @D@@@*           SELECT JBMFDFIL ASSGS
)@@G@@IGN TO DISC JBMFDFIL.   @D@@@*           SELECT DIRECTORY-IN ASSIGN TO DGT
)@@G@@ISC XA.     @^@@@*       DATA DIVISION.   @@@@@*@^@@@*       FILE SECTIOGU
)@@G@@N.    @^@@@*      ***************   @@@@@*@^@@@*       FD  JBMFDFIL     GV
)@@G@@@B@@@*            LABEL RECORDS ARE STANDARD    @B@@@*            BLOCK GW
)@@G@@CONTAINS 20 RECORDS.    @C@@@*       01  MFDFIL-REC             PIC X(16GX
)@@G@@8).   @^@@@*       SD  DIRECTORY-IN @C@@@*            RECORD CONTAINS 16GY
)@@G@@8 CHARACTERS.     @A@@@*       01  SRTREC.  COPY MFD-MAIN-0.@@@%@*@]@@@%GZ
)@@G@@      /     @A@@@*       WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.     @A@@@*      ******HA
)@@G@@********************    @@@@@*@E@@@*       01  CNTR                   PIHB
)@@G@@C H9(10) VALUE ZERO.    @E@@@*       01  UNLD                   PIC H9(1HC
)@@G@@0) VALUE ZERO.    @E@@@*       01  BAD-LI-COUNT           PIC H9(10) VALHD
)@@G@@UE ZERO.    @E@@@*       01  BAD-MI-COUNT           PIC H9(10) VALUE ZERHE
)@@G@@O.    @C@@@*       01  FILE-DUMP              PIC X(30).    @B@@@*      HF
)@@G@@ 01  FILE-CYCLE             PIC 999.@C@@@*       01  DUMP-TEXT          HG
)@@G@@    PIC X(4).     @E@@@*       01  DISABLED-COUNT         PIC H9(10) VALHH
)@@G@@UE ZERO.    @E@@@*       01  SUB                    PIC H9(10) VALUE ZERHI
)@@G@@O.    @E@@@*       01  DGET-FILE              PIC X(12) VALUE 'MSDGET'. HJ
)@@G@@@^@@@*       01  DGET-BUFFER. @E@@@*           03  DGET-BUFFER-WORD   PIHK
)@@G@@C X(6) OCCURS 3590.     @ @@@*       01  DGET-ASTAT-BIN.    @D@@@*      HL
)@@G@@     03  FILLER             PIC 111 VALUE 1.    @E@@@*           03  FILHM
)@@G@@LER             PIC 1(33) VALUE ZERO.     @F@@@*       01  DGET-ASTAT  RHN
)@@G@@EDEFINES  DGET-ASTAT-BIN    PIC H9(10).   @A@@@*       01  ALREADY-ASSIGHO
)@@G@@NED-BITS.   @D@@@*           03  FILLER             PIC 111 VALUE 1.    HP
)@@G@@@E@@@*           03  FILLER             PIC 1(33) VALUE ZERO.     @G@@@*HQ
)@@G@@       01  ALREADY-ASSIGNED REDEFINES ALREADY-ASSIGNED-BITS   PIC 1(36).HR
)@@G@@@D@@@:       01  B-OPT-SET              PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @C@@@*      HS
)@@G@@ 01  DGET-MSTAT             PIC H9(10).   @C@@@*       01  BINARY-DUMP  HT
)@@G@@          PIC H9(10).   @C@@@*       01  BINARY-DUMP-1  REDEFINES BINARYHU
)@@G@@-DUMP.@D@@@*           03  BINARY-VAL         PIC 111 OCCURS 12.  @D@@@:HV

)@@G@@CTAL-DUMP.  @D@:@*           03  OCTAL-VAL          PIC 9   OCCURS 12.  HX
)@@G@@@C@?@*       01  MFDSP-CODE  REDEFINES  OCTAL-DUMP.   @C@?@*           0HY
)@@G@@3  FILLER             PIC 9(9).     @B@?@*           03  MFDSP-ERROR    HZ
)@@G@@    PIC 999.@@@@@*@C@@@*       01  MFDSP-FUNCTION         PIC H9(10).   IA
)@@G@@@ @@@*       01  MFDSP-REGISTERS.   @D@@@*           03  MFDSP-A0       IB
)@@G@@    PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @D@@@*           03  MFDSP-A1           PIC H9(1IC
)@@G@@0) VALUE 0. @D@@@*           03  MFDSP-A2           PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. ID
)@@G@@@D@@@*           03  MFDSP-A3           PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @D@@@*      IE
)@@G@@     03  MFDSP-A4           PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @D@@@*           03  MFDIF
)@@G@@SP-A5           PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @E@@@*       01  MFDSP-LENBUF       IG
)@@G@@    PIC H9(10) VALUE 6000.    @^@@@*       01  MFDSP-BUFFER.@E@@@*      IH
)@@G@@     03  MFDSP-BUFFER-WORD  PIC X(6)  OCCURS 6000.    @ @@@*       01  MII
)@@G@@FDSP-MFDITEM.     @C@@@*           03  MFD-WORD-0         PIC SH9(10).  IJ
)@@G@@@C@@@*           03  MFD-QUAL           PIC X(12).    @C@@@*           0IK

)@@G@@    PIC X(6) OCCURS 4.  @C@@@*           03  FILLER             PIC 1(24IM
)@@G@@).    @C@@@*           03  MFD-LI-CYCLE       PIC 1(12).    @D@@@*      IN
)@@G@@     03  FILLER             PIC X(6) OCCURS 7.  @C@@@*           03  FILIO
)@@G@@LER             PIC 1(24).    @C@@@*           03  MFD-MI-CYCLE       PIIP
)@@G@@C 1(12).    @D@@@*           03  FILLER             PIC X(6) OCCURS 10. IQ
)@@G@@@@@@@*@ @@@*       01  MAIN-ITEM-SECTOR-1.@E@@@*           05  WORD-0-6 IR
)@@G@@          PIC X(42) VALUE ALL '6'.  @C@@@*           05  MIS1-NO-BACKUP IS
)@@G@@    PIC 1(12).    @C@@@*           05  FILLER             PIC 1(24).    IT
)@@G@@@C@@@*           05  MIS1-BACKUP-TDATE  PIC X(6).     @^@@@*           0IU
)@@G@@5  WORD-9.  @C@@@*               10  FILLER         PIC 1(18).    @C@@@*IV
)@@G@@               10  SIZE-IN-TRACKS PIC 1(18).    @C@@@*           05  WORIW
)@@G@@D-10            PIC X(6).     @C@@@*           05  MIS1-REEL-1        PIIX
)@@G@@C X(6).     @C@@@*           05  MIS1-REEL-2        PIC X(6).     @C@@@*IY
)@@G@@           05  WORD-13-16         PIC X(24).    @^@@@*           05  WORIZ
)@@G@@D-17. @C@@@*               10  FILLER         PIC 1(24).    @C@@@*      JA
)@@G@@         10  NBR-DISC-PACKS PIC 1(12).    @C@@@*           05  DISC-PACKJB
)@@G@@-ID-1     PIC X(6).     @C@@@*           05  WORD-19            PIC X(6)JC
)@@G@@.     @C@@@*           05  DISC-PACK-ID-2     PIC X(6).     @C@@@*      JD

)@@G@@-ID-5     PIC X(6).     @C@@@*           05  WORD-27            PIC X(6)JI
)@@G@@.     @^@@@?       01  MFDSP-CODE.  @C@@@?           03  FILLER         JJ
)@@G@@    PIC 9(9).     @B@@@?           03  MFDSP-ERROR        PIC 999.@C@@@?JK
)@@G@@       01  OCTAL-DUMP  REDEFINES MFDSP-CODE.    @D@@@?           03  OCTJL
)@@G@@AL-VAL          PIC 9   OCCURS 12.  @^@@@:       01  OPTION-WORD. @C@@@:JM
)@@G@@           03  FILLER             PIC 1(11).    @B@@@:           03  B-OJN
)@@G@@PT              PIC 1.  @C@@@:           03  FILLER             PIC 1(24JO
)@@G@@).    @^@?@:       01  OCTAL-DUMP.  @D@?@:           03  OCTAL-VAL      JP
)@@G@@    PIC 9   OCCURS 12.  @A@@@*       01  WS-WORD13 PIC 1(36).     @D@:@*JQ
)@@G@@       01  LEAD-ITEM-HAS-SECTOR-1 PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @]@@@*      /     JR
)@@G@@@ @@@*       PROCEDURE DIVISION.    @ @@@*      *********************   JS
)@@G@@@@@@@*@^@@@*       MAIN SECTION.    @#@@@*       INITIALISE.@C@:@*      JT
)@@G@@     DISPLAY 'GETDIR 3.0' UPON PRINTER.   @C@@@:           DISPLAY 'GETDJU
)@@G@@IR 3.1' UPON PRINTER.   @C@@@:           CALL 'OPTION' USING OPTION-WORDJV
)@@G@@.     @ @@@:           IF B-OPT NOT = 0   @A@@@:               MOVE 1 TOJW
)@@G@@ B-OPT-SET. @C@@@*           ENTER FORTRAN 'DGET' USING DGET-FILE @D@@@*JX
)@@G@@                                      DGET-BUFFER     @C@@@*            JY
)@@G@@                          DGET-ASTAT@D@@@*                              JZ
)@@G@@        DGET-MSTAT.     @B@@@*           MOVE DGET-ASTAT TO BINARY-DUMP.KA
)@@G@@@A@@@*           PERFORM OCTAL-CONVERSION.@F@@@*           DISPLAY 'DGETKB
)@@G@@: MSDGET ASSIGN STATUS = ' OCTAL-DUMP     @ @@@*               UPON PRINKC
)@@G@@TER.  @B@@@*           MOVE DGET-MSTAT TO BINARY-DUMP.@A@@@*           PKD
)@@G@@ERFORM OCTAL-CONVERSION.@F@@@*           DISPLAY 'DGET: MSCON$ STATUS REKE
)@@G@@TURN = ' OCTAL-DUMP     @ @@@*               UPON PRINTER.  @F@@@*      KF
)@@G@@     IF DGET-MSTAT = 0 AND DGET-ASTAT NOT = ALREADY-ASSIGNED@F@@@*      KG
)@@G@@         DISPLAY '*** ERROR ***  DGET FAILED' UPON PRINTER  @A@@@*      KH
)@@G@@         GO TO TERMINATION.   @D@@@*           MOVE 'MSDGET' TO MFDSP-BUKI
)@@G@@FFER-WORD(1).     @D@@@*           MOVE  SPACES  TO MFDSP-BUFFER-WORD(2)KJ
)@@G@@.     @@@@@*@D@@@*           SORT DIRECTORY-IN ASCENDING KEY W12-BIT-27 KK
)@@G@@@D@@@*                                           ACT-NBR    @D@@@*      KL
)@@G@@                                     PROJ-ID    @D@@@*                  KM
)@@G@@                         QUALIFIER  @D@@@*                              KN
)@@G@@             FILENAME   @D@@@*                                          KO
)@@G@@ F-CYCLE    @A@@@*           INPUT PROCEDURE IS REL-IT@B@@@*           OKP
)@@G@@UTPUT PROCEDURE IS RTN-IT.    @@@@@*@A@@@*           DISPLAY ' ' UPON PRKQ
)@@G@@INTER.@F@@@*           DISPLAY CNTR ' FILES WRITTEN TO JBMFDFIL' UPON PRKR
)@@G@@INTER.@E@@@*           DISPLAY UNLD ' FILES WERE UNLOADED' UPON PRINTER.KS
)@@G@@@G@@@*           DISPLAY DISABLED-COUNT ' FILES NOT WRITTEN: FATALLY DISKT
)@@G@@ABLED'@ @@@*               UPON PRINTER.  @G@@@*           DISPLAY BAD-LKU
)@@G@@I-COUNT ' FILES NOT WRITTEN: BAD LEAD ITEM'     @ @@@*               UPOKV
)@@G@@N PRINTER.  @G@@@*           DISPLAY BAD-MI-COUNT ' FILES NOT WRITTEN: BKW
)@@G@@AD MAIN ITEM'     @ @@@*               UPON PRINTER.  @ @@@*           CKX
)@@G@@LOSE JBMFDFIL.    @^@@@*       TERMINATION.     @^@@@*           STOP RUKY
)@@G@@N.    @@@@@*@A@@@*       OCTAL-CONVERSION SECTION.    @A@@@*      ******KZ
)@@G@@*********************   @@@@@*@#@@@*       OCTAL-000. @ @@@*           MLA
)@@G@@OVE 12 TO SUB.    @#@@@*       OCTAL-100. @D@@@*           MOVE BINARY-VLB
)@@G@@AL(SUB) TO OCTAL-VAL(SUB).    @A@@@*           SUBTRACT 1 FROM SUB.     LC
)@@G@@@ @@@*           IF SUB NOT = 0     @A@@@*               GO TO OCTAL-100LD
)@@G@@.     @]@@@*      /     @^@@@*       REL-IT SECTION.  @^@@@*      ******LE
)@@G@@*********** @@@@@*@#@@@*       MFDSP-OPEN.@@@@@*@F@@@*      * INITIALISELF
)@@G@@ MFD SERVICE PACKAGE AND GET FIRST LEAD ITEM    @@@@@*@A@@@*           MLG
)@@G@@OVE 0 TO MFDSP-FUNCTION.@D@@@*           ENTER FORTRAN 'FMFDSP' USING MFLH
)@@G@@DSP-FUNCTION@E@@@*                                        MFDSP-REGISTERLI
)@@G@@S     @D@@@*                                        MFDSP-LENBUF  @D@@@*LJ
)@@G@@                                        MFDSP-BUFFER  @D@@@*            LK
)@@G@@                            MFDSP-MFDITEM.@ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A4 NLL
)@@G@@OT = 0@G@@@*               PERFORM MFDSP-STATUS-CHECK-REL THRU MFDSP-STALM
)@@G@@TUS-REL-END.@F@@@*           DISPLAY 'MIN. MFDSP BUFFER SIZE = ' MFDSP-ALN
)@@G@@5 ' WORDS'  @ @@@*               UPON PRINTER.  @G@@@*           DISPLAYLO
)@@G@@ 'SIZE CURRENTLY IN USE  = ' MFDSP-LENBUF ' WORDS'    @ @@@*            LP
)@@G@@   UPON PRINTER.  @A@@@*           DISPLAY ' ' UPON PRINTER.@@@@@*@F@@@*LQ
)@@G@@      * START OF LOOP TO READ THE 'DGET' FILE OF DIRECTORY ITEMS  @@@@@*LR
)@@G@@@^@@@*       MAIN-ITEM-READ.  @A@@@*           MOVE 4 TO MFDSP-FUNCTION.LS
)@@G@@@D@@@*           ENTER FORTRAN 'FMFDSP' USING MFDSP-FUNCTION@E@@@*      LT
)@@G@@                                  MFDSP-REGISTERS     @D@@@*            LU
)@@G@@                            MFDSP-LENBUF  @D@@@*                        LV
)@@G@@                MFDSP-BUFFER  @D@@@*                                    LW
)@@G@@    MFDSP-MFDITEM.@ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A4 NOT = 0@G@@@*            LX
)@@G@@   PERFORM MFDSP-STATUS-CHECK-REL THRU MFDSP-STATUS-REL-END.@ @@@*      LY
)@@G@@     IF MFDSP-A1 NOT = 0@A@@@*               GO TO RELEASE-PARA.  @@@@@*LZ
)@@G@@@^@@@*       LEAD-ITEM-READ.  @B@@@*           IF LEAD-ITEM-HAS-SECTOR-1MA
)@@G@@ = 0  @B@@@*               MOVE 2 TO MFDSP-FUNCTION   @#@@@*           EMB
)@@G@@LSE   @B@@@*               MOVE 3 TO MFDSP-FUNCTION.  @D@@@*           EMC
)@@G@@NTER FORTRAN 'FMFDSP' USING MFDSP-FUNCTION@E@@@*                        MD
)@@G@@                MFDSP-REGISTERS     @D@@@*                              ME
)@@G@@          MFDSP-LENBUF  @D@@@*                                        MFMF
)@@G@@DSP-BUFFER  @D@@@*                                        MFDSP-MFDITEM.MG
)@@G@@@ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A1 = 0    @A@@@*               GO TO END-OF-MFMH
)@@G@@D.    @ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A4 NOT = 0@G@@@*               PERFORM MMI
)@@G@@FDSP-STATUS-CHECK-REL THRU MFDSP-STATUS-REL-END.@@@@@*@H@@@*      * 23 =MJ
)@@G@@ 027 = CODE FOR LEAD ITEM WITH INVALID LINKS TO ALL MAIN ITEMS    @@@@@*MK
)@@G@@@ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A2 = 23   @A@@@*               GO TO LEAD-ITEMML
)@@G@@-READ.@@@@@*@H@@@*      * IF BIT 35 OF WORD-0 OF LEAD ITEM IS ZERO, THERMM
)@@G@@E IS A SECTOR 1 OF THE  @H@@@*      * LEAD ITEM (CONTAINING LINKS TO MAIMN
)@@G@@N ITEMS FOR FILE CYCLES -17 TO -31) @F@@@*      * SET LEAD-ITEM-HAS-SECTMO
)@@G@@OR-1 SWITCH FOR USE ABOVE.    FMFDSP@H@@@*      * FUNCTION 3 GETS SECTORMP
)@@G@@ 1 IN THIS CASE.   IF BIT 35 IS SET, I.E. WORD-0@H@@@*      * LOOKS NEGAMQ
)@@G@@TIVE, THERE IS ONLY A SECTOR 0, SO FUNCTION 2 GETS THE NEXT @#@@@*      MR
)@@G@@* LEAD ITEM.@@@@@*@B@@@*           IF MFD-WORD-0 IS LESS THAN ZERO@C@@@*MS
)@@G@@               MOVE 0 TO LEAD-ITEM-HAS-SECTOR-1 @#@@@*           ELSE   MT
)@@G@@@C@@@*               MOVE 1 TO LEAD-ITEM-HAS-SECTOR-1.@A@@@*           GMU
)@@G@@O TO MAIN-ITEM-READ.    @@@@@*@^@@@*       RELEASE-PARA.    @C@@@*      MV
)@@G@@     RELEASE SRTREC FROM MFDSP-MFDITEM.   @A@@@*           GO TO MAIN-ITMW
)@@G@@EM-READ.    @]@@@*      /     @ @@@*       MFDSP-STATUS-CHECK-REL.@ @@@*MX
)@@G@@      ************************@@@@@*@C@@@*           IF MFDSP-A2 NOT = 7MY
)@@G@@ AND NOT = 23     @B@@@*               GO TO REGISTER-DUMP-REL.   @B@@@*MZ
)@@G@@           MOVE MFDSP-A2 TO BINARY-DUMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTALNA
)@@G@@-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. @ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A2 = 7    NB
)@@G@@@C@@@*               MOVE MFD-MI-CYCLE TO FILE-CYCLE  @B@@@*            NC
)@@G@@   MOVE 'MAIN' TO DUMP-TEXT   @A@@@*               ADD 1 TO BAD-MI-COUNTND
)@@G@@@#@@@*           ELSE   @C@@@*               MOVE MFD-LI-CYCLE TO FILE-CNE
)@@G@@YCLE  @B@@@*               MOVE 'LEAD' TO DUMP-TEXT   @B@@@*            NF
)@@G@@   ADD 1 TO BAD-LI-COUNT.     @ @@@*           PERFORM STRING-REL.@F@@@*NG
)@@G@@           DISPLAY '** BAD ' DUMP-TEXT ' ITEM: ERROR-CODE = '     @E@@@*NH
)@@G@@               MFDSP-ERROR ' ON ' FILE-DUMP UPON PRINTER.   @B@@@*      NI
)@@G@@     GO TO MFDSP-STATUS-REL-END.    @ @@@*       REGISTER-DUMP-REL.     NJ
)@@G@@@F@@@*           DISPLAY '** FMFDSP ERRORED: REGISTER DUMP FOLLOWS'     NK
)@@G@@@G@@@*               '  (SEE SYSLIB MANUAL UP-8728 CHAP.6)' UPON PRINTERNL
)@@G@@.     @ @@@*           PERFORM STRING-REL.@D@@@*           EXHIBIT NAMEDNM
)@@G@@ MFDSP-FUNCTION FILE-DUMP.    @B@@@*           MOVE MFDSP-A0 TO BINARY-DNN
)@@G@@UMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTAL-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. NO
)@@G@@@E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A0 = ' OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*NP
)@@G@@           MOVE MFDSP-A1 TO BINARY-DUMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTALNQ
)@@G@@-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. @E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A1 = 'NR
)@@G@@ OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*           MOVE MFDSP-A2 TO BINARY-DNS
)@@G@@UMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTAL-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. NT
)@@G@@@E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A2 = ' OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*NU
)@@G@@           MOVE MFDSP-A3 TO BINARY-DUMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTALNV
)@@G@@-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. @E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A3 = 'NW
)@@G@@ OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*           MOVE MFDSP-A4 TO BINARY-DNX
)@@G@@UMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTAL-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. NY
)@@G@@@E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A4 = ' OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*NZ
)@@G@@           MOVE MFDSP-A5 TO BINARY-DUMP.  @E@@@*           PERFORM OCTALOA
)@@G@@-CONVERSION-REL THRU OCTAL-REL-END. @E@@@*           DISPLAY '    A5 = 'OB
)@@G@@ OCTAL-DUMP UPON PRINTER.     @B@@@*           GO TO MFDSP-STATUS-REL-ENOC
)@@G@@D.    @@@@@*@#@@@*       STRING-REL.@A@@@*           MOVE SPACES TO FILEOD
)@@G@@-DUMP.@C@@@*           STRING MFD-QUAL DELIMITED BY SPACE   @C@@@*      OE
)@@G@@            '*'      DELIMITED BY SIZE    @C@@@*                  MFD-FIOF
)@@G@@LE DELIMITED BY SPACE   @C@@@*                  '('      DELIMITED BY SIOG
)@@G@@ZE    @C@@@*                  FILE-CYCLE DELIMITED BY SIZE  @C@@@*      OH
)@@G@@            ')'      DELIMITED BY SIZE    @A@@@*                  INTO FOI
)@@G@@ILE-DUMP.   @@@@@*@ @@@*       MFDSP-STATUS-REL-END.  @#@@@*           EOJ
)@@G@@XIT.  @@@@@*@ @@@*       OCTAL-CONVERSION-REL.  @ @@@*      ************OK
)@@G@@**********  @@@@@*@ @@@*           MOVE 12 TO SUB.    @^@@@*       OCTALOL
)@@G@@-REL100.    @D@@@*           MOVE BINARY-VAL(SUB) TO OCTAL-VAL(SUB).    OM
)@@G@@@A@@@*           SUBTRACT 1 FROM SUB.     @ @@@*           IF SUB NOT = ON
)@@G@@0     @A@@@*               GO TO OCTAL-REL100.  @^@@@*       OCTAL-REL-EOO
)@@G@@ND.   @#@@@*           EXIT.  @@@@@*@#@@@*       END-OF-MFD.@F@@@*      OP
)@@G@@     DISPLAY 'END OF SORT INPUT (REL-IT)' UPON PRINTER.     @]@@@*      OQ
)@@G@@/     @^@@@*       RTN-IT SECTION.  @^@@@*      ***************** @@@@@*OR
)@@G@@@^@@@*       RETURN-START.    @A@@@*           OPEN OUTPUT JBMFDFIL.    OS
)@@G@@@F@@@*           DISPLAY 'START OF SORT OUTPUT (RTN-IT)' UPON PRINTER.  OT
)@@G@@@^@@@*       RETURN-A-RECORD. @E@@@*           RETURN DIRECTORY-IN RECOROU
)@@G@@D AT END GO TO FIN-IT.  @@@@@*@G@@@*      *    ACCOUNT-NUMER OF '@@@@@@@OV
)@@G@@@@@@@' SHOULD BE 'INSTALLATION'     @@@@@*@A@@@*           IF ACT1 = 0 AOW
)@@G@@ND ACT2 = 0 @A@@@*               PERFORM STRING-NAME  @G@@@*            OX
)@@G@@   DISPLAY 'ZERO ACCOUNT CHANGED TO ''INSTALLATION'' FOR '  @B@@@*      OY
)@@G@@             FILE-DUMP UPON PRINTER @C@@@*               MOVE 'INSTALLATOZ
)@@G@@ION' TO ACT-NBR.  @@@@@*@^@@@*           IF TAPE-FILE @C@@@*            PA
)@@G@@   GO TO WRITE-JBMFDFIL-RECORD.     @@@@@*@ @@@*           IF SHARED-FLAPB
)@@G@@G = 32@B@@@*               MOVE 1 TO NEW-SHARED-FLAG  @#@@@*           EPC
)@@G@@LSE   @B@@@*               MOVE 0 TO NEW-SHARED-FLAG. @@@@@:@A@@@:      PD
)@@G@@     IF NOT REMOVABLE-DISK AND@A@@@:              NOT UNLOADED       ANDPE
)@@G@@@ @@@:              B-OPT-SET = 0   @C@@@:                GO TO WRITE-JBPF
)@@G@@MFDFIL-RECORD.    @@@@@*@C@@@*           MOVE LNK-SECT1-MN-ITM TO MFDSP-PG
)@@G@@A2.   @A@@@*           MOVE 8 TO MFDSP-FUNCTION.@D@@@*           ENTER FPH
)@@G@@ORTRAN 'FMFDSP' USING MFDSP-FUNCTION@E@@@*                              PI

)@@G@@@ @@@*           IF MFDSP-A4 NOT = 0@G@@@*               PERFORM MFDSP-SPM

)@@G@@VABLE-DISK  @D@@@*               MOVE NBR-DISC-PACKS TO NBR-DISK-PACKS  PO
)@@G@@@D@@@*               MOVE DISC-PACK-ID-1 TO DISK-PACK-ID-1  @D@@@*      PP
)@@G@@         MOVE DISC-PACK-ID-2 TO DISK-PACK-ID-2  @B@@@*               GO PQ
)@@G@@TO WRITE-JBMFDFIL-RECORD@#@@@*           ELSE   @D@@@*               MOVPR
)@@G@@E MIS1-BACKUP-TDATE TO BACKUP-TDATE @C@@@*               MOVE MIS1-REEL-PS
)@@G@@1 TO BACKUP-REEL-1@C@@@(               MOVE MIS1-REEL-2 TO BACKUP-REEL-2PT
)@@G@@@D@@@(           MOVE MIS1-NO-BACKUP TO NBR-BACKUP-REELS.   @A@(@*      PU
)@@G@@         IF MIS1-NO-BACKUP > 1@D@(@*                   MOVE MIS1-REEL-2 PV
)@@G@@TO BACKUP-REEL-2  @^@(@*               ELSE     @D@(@*                  PW
)@@G@@ MOVE LOW-VALUES TO MIS1-REEL-2.    @@@@@*@ @:@*           IF NOT UNLOADPX
)@@G@@ED    @^@@@:           IF UNLOADED  @B@:@*               GO TO WRITE-JBMPY
)@@G@@FDFIL-RECORD@#@:@*           ELSE   @C@@@*               MOVE SIZE-IN-TRPZ

)@@G@@UAL 10@A@@@*               PERFORM STRING-NAME  @F@@@*               DISQC

)@@G@@@B@@@*               GO TO RETURN-A-RECORD.     @@@@@*@ @@@*       WRITEQF

)@@G@@           ADD 1 TO CNTR.     @A@@@*           GO TO RETURN-A-RECORD.   QH
)@@G@@@@@@@:@@@@@:@ @@@*       MFDSP-STATUS-CHECK-RTN.@ @@@*      ************QI
)@@G@@************@@@@@*@F@@@*           DISPLAY '** FMFDSP ERRORED: REGISTER QJ
)@@G@@DUMP FOLLOWS'     @G@@@*               '  (SEE SYSLIB MANUAL UP-8728 CHAQK
)@@G@@P.6)' UPON PRINTER.     @A@@@*           MOVE SPACES TO FILE-DUMP.@B@@@*QL

)@@G@@RU OCTAL-RTN-END. @G@@@*           EXHIBIT NAMED MFDSP-FUNCTION FILE-DUMQT

)@@G@@@@@___@@@___@@@___@@@___@@^@@]@@A@@[@@C@@^@@S@@@@@@@@A@@@@@HIOW$        EU
)@@G@@C$BRPCIOSHDR@@[@@@@@@@@@RPCIOSHDR   @@[@@@@@@@@@C$BWPCIOSHDR@@[@@@@@@@@]EV
)@@G@@WPCIOSHDR   @@[@@@@@@@@]I(0)**(G -0,0))=(G -0,0)*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@P@L      EW
)@@G@@    AXR$    @B@@@L. CALL 'RPCIOSHDR' USING 'FILE' HDR-BUF.  @B@@@L. CALLEX
)@@G@@ 'WPCIOSHDR' USING 'FILE' HDR-BUF.  @[@@@L.     @A@@@L.   WHERE 'FILE' IEY
)@@G@@S A PCIOS FILENAME@F@P@L.         HDR-BUF IS A BUFFER FOR SECTOR 0 (LABEEZ
)@@G@@L) OF THE FILE    @G@@@P.         HDR-BUF IS A 28-WORD-BUFFER FOR SECTORFA
)@@G@@ 0 (LABEL) OF THE FILE  @[@@@L.     @G@@@L.   THIS SUBROUTINE ALLOWS A PFB
)@@G@@CIOS HEADER TO BE READ AND/OR WRITTEN     @I@@@P.   ITS ORIGINAL JUSTIFIFC
)@@G@@CATION WAS TO ACCESS THE 'HIGHEST RELATIVE KEY WRITTEN'     @G@@@P.   VAFD
)@@G@@LUE FOR A DIRECT-ACCESS FILE.  WHEN THE FILE IS ALWAYS ADDED TO   @G@@@PFE
)@@G@@.   SEQUENTIALLY FROM THE LAST POINT REACHED, THIS KEY VALUE COMPARED TOFF
)@@G@@@G@@@P.   THE 'HIGHEST KEY ALLOWED' FIELD TELLS US QUICKLY AND CHEAPLY HFG
)@@G@@OW    @C@@@P.   NEAR THE FILE IS TO BEING COMPLETELY FULL.  @[@@@L.     FH
)@@G@@@F@@@P.       WRITTEN BY RICHARD STRANGE: SDC/EPA-NCC DECEMBER 1981     FI
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @#@@@P          AXR$    @[@@@L$(0). @A@@@LIOPKT     I$OD    FJ
)@@G@@  ' ',0 28,0,0    @[@@@L$(1). @#@@@LC$BRPCIOSHDR*     @]@@@LRPCIOSHDR*  FK
)@@G@@@C@@@L          L,U       A1,020            . R$ CODE @ @@@L          J FL
)@@G@@        GETFIL    @#@@@LC$BWPCIOSHDR*     @]@@@LWPCIOSHDR*  @C@@@L      FM
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,010            . W$ CODE @E@N@LGETFIL    S,S2      A1,IFN
)@@G@@OPKT+3        . ENTER FUNCTION CODE @E@O@NGETFIL    S,T1      A1,IOPKT+3FO
)@@G@@        . ENTER FUNCTION CODE @E@@@OGETFIL    S,S2      A1,IOPKT+3      FP
)@@G@@  . ENTER FUNCTION CODE @F@@@O          SZ,S1     IOPKT+3           . MAFQ
)@@G@@KE SURE BIT 35 NOT SET  @E@@@L          DL        A1,*1,A0          . GEFR
)@@G@@T PCIOS FILENAME  @D@@@L          DS        A1,IOPKT          . PUT IN IFS
)@@G@@/O PKT@F@@@L          L         A1,2,A0           . GET HEADER BUFFER ADFT
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@L          S,H2      A1,IOPKT+4        . STORE IN I/O PKT    FU
)@@G@@@F@@@L          SZ        IOPKT+5           . MAKE SURE WE GET SECTOR 0 FV
)@@G@@@E@@@L          I$OW      IOPKT             . GET HEADER SECTOR   @B@@@MFW
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             .   @#@@@L          END     _@@@@@FX
)@@G@@^@)ES?ES2^@)^@)^@)CC1 -DD9KDTO S3^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)*[S@@@*SDFF*@F@@@]C THISFY
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE IS CALLED FROM SECUPDATE AND IS USED TO READ THE@F@@@]C SEC-FZ
)@@G@@PRT FILE.   THIS IS NECESSARY BECAUSE COBOL IS SUCH A DISMAL@G@@@]C LANGGA
)@@G@@UAGE THAT AMONGST ALL ITS VERBIAGE IT DOES NOT APPEAR TO HAVE     @G@@@]GB
)@@G@@C ANY MEANS OF GRACEFULLY DETECTING A MISSING SDF-EOF ON AN ALTERNATE   GC
)@@G@@@G@@@]C CARD-READER FILE IT IS READING.   INSTEAD IT GOES STRAIGHT INTO GD
)@@G@@A     @F@@@]C (TYPICALLY UNINFORMATIVE) ER ERR$, LEAVING ANY OTHER COBOLGE
)@@G@@ FILES@H@@@]C UNFORTUNATE (OR UNWISE) ENOUGH STILL TO BE OPEN IN A DOUBTGF
)@@G@@FUL, POSSIBLY     @G@@@]C CORRUPT, STATE.   HENCE 7 TERSE LINES OF OLD-FGG
)@@G@@ASHIONED FORTRAN V TO   @#@@@]C THE RESCUE.     @[@@@]C     @G@@@]C     GH
)@@G@@                    WRITTEN BY RICHARD STRANGE: FEBRUARY 1981     @[@@@]GI
)@@G@@C     @A@@@]      SUBROUTINE RDSPRT(IMG,IOSTAT) @^@@@]      INTEGER IMG(GJ
)@@G@@22)   @#@@@#      CALL SAVEX9 @A@@@]      READ(7,100,END=50,ERR=50) IMG GK
)@@G@@@#@@@]100   FORMAT(22A6)@]@@@]      RETURN@#@@@]50    IOSTAT = 1  @#@ @]GL
)@@G@@      WRITE(6,105)@#@^@]      CALL TON    @#@@@#      CALL RESTX9 @B@ @]GM
)@@G@@105   FORMAT(' ***  RDSPRT LABEL 50  ***')@]@@@]      RETURN@]@@@]      GN
)@@G@@END   _@@@@@CDO C)@A@@@[^@)^@)^@)DDIE- C9 EK)DDHC8*AK2 C)^@)@ @@@#^@)^@)GO
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@#       IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.     @ @@@#       PROGRGP
)@@G@@AM-ID. RELOAD.    @@@@@#@F@@@#      *  WRITTEN BY RICHARD STRANGE - SDC/GQ
)@@G@@ISI RTP OCTOBER 1980    @]@@@#      *     @G@@@#      * THIS PROGRAM ALLGR
)@@G@@OWS USERS TO REQUEST FILE RELOADS FROM SECURE   @G@@@#      * OR REMOVE GS
)@@G@@TAPES.   THEY ARE OFFERED DATES FROM WHICH A RELOAD   @G@@@#      * CAN GT
)@@G@@BE MADE.  SAVED FILENAMES ARE STORED IN FILE SEC-FILES WITH @G@@@#      GU
)@@G@@* AVAILABLE DATES AND KEYS INTO FILE SEC-TAPES WHICH HOLDS THE    @F@@@#GV
)@@G@@      * CORRESPONDING TAPE-NUMBERS.   THE USER'S CHOICE OF DATE IS@G@@@#GW
)@@G@@      * USED TO GET THE TAPE-NUMBER.   THIS NUMBER AND THE FILENAME     GX
)@@G@@@G@@@#      * REQUESTED ARE STORED IN FILE SEC-USERS FROM WHICH USER SERGY
)@@G@@VICES @G@@@#      * RECOVER THE INFORMATION TO BUILD A SECURE RUNSTREAM GZ
)@@G@@WHICH IS    @G@@@#      * FIRED OFF PERIODICALLY DURING PRIME-SHIFT.   THA
)@@G@@HE USER DOES NOT  @G@@@#      * HAVE ACCESS TO THE SECURE TAPE-NUMBERS. HB
)@@G@@  ACCESS TO THE FILES   @G@@@#      * CONTAINING THIS INFORMATION, ALBEIHC
)@@G@@T DISGUISED BY CROSS-INDEXING,@E@@@#      * IS PREVENTED BY DOING I-OPTIHD
)@@G@@ON ASSIGNS INTERNALLY.  @@@@@#@D@@@#      * LEVEL 1.6: BATCH-MODE OPERATHE
)@@G@@ION ADDED (B-OPT) @D@@@#      * LEVEL 1.7: S2K FILE HANDLING    ADDED (KHF
)@@G@@-OPT) @G@@@#      * LEVEL 1.8: CORRECTS FAILURE TO DELETE FILES WITH KEYHG
)@@G@@S (BY ADDING@G@@@#      *            CSF-STATUS-2) - AFTER FIRST FILE,ASHH
)@@G@@KS 'ENTER NEXT...'@I@@@#      *            CHECKS FOR PRIVILEGE BY DIRECHI
)@@G@@T LOOK AT PCT - ALLOWS ENTRY OF     @F@@@#      *            SINGLE CHARHJ
)@@G@@ACTER FILENAMES (OTHER THAN 'S')    @H@@@#      * LEVEL 2.0: HANDLES SECHK
)@@G@@URE SAVES TO CONTINUATION-REELS (DOUBLE-TAPES)  @G@@@#      *           HL
)@@G@@ AND STARTS SECRUN RUNS AFTER 6 PM AND ON SATURDAYS   @I@@@#      * LEVEHM
)@@G@@L 2.1: CSF-MESSAGE USED FOR FILE-DELETE MSG,NEEDED SPACES IN CS-100     HN
)@@G@@@F@@@#      * LEVEL 3.0: MUFS COMPATIBLE - SHARED/LOCAL FILE REQUESTS   HO
)@@G@@@H@@@#      * LEVEL 3.1: CORRECTS ERRORS WITH CYCLES ENTERED IN CC-242 -HP
)@@G@@ CC-249     @E@@@#      *            AND REMOVES B-OPT=0 TEST FROM CG-00HQ
)@@G@@0     @H@@@#      * LEVEL 3.2: LEAVES CG-SECTION FROM CG-910 ONCE AN F-CHR
)@@G@@YCLE IS CHOSEN    @E@@@#      * LEVEL 3.3: NEW EXIT MESSAGE PLUS MINOR CHS
)@@G@@ODE CLEAN-UP@E@@@#      * LEVEL 3.4: PRIVILEGED 'LIST' CAN SELECT TAPE-NHT
)@@G@@UMBER @F@@@#      * LEVEL 3.5: CORRECTS F-CYCLE TESTS IN CC-600 AND CI-0HU
)@@G@@00    @G@@@#      *            DOES INTERNAL CHECK+CAT.OF ALT.OUTFILE INHV
)@@G@@ CH-055     @G@@@#      *            CHECKS VALIDITY OF PRIV.TAPE IN CD-HW
)@@G@@900 NOT CF-000    @F@@@#      * LEVEL 3.6: CORRECTION FOR MAX.CYCLE>HIGHHX
)@@G@@EST IN CI-000     @G@@@#      *            '/S' SUBOPTION ON '@ASG' REMOHY
)@@G@@VED IN BA-100,CH-000,   @A@@@#      *            CH-053,CH-100    @F@@@#HZ
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 4.0: FILE-HOST PIC XX FOR BETTER WORD ALIGNMENT     @G@@@#IA
)@@G@@      *            NO VALID-CYCLE CHECK (CI-..) IN CC-550 IF A DIFFERENTIB
)@@G@@@E@@@#      *            OUTPUT FILE HAS BEEN CHOSEN (IN CH-050)  @H@@@#IC
)@@G@@      *            CHECK EXCL-ASGD-BIT IN CS-115 (ALREADY-.. NOT SET WHEID
)@@G@@N     @A@@@#      *            EXCL.ASSIGNED)   @I@@@#      *           IE
)@@G@@ IF A HOST IS CHOSEN IN CC-299,ONLY THAT HOST SEARCHED IN CG-..   @E@@@#IF
)@@G@@      *            CG-400 RETURNS TO CG-110 WHEN SUB<100    @F@@@#      IG
)@@G@@*            'FORGET' SET TO ZERO IN CC-000 (WAS CB-000)    @D@@@#      IH
)@@G@@* LEVEL 4.1: CT-FIND-PRIOR-ENTRIES SECTION ADDED@F@@@#      *           II
)@@G@@ NO SEC-USERS UPDATE IF ALL ENTRIES ARE REJECTED@D@@@#      *           IJ
)@@G@@ DUPLICATES (CS-120: FILE-COUNT=0)  @G@@@#      * LEVEL 4.2: TEST IF DELIK
)@@G@@ETED FILES STILL ASSIGNED IN CH-120...    @F@@@#      *            DO ACIL
)@@G@@COUNT SWITCH ON ALT.OUTPUT FILE IN CH-058 @B@@@#      *            INSTAIM
)@@G@@LLATION-PROCS USED@C@@@#      * LEVEL 5.0: SEC-TAPES MADE MSAM (WAS SEQ)IN
)@@G@@@D@@@#      *            3 WAIT-STATUS TESTS PUT INTO CS-115@@@@@#@G@@@#IO
)@@G@@      *  IMPORTANT:  THIS CODE MUST BE COMPILED WITH THE @ACOB T-OPTION IP
)@@G@@@@@@@#@ @@@#       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.  @ @@@#       CONFIGURATION SECIQ
)@@G@@TION. @A@@@#       SOURCE-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@A@@@#       OBJECT-COMPIR
)@@G@@UTER. UNIVAC-1110.@ @@@#       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.  @^@@@#       FILE-IS
)@@G@@CONTROL.    @C@@@#           SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO PRINTER.@D@@@#IT
)@@G@@           SELECT  INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO CARD-READER.  @ @@@            CIU
)@@G@@OPY SELECT-TAPES. @D@ @#           SELECT SEC-TAPES  ASSIGN TO DISC  SECIV
)@@G@@-TAPES@B@ @#               ORGANIZATION IS INDEXED    @A@ @#            IW
)@@G@@   ACCESS MODE IS RANDOM@B@ @#               RECORD KEY IS TAPE-KEYX    IX
)@@G@@@C@ @#               ALTERNATE RECORD KEY IS TAPE-NAME@B@ @#            IY
)@@G@@   FILE STATUS IS T-STATUS.   @E@@@#           SELECT  SEC-FILES  ASSIGNIZ
)@@G@@ TO DISC  SEC-FILES     @B@@@#               ORGANIZATION IS INDEXED    JA
)@@G@@@B@@@#               ACCESS MODE IS DYNAMIC     @B@@@#               RECJB
)@@G@@ORD KEY IS SEC-FILE-KEY @B@@@#               FILE STATUS IS F-STATUS.   JC
)@@G@@@D@@@#           SELECT  SEC-USERS  ASSIGN TO DISC SEC-USERS@B@@@#      JD
)@@G@@         ORGANIZATION IS RELATIVE   @B@@@#               ACCESS MODE IS JE
)@@G@@DYNAMIC     @C@@@#               RELATIVE KEY IS SEC-USERS-KEY    @B@@@#JF
)@@G@@               FILE STATUS IS U-STATUS.   @@@@@#@^@@@#       DATA DIVISIJG
)@@G@@ON.   @^@@@#       FILE SECTION.    @^@@@#      ***************   @@@@@#JH
)@@G@@@^@@@#       FD  INPUT-FILE   @B@@@#           LABEL RECORDS ARE OMITTEDJI
)@@G@@.     @C@@@#       01  INPUT-REC              PIC X(84).    @@@@@#@^@@@#JJ
)@@G@@       FD  OUTPUT-FILE  @B@@@#           LABEL RECORDS ARE OMITTED.     JK
)@@G@@@^@@@#       01  OUTPUT-REC.  @C@@@#           03  OUTPUT-LINE        OCJL
)@@G@@CURS 10.    @C@@@#               05  OR-DATE        PIC X(6).     @B@@@#JM

)@@G@@          PIC X(8).     @@@@@#@ @@@#       FD  COPY SEC-TREC.     @@@@@#JO

)@@G@@*AS-SCREEN-DUMP SECTION 1.    @A@@@#      *************************DIAG*TW

)@@G@@= 0   @E@@@#*S-OPT*        DISPLAY '  ****>' INPUT-REC UPON PRINTER.    TY
)@@G@@@@@@@#@A@@@#       AX-CSF-FAILURE SECTION 1.    @ @@@#      ************TZ
)@@G@@************@^@@@#           COPY CSF-PD. @]@@@#      /     @ @@@#      UA
)@@G@@ AY-CODED-CSF SECTION 1.@A@@@#      *************************     @@@@@#UB
)@@G@@@G@@@#      * THIS SECTION ASSEMBLES FILENAMES AND KEYS, E.G. 'SEC-FILESUC
)@@G@@/X/X' @F@@@#      * FROM DISGUISED D-BANK CONTENTS.  THE MAIN STEP IS SIUD
)@@G@@MPLE: @D@@@#      *    E.G.  CODED-JUMBLE + CODED-FILES = '-FILES'@H@@@#UE
)@@G@@      * BUT IN THE D-BANK NEITHER CODED-JUMBLE NOR CODED-FILES SHOULD LOUF
)@@G@@OK    @G@@@#      * LIKE '-FILES', ONLY AFTER BINARY ADDITION DO THEY GIUG
)@@G@@VE A NUMBER @E@@@#      * WHICH WHEN TREATED AS A FIELDATA STRING IS '-FUH
)@@G@@ILES'.@H@@@#      * ALL THE OTHER MESSING AROUND WITH CALLS TO 'TIME', QUI
)@@G@@UOTIENTS ETC.     @G@@@#      * IS ONLY TO MUDDY THE TRAIL.  IT MAY BE HUJ
)@@G@@ARD TO FOLLOW HERE:  IT @G@@@#      * IS MEANT TO BE INCOMPREHENSIBLE TOUK
)@@G@@ ANY ONE TRYING TO GET THE    @H@@@#      * FILENAMES AND KEYS BY UNSCRAUL
)@@G@@MBLING A POSTMORTEM I- AND D-BANK DUMP.   @@@@@#@G@@@#      * TO CALCULAUM
)@@G@@TE THE VALUE OF 'CODED-TAPES' THAT IS USED TO CREATE  @E@@@#      * THE UN
)@@G@@STRING '-TAPES', FOR EXAMPLE, DO AS FOLLOWS:    @^@@@#      *   @ASG,T XUO
)@@G@@.     @#@@@#      *   @ED,I X.@#@@@#      *   -TAPES  @ @@@#      *   @WUP
)@@G@@ORK.FILEDIT X.    @E@@@#      *   A 1,4                   . '-TAPES' IS UQ
)@@G@@IN WORD 4   @F@@@#      *   C 1,'@#@$@&'            . PUT CODED-JUMBLE IUR
)@@G@@N WORD 1    @F@@@#      *   ADD 1@1,-(1@4)          . GIVES DECIMAL 3291US
)@@G@@5398029     @@@@@#@A@@@#      *  CODED-FILE1 GIVES 'ER*SEC' @A@@@#      UT
)@@G@@*  CODED-FILE3 GIVES '/X/X  ' @A@@@#      *  CODED-FILES GIVES '-FILES' UU
)@@G@@@A@@@#      *  CODED-TAPES GIVES '-TAPES' @A@@@#      *  CODED-USERS GIVUV
)@@G@@ES '-USERS' @@@@@#@#@@@#       AY-000.    @B@@@#           MOVE CODED-FIUW
)@@G@@LE1 TO CODED-F1.  @B@@@#           MOVE CODED-FILE3 TO CODED-F3.  @^@@@#UX
)@@G@@           IF SUB1 = 1  @C@@@#               MOVE CODED-FILES TO CODED-FUY
)@@G@@2.    @^@@@#           IF SUB1 = 2  @C@@@#               MOVE CODED-TAPEUZ
)@@G@@S TO CODED-F2.    @^@@@#           IF SUB1 = 3  @C@@@#               MOVVA
)@@G@@E CODED-USERS TO CODED-F2.    @A@@@#           CALL 'TIME' USING TIME1. VB
)@@G@@@D@@@#           DIVIDE CODED-F1 BY TIME1 GIVING CODING-Q1  @D@@@#      VC
)@@G@@                           REMAINDER CODING-R1. @D@@@#           ADD CODVD
)@@G@@ING-R1 CODED-JUMBLE GIVING SUB4.    @C@@@#           SUBTRACT CODING-R1 VE
)@@G@@FROM CODED-F1.    @C@@@#           SUBTRACT CODING-R1 FROM CODED-F2.    VF
)@@G@@@C@@@#           SUBTRACT CODING-R1 FROM CODED-F3.    @A@@@#           AVG
)@@G@@DD SUB4 TO CODED-F1.    @A@@@#           ADD SUB4 TO CODED-F2.    @A@@@#VH
)@@G@@           ADD SUB4 TO CODED-F3.    @B@@@#           MOVE '    US' TO CSVI
)@@G@@F-QUALIFIER.@C@@@#           MOVE CODED-FILENAME TO CSF-FILENAME. @A@@@#VJ
)@@G@@           MOVE ' . ' TO CSF-PERIOD.@D@@@#           CALL 'CSF' USING CSVK
)@@G@@F-STATUS CSF-MESSAGE.   @E@@@#           IF ROLLED-OUT-BIT = 0  AND  EXCVL
)@@G@@L-ASGD-BIT = 0    @ @@@#               GO TO AY-999.  @@@@@#@F@@@#      VM
)@@G@@*   IF A FILE IS ROLLED OUT, ASSIGN OTHERS IN CASE THEY     @G@@@#      VN
)@@G@@*   ARE ALSO, BEFORE ENDING PROGRAM.   EXCLUSIVE USE CONFLICT     @H@@@#VO
)@@G@@      *    SHOULD ONLY ARISE ON SEC-FILES OR SEC-TAPES IF A 'SECUPDATE' VP
)@@G@@RUN IS@A@@@#      *    ACTIVE AND UPDATING THEM.@H@@@#      *   SHOULD OVQ
)@@G@@NLY ARISE WITH FILE SEC-USERS IN USE IN RUN 45FILE WHICH    @C@@@#      VR
)@@G@@*   IS @START-ED FROM RUNSTREAM.SECRUN    @@@@@#@#@@@#       AY-600.    VS
)@@G@@@B@@@#           IF REQUEST-ACCEPTED-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@#               PERVT
)@@G@@FORM AY-700 THRU AY-710.@A@@@#           IF EXCL-ASGD-BIT NOT = 0 @ @@@#VU
)@@G@@               GO TO AY-999.  @ @@@#           ADD 1 TO SUB1.     @ @@@#VV
)@@G@@           IF SUB1 NOT > 3    @ @@@#               PERFORM AY-000 @ @@@#VW
)@@G@@               GO TO AY-600.  @B@@@#           PERFORM AB-ERROR-TERMINATVX
)@@G@@ION.  @@@@@#@#@@@#       AY-700.    @ @@@#           MOVE 0 TO SUB.     VY
)@@G@@@#@@@#       AY-710.    @^@@@#           ADD 1 TO SUB.@^@@@#           IVZ
)@@G@@F SUB < 13  @D@@@#               MOVE CSF-BYTE(SUB) TO CSF-OCTAL(SUB)   WA
)@@G@@@ @@@#               GO TO AY-710.  @F@@@#           DISPLAY 'A FILE REQWB
)@@G@@UIRED INTERNALLY IS TEMPORARILY '   @G@@@#               'UNAVAILABLE: CWC
)@@G@@ODE=' SUB1 ' STATUS=' CSF-OCTAL-DIGITS    @ @@@#                  UPON PWD
)@@G@@RINTER@^@@@#           IF SUB < 3   @F@@@#               DISPLAY 'PLEASEWE
)@@G@@ WAIT 15 MINUTES THEN TRY AGAIN'    @C@@@#                              WF
)@@G@@ UPON PRINTER.    @@@@@#@#@@@#       AY-999.    @#@@@#           EXIT.  WG
)@@G@@@]@@@#      /     @A@@@#       BA-RUN-SET-UP SECTION 50.    @ @@@#      WH
)@@G@@********************    @@@@@#@#@@@#       BA-000.    @C@@@#           CWI
)@@G@@ALL 'ORIGIN' USING SUB HOST-ID.     @ @@@#           COPY RELOAD-HOST-1.WJ
)@@G@@@C@@@#           CALL 'OPTION' USING OPTION-WORD.     @B@@@#           IWK
)@@G@@F SUB = 6  AND  D-OPT = 0     @A@@@#               MOVE 1 TO B-OPT.     WL
)@@G@@@A@@@#           OPEN  INPUT  INPUT-FILE  @A@@@#                OUTPUT OWM
)@@G@@UTPUT-FILE. @@@@@#@H@@@#      * 'RELOAD' IS A PROCESSOR CALL (NOT @XQT) WN
)@@G@@SO A FIRST READ IS NECESSARY  @F@@@#      *  TO GET (AND DISCARD, IN THIWO
)@@G@@S PROGRAM) THE INFOR-TABLE.   @@@@@#@F@@@#           READ INPUT-FILE  ATWP
)@@G@@ END PERFORM AB-ERROR-TERMINATION.  @@@@@#@F@@@#           CALL 'DATE' UWQ
)@@G@@SING DATE-WORD TIME-WORD DAY-OF-WEEK.     @C@@@#           MOVE DATE-WORWR
)@@G@@D TO USER-RUN-DATE.     @C@@@#           MOVE TIME-WORD TO USER-RUN-TIMEWS
)@@G@@.     @E@@@#           DISPLAY 'RELOAD 5.0 ' TIME-WORD ' ' DATE-WORD    WT
)@@G@@@C@@@#               ' FILE RELOAD REQUEST PROGRAM'   @C@@@#            WU
)@@G@@   ' ON ' HOST-ID UPON PRINTER.     @@@@@#@ @@@#           IF T-OPT NOT WV
)@@G@@= 0   @C@@@#               ACCEPT TIME-WORD FROM CARD-READER@C@@@#      WW
)@@G@@         ACCEPT DATE-WORD FROM CARD-READER@D@@@#               ACCEPT DAWX
)@@G@@Y-OF-WEEK FROM CARD-READER    @F@@@#               EXHIBIT NAMED 'T-OPT WY
)@@G@@USING' TIME-WORD DATE-WORD    @A@@@#                   DAY-OF-WEEK.     WZ
)@@G@@@A@@@#           CALL 'PRIVCK' USING SUB. @^@@@#           IF SUB = 0   XA
)@@G@@@ @@@#               MOVE 0 TO L-OPT@ @@@#               GO TO BA-100.  XB
)@@G@@@B@@@#           MOVE 1 TO PRIVILEGED-ACCESS.   @ @@@#           IF B-OPXC
)@@G@@T NOT = 0   @ @@@#               MOVE 1 TO L-OPT@ @@@#               GO XD
)@@G@@TO BA-100.  @E@@@#           DISPLAY 'DO YOU WANT TAPE NUMBERS DISPLAYEDXE
)@@G@@?'    @C@@@#               '  ANSWER: YES/NO' UPON PRINTER. @B@@@#      XF
)@@G@@     READ INPUT-FILE INTO SCREEN-REC@D@@@#               AT END PERFORM XG
)@@G@@AB-ERROR-TERMINATION.   @ @@@#           IF SCREEN1 = 'Y'   @A@@@#      XH

)@@G@@  ),F(301),.. ETC.,     @G@@@#      * HENCE, IN THIS EXAMPLE, IF THERE ITC

)@@G@@ECK-VALID-CYCLE-LOAD SECTION 51.    @B@@@#      ************************ZY
)@@G@@************@@@@@#@G@@@#      * YOU CAN'T CATALOGUE, AND SO CAN'T RECOVEZZ
)@@G@@R, ANY FILE-CYCLE WHICH @G@@@#      * LIES BELOW THE MAX-RANGE SPECIFIEDAA
)@@G@@ FOR THE FILE.  FOR EXAMPLE,  @G@@@#      * IF THE MAX-RANGE IS 3 AND CYAB
)@@G@@CLES 9,8,7 EXIST, YOU CAN'T RECOVER @I@@@#      * CYCLE 5.  ALSO, YOU CAAC
)@@G@@NNOT CATALOGUE A CYCLE GREATER THAN (LOWEST+RANGE),   @H@@@#      * E.G.AD
)@@G@@ IN THE ABOVE EXAMPLE, CYCLES 11 AND HIGHER (I.E. >(7+3) ) MAY    @H@@@#AE
)@@G@@      * NOT BE CATALOGED.   ?ADDING A CYCLE TO A RANGE THAT IS ALREADY FAF
)@@G@@ULL   @H@@@#      * CAUSES DELETION OF THE BOTTOM CYCLE, E.G. CATALOGUEIAG
)@@G@@NG CYCLE 10 WILL  @E@@@#      * CAUSE DELETION OF CYCLE 7 WHEN THE MAX RAH
)@@G@@ANGE IS 3.  @G@@@#      * THIS SECTION CHECKS FOR THESE CONDITIONS.   NOAI
)@@G@@N-PRIVILEGED USERS@G@@@#      * ARE TOLD TO CONTACT USER SERVICES.   PRIAJ
)@@G@@VILEGED USERS ARE ASKED @H@@@#      * TO SPECIFY A DIFFERENT FILENAME INAK
)@@G@@TO WHICH THE FILE WILL BE RELOADED. @@@@@#@#@@@#       CI-000.    @B@@@#AL
)@@G@@           MOVE SPACES TO FILE-ASG-NAME.  @G@@@#           UNSTRING QUALAM
)@@G@@-FNAME DELIMITED BY '(' INTO FILE-ASG-NAME.     @C@@@#           MOVE '@AN
)@@G@@ASG,AYI' TO FILE-COMMAND.     @D@@@#           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATAO
)@@G@@US FILE-CARD.     @ @@@#           IF NOT-CAT-BIT = 1 @ @@@#            AP
)@@G@@   GO TO CI-999.  @@@@@#@C@@@#           MOVE '@USE DR$F$N,' TO FILE-COMAQ
)@@G@@MAND. @D@@@#           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS FILE-CARD.     @A@@@#AR
)@@G@@           MOVE 0 TO DRD-ST-ITEM.   @D@@@#           CALL 'MSCON' USING AS
)@@G@@DREAD-PKT DRD-STATUS    @D@@@#                              LEAD-ITEM-SEAT
)@@G@@CTOR-0.     @@@@@#@G@@@#      * SUB4 = LOWEST CYCLE ALLOWED (HIGHEST CURAU

)@@G@@(HIGHEST CUURENT-CURRENT RANGE+1)   @@@@@#@F@@@#           SUBTRACT CURRAY
)@@G@@-RANGE FROM HIGHEST-CYCLE GIVING SUB2.    @ @@@#           ADD 1 TO SUB2AZ
)@@G@@.     @@@@@#@E@@@#      * SUB3 = HIGHEST CYCLE ALLOWED (CURRENT BOTTOM+RBA
)@@G@@ANGE) @@@@@#@B@@@#           ADD SUB2 MAX-RANGE GIVING SUB3.@^@@@#      BB
)@@G@@     IF SUB3 > 999@B@@@#               SUBTRACT 999 FROM SUB3.    @@@@@#BC

)@@G@@               GO TO CI-999.  @@@@@#@H@@@#      * CHECK FOR SPECIAL CASEBF

)@@G@@WED IS 995 AND HIGHEST IS 3   @@@@@#@ @@@#           IF SUB3 < SUB4     BI
)@@G@@@D@@@#               IF SUB1 > SUB4  OR  SUB1 NOT > SUB3    @A@@@#      BJ
)@@G@@             GO TO CI-999.    @@@@@#@H@@@#      * NEXT CHECK FOR LOAD OFBK

)@@G@@@H@@@#      * THIS SAVES A LITTLE PROCESSING TIME DURING THE SECURE/@PRTCQ
)@@G@@,F/CHGREF   @H@@@#      * PHASE OF SECRUN, BUT IN PARTICULAR IT PREVENTSCR
)@@G@@ ERROR IN SECLOADMSG.   @H@@@#      * WITH TWO ENTRIES, THERE WOULD BE TCS
)@@G@@WO SEC-HIST KEYS PUT OUT BY SECRUN  @G@@@#      * SO TWO SECURE LOADS WOCT
)@@G@@ULD BE LOOKED FOR BY SECLOADMSG.  HOWEVER @H@@@#      * SECURE ONLY PUTSCU
)@@G@@ OUT ONE LOAD-MESSAGE FOR A DUPLICATE LOAD REQUEST,   @H@@@#      * SO SCV
)@@G@@ECLOADMSG WOULD THINK A SECURE LOAD WAS MISSING AND REPORT IT     @C@@@#CW
)@@G@@      * AS AN ERROR - WHICH IT ISN'T REALLY.    @@@@@#@#@@@#       CJ-00CX

)@@G@@       CK-SYMBOL-CHECK SECTION 51.  @A@@@#      ************************DU
)@@G@@****  @@@@@#@#@@@#       CK-000.    @B@@@#           MOVE SPACES TO AFTEDV
)@@G@@R-SYMBOL.   @B@@@#           MOVE FILE-STRING TO DUMP18.    @@@@@#@#@@@#DW
)@@G@@       CK-100.    @E@@@#           UNSTRING DUMP18 DELIMITED BY SYMBOL(SDX
)@@G@@YMBOL-INDEX)@B@@@#                    INTO BEFORE-SYMBOL    @B@@@#      DY
)@@G@@              DELIMITER DELIM1,     @A@@@#                    COUNT     DZ
)@@G@@CNT1, @A@@@#                    AFTER-SYMBOL    @B@@@#                  EA
)@@G@@  DELIMITER DELIM2.     @ @@@#           IF DELIM1 = SPACE  @B@@@#      EB
)@@G@@         GO TO CK-SYMBOL-CHECK-END. @@@@@#@H@@@#      *    DELIM2 IS EITEC
)@@G@@HER SPACE (= END OF DUMP18) OR THE SYMBOL I.E. THERE  @H@@@#      *    WED
)@@G@@ERE TWO OCCURENCES OF THE SAME SYMBOL IN THE DUMP18.  IN THIS     @G@@@#EE
)@@G@@      *    CASE, AFTER-SYMBOL WILL NOT CONTAIN ALL THE REST OF THE NAME EF
)@@G@@@G@@@#      *    BUT ONLY THE BIT UP TO AND EXCLUDING THE SECOND OCCURENEG
)@@G@@CE OF @G@@@#      *    THE SYMBOL.  SO WE MUST UNSTRING THE WHOLE OF DUMEH
)@@G@@P18 FROM THE@D@@@#      *    FIRST SYMBOL OCCURENCE INTO AFTER-SYMBOL.  EI
)@@G@@@G@@@#      *    EXAMPLE:  IF DUMP18 STARTED AS ABC#DEF#G WITH # AS A SYEJ
)@@G@@MBOL, @E@@@#      *       AFTER THE UNSTRING ABOVE, BEFORE-SYMBOL = ABC EK
)@@G@@@E@@@#      *                                 AFTER-SYMBOL  = DEF @F@@@#EL
)@@G@@      *       AND WE WOULD END WITH AN EXPANDED STRING = ABCXYZDEF@F@@@#EM
)@@G@@      *       INSTEAD OF ABCXYZDEFXYZG  (SYMBOL # REPRESENTS XYZ) @G@@@#EN
)@@G@@      *       TO DETECT THIS SITUATION, WE CHECK DELIM2.  IF IT IS NOT  EO
)@@G@@@G@@@#      *       A SPACE, THERE WAS A SECOND OCCURENCE OF SYMBOL AND EP
)@@G@@THE   @G@@@#      *       UNSTRING BELOW RECONSTRUCTS AFTER-SYMBOL TO BEEQ
)@@G@@ 'DEF#G'.   @G@@@#      *       THUS, AT THE END OF THE FIRST PASS, THE ER
)@@G@@EXPANDED DUMP18   @G@@@#      *       IS ABCXYZDEF#G, AND THE SECOND PASES
)@@G@@S WILL COMPLETE THE     @^@@@#      *       EXPANSION.@@@@@#@A@@@#      ET
)@@G@@     IF DELIM2 NOT = SPACE    @ @@@#               ADD 2 TO CNT1  @D@@@#EU
)@@G@@               UNSTRING DUMP18 DELIMITED BY SPACE     @C@@@#            EV
)@@G@@                  INTO AFTER-SYMBOL @C@@@#                              EW
)@@G@@POINTER CNT1.     @D@@@#           STRING BEFORE-SYMBOL DELIMITED BY SPAEX
)@@G@@CES   @F@@@#                  SYMBOL-STRING(SYMBOL-INDEX) DELIMITED BY SEY
)@@G@@PACE  @D@@@#                  AFTER-SYMBOL  DELIMITED BY SPACES   @ @@@#EZ
)@@G@@                  INTO DUMP18.@A@@@#           IF DELIM1 NOT = SPACE    FA
)@@G@@@ @@@#               GO TO CK-100.  @ @@@#       CK-SYMBOL-CHECK-END.   FB
)@@G@@@B@@@#           MOVE DUMP18 TO FILE-STRING.    @]@@@#      /     @A@@@#FC
)@@G@@       CL-S2K-LATEST SECTION 51.    @A@@@#      ************************FD

)@@G@@ CT-FIND-PRIOR-ENTRIES SECTION 52.  @B@@@#      ************************PA
)@@G@@*********** @@@@@#@G@@@#      * THIS SECTION CHECKS WHETHER ANY OF THE FPB
)@@G@@ILES ENTERED IN THIS    @F@@@#      * EXECUTION OF 'RELOAD' WERE ENTEREDPC
)@@G@@ IN A PREVIOUS 'RELOAD' @G@@@#      * EXECUTION SINCE THE LAST RUN OF 'SPD
)@@G@@ECRUN'.   THIS CHECK IS DONE  @G@@@#      * BECAUSE DUPLICATE ENTRIES CAPE
)@@G@@USE ERRORS IN THE FILE-LOADING RUNS @G@@@#      * (45FIL0 ETC) GENERATEDPF
)@@G@@ BY 'SECRUN' I.E. THE 'FOUND AS CYCLE 1'  @F@@@#      * MESSAGE.   IF A PG
)@@G@@USER ENTERS A FILE TWICE BECAUSE HE HAS   @G@@@#      * WAITED MORE THANPH
)@@G@@ AN HOUR FOR IT TO COME BACK, THAT MIGHT BE     @H@@@#      * BECAUSE 'SPI
)@@G@@ECRUN' HAS ERRORED OR IS NOT IN BACKLOG.   THE MESSAGES     @G@@@#      PJ
)@@G@@* ON FILE ENTRY DATE/TIME MAY CAUSE THE USER TO CONTACT US TO     @G@@@#PK
)@@G@@      * QUERY THIS, WHICH MAY BE OUR FIRST INDICATION OF THE ERROR.     PL
)@@G@@@@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-000.    @B@@@#           MOVE 0 TO DUPLICATE-ENTRYPM

)@@G@@           EXIT.  @@@@@#@G@@@#      * FOR EACH FILENAME READ OFF SEC-USEQF
)@@G@@RS, CHECK FOR A MATCH AGAINST @G@@@#      * EVERY FILE ENTERED DURING THQG
)@@G@@IS EXECUTION OF 'RELOAD' (I.E. ALL  @ @@@#      * TABLE-F-DATA ENTRIES).QH
)@@G@@@@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-500.    @E@@@#           IF TABLE-FNAME(TABLE-INDEQI
)@@G@@X) NOT = USER-FILENAME  @ @@@#               GO TO CT-599.  @C@@@#      QJ
)@@G@@     IF USER-OFNAME NOT = LOW-VALUES  AND @E@@@#                        QK
)@@G@@  NOT = TABLE-OFNAME(TABLE-INDEX)   @ @@@#               GO TO CT-599.  QL
)@@G@@@G@@@#           DISPLAY 'A REQUEST TO LOAD FILE ' USER-FILENAME UPON PRQM
)@@G@@INTER.@B@@@#           IF USER-OFNAME NOT = LOW-VALUES@F@@@#            QN
)@@G@@   DISPLAY 'INTO FILE ' USER-OFNAME UPON PRINTER.     @E@@@#           DQO
)@@G@@ISPLAY 'FROM ' USER-TAPE-DATE ' WAS MADE BY '   @B@@@#               USEQP
)@@G@@R-NAME UPON PRINTER.    @E@@@#           DISPLAY 'AT ' USER-RUN-TIME ' OQQ
)@@G@@N ' USER-RUN-DATE @ @@@#               UPON PRINTER.  @G@@@#           DQR
)@@G@@ISPLAY 'ONLY ONE FILE OF THIS NAME CAN BE CATALOGED AND '   @B@@@#      QS
)@@G@@         'RELOADED' UPON PRINTER.   @G@@@#           DISPLAY 'SHOULD THEQT
)@@G@@ CURRENT REQUEST REPLACE THE EARLIER ONE?'@C@@@#               '  ANSWERQU
)@@G@@: Y/N' UPON PRINTER.    @ @@@#           IF B-OPT NOT = 0   @G@@@#      QV
)@@G@@        DISPLAY 'BATCH-MODE ASSUMES ANSWER IS ''NO''' UPON PRINTER@A@@@#QW
)@@G@@               MOVE 'N' TO SCREEN1  @ @@@#               GO TO CT-550.  QX
)@@G@@@B@@@#           IF INPUT-FILE-OPEN-SWITCH = 0  @C@@@#               MOVQY
)@@G@@E 1 TO INPUT-FILE-OPEN-SWITCH @B@@@#               OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILEQZ
)@@G@@.     @B@@@#           READ INPUT-FILE INTO SCREEN-REC@D@@@#            RA
)@@G@@   AT END PERFORM AB-ERROR-TERMINATION.   @@@@@#@G@@@#      * A 1-WORD FRB
)@@G@@LAG OF '******' IS SET IN THE TAPE-NUMBER-1 FIELD OF  @H@@@#      * EITHRC
)@@G@@ER THE SEC-USERS RECORD OR THE CURRENT RUN ENTRY IN TABLE-F-DATA  @C@@@#RD
)@@G@@      * TO INDICATE THAT IT IS TO BE IGNORED.   @@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-55RE
)@@G@@0.    @A@@@#           IF SCREEN1 NOT = 'Y'     @B@@@#               ADDRF
)@@G@@ 1 TO DUPLICATE-ENTRY   @E@@@#               MOVE '******' TO TABLE-TAPERG
)@@G@@1(TABLE-INDEX)    @#@@@#           ELSE   @C@@@#               MOVE '***RH
)@@G@@***' TO USER-TAPE-NO    @F@@@#               REWRITE SEC-USERS-RECORD FRRI
)@@G@@OM USER-FILE-RECORD     @C@@@#                   INVALID KEY GO TO CT-90RJ
)@@G@@2.    @B@@@#           SET TABLE-INDEX TO FILE-COUNT. @#@@@#       CT-59RK
)@@G@@9.    @A@@@#           SET TABLE-INDEX UP BY 1. @@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-90RL
)@@G@@0.    @G@@@#           DISPLAY 'CT-900: FAILED TO READ USER-FILE HEADER-RM
)@@G@@RECORD'     @D@@@#               ': STATUS = ' U-STATUS UPON PRINTER.   RN
)@@G@@@^@@@#           GO TO CT-990.@@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-901.    @F@@@#      RO

)@@G@@         SEC-USERS-KEY ': STATUS = ' U-STATUS UPON PRINTER. @^@@@#      RQ
)@@G@@     GO TO CT-990.@@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-902.    @F@@@#           DISPLAYRR
)@@G@@ 'CT-902: FAILED TO REWRITE USER-FILE-RECORD'   @G@@@#               'USRS
)@@G@@ER-FILE-RECORD : STATUS = ' U-STATUS UPON PRINTER.    @^@@@#           GRT
)@@G@@O TO CT-990.@@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-990.    @D@@@#           MOVE SAVE-USERU
)@@G@@R-RECORD TO USER-NAME-RECORD. @@@@@#@#@@@#       CT-999.    @C@@@#      RV

)@@G@@@#@@@[XA-DATES PROC     @]@@@[      /     @A@@@[       XA-DATE-CONVERSIOPF
)@@G@@N SECTION.  @A@@@[      ***************************** @@@@@[@#@@@[      PG
)@@G@@ XA-000.    @@@@@[@E@@@[      * CHECK FOR LEAP-YEAR: IF SO, INCREMENT FEPH
)@@G@@B DAYS.     @@@@@[@F@@@[           DIVIDE 4 INTO SUB3 GIVING LEAP-CNT REPI
)@@G@@MAINDER SUB2.     @^@@@[           IF SUB2 = 0  @ @@@[               MOVPJ
)@@G@@E 29 TO FEB @#@@@[           ELSE   @ @@@[               MOVE 28 TO FEB.PK
)@@G@@@@@@@[@G@@@[      * IF RUN STARTED AFTER MIDNIGHT BUT BEFORE PRIME-SHIFTPL
)@@G@@ (0700 HRS) @A@@@[      * DATE AS THE PREVIOUS DAY    @@@@@[@^@@@[      PM
)@@G@@     IF RUN-HR > 7@ @@@[               GO TO XA-100.  @A@@@[           SPN
)@@G@@UBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-DD.  @ @@@[           IF RUN-DD NOT = 0  @ @@@[      PO
)@@G@@         GO TO XA-100.  @A@@@[           SUBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-MM.  @^@@@[PP
)@@G@@           IF RUN-MM = 0@B@@@[               MOVE 12 TO RUN-MM SUB1     PQ
)@@G@@@B@@@[               SUBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-YY SUB3@#@@@[           ELSE   PR
)@@G@@@A@@@[               MOVE RUN-MM TO SUB1. @C@@@[           MOVE MONTH-DAPS
)@@G@@YS(SUB1) TO RUN-DD.     @@@@@[@#@@@[       XA-100.    @A@@@[           MPT
)@@G@@OVE RUN-MM TO SUB1.     @@@@@[@G@@@[      * CALCULATE NO. OF DAYS SINCE PU
)@@G@@1/1/64, ALLOWING FOR LEAP-YEARS     @@@@@[@D@@@[           COMPUTE JULIAPV
)@@G@@N-CNT = SUB3 * 365 + LEAP-CNT @F@@@[                                 + JPW
)@@G@@ULIAN-DAYS(SUB1) + RUN-DD.    @@@@@[@I@@@[      * IF THIS IS A LEAP-YEARPX
)@@G@@ (SUB2=0) AND WE ARE PAST FEBRUARY (SUB1>2),ADD 1     @@@@@[@A@@@[      PY
)@@G@@     IF SUB2 = 0 AND SUB1 > 2 @A@@@[               ADD 1 TO JULIAN-CNT. PZ
)@@G@@@@@@@[@G@@@[      * CALCULATE PSEUDO-BINARY DATE (MMDD -PIC 9999- HELD AQA
)@@G@@S BINARY)   @@@@@[@A@@@[           MOVE RUN-MM TO RUN-M.    @A@@@[      QB
)@@G@@     MOVE RUN-DD TO RUN-D.    @B@@@[           MOVE RUN-DATE2 TO PB-DATEQC
)@@G@@.     @A@@@[           MOVE RUN-YY TO RUN-Y.    @B@@@[           MOVE RUQD
)@@G@@N-MDY-9 TO TAPE-DATE.   @@@@@[@[@@@[ END  @#@@@ MFD-MAIN-0  PROC  @H@@@ QE
)@@G@@      * CONTENTS OF SECTOR-0 OF THE MAIN ITEM OF THE MASTER-FILE-DIRECTOQF
)@@G@@RY    @H@@@       *     WORDS 0 AND 16 ARE RESET IN 'GETDIR' TO THE FIRSQG
)@@G@@T 2 REMOVABLE     @D@@@       *        DISC PACK-IDS (TAKEN FROM SECTOR QH
)@@G@@1)    @G@@@       *        OR BACKUP REELS 1+2 IF THE FILE IS ON FOXED MQI
)@@G@@ASS-STORAGE @E@@@       *        (TAKEN FROM WORD 11,12 OF SECTOR 1 MAINQJ
)@@G@@ ITEM)@H@@@       *     WORD 11 BIT 30 IS SET IF THE FILE IS SHARED (THEQK
)@@G@@ ORIGINAL FLAG IN @H@@@       *     WORD 16 IS OVERWRITTEN WHEN THE WORDQL
)@@G@@ IS USED FOR DISC/BACKUP ID)  @G@@@       *     WORD 12 BITS 5-0 ARE ALSQM
)@@G@@O SET TO THE NUMBER OF DISC-PACKS   @H@@@       *     WORD 12 BITS 23-18QN
)@@G@@ ARE SET TO THE NO. OF BACKUP REELS (FROM MAIN  @B@@@       *        ITEQO
)@@G@@M SECTOR 1 WORD 7/T1)   @H@@@       *     WORD 14 IS SET TO THE TDATE$ OQP
)@@G@@F BACKUP-FILE CREATION (TAKEN FROM  @B@@@       *        MAINITEM SECTORQQ
)@@G@@ 1 WORD 8)  @@@@@ @H@@@       *    'NEW' IN CC 1-4 INDICATES FIELDS WHICQR
)@@G@@H ARE INTENDED TO BE USED     @E@@@       *    BUT WHICH ARE NOT YET SETQS
)@@G@@ AND/OR USABLE RELIABLY @@@@@ @C@@@            05  DISK-PACK-ID-1     PIQT
)@@G@@C X(6).     @D@@@            05  BACKUP-REEL-1 REDEFINES DISK-PACK-ID-1.QU
)@@G@@@C@@@                10  BACKUP-REEL-1-1 PIC XXX.     @C@@@             QV

)@@G@@ IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.     @A@@@#       PROGRAM-ID. SECBCKUPCHEK.    CM
)@@G@@@H@@@#      * THIS PROGRAM COMPARES THE CURRENT BACKUP ENTRY IN THE MFD CN
)@@G@@WITH THE    @H@@@#      * LATEST AVAILABLE BACKUP ACCORDING TO 'RELOAD'.CO
)@@G@@  IF BACKUPS DO NOT     @H@@@#      * MATCH OR A FILE IN THE MFD IS NOT CP
)@@G@@IN SEC-FILES, THE 'RELOAD' FILES ARE@G@@@#      * UPDATED TO REFLECT THECQ
)@@G@@, PRESUMABLY MORE UP-T0-DATE, MFD ENTRY.  @G@@@#      * DISCREPANCIES CACR
)@@G@@N OCCUR IF, FOR EXAMPLE, 'SECURE' IS USED TO    @G@@@#      * UNLOAD PACCS
)@@G@@KS, WHICH UPDATES THE MFD BUT DOES NOT GET TRAPPED BY @H@@@#      * 'RELCT
)@@G@@OAD' AS IT IS NOT ONE OF THE STANDARD SAVE/REMOVE RUNS PROCESSED  @^@@@#CU
)@@G@@      * BY 'SECUPDATE'. @]@@@#      *     @A@@@#      * LEVEL 1.0: INITICV
)@@G@@AL RELEASE  @G@@@#      * LEVEL 1.1: FILE-HOST PIC XX.   FILE UPDATES ONCW
)@@G@@LY DONE IF MFD IS @C@@@#      *            MORE UP-TO-DATE THAN RELOAD  CX
)@@G@@@C@@@#      * LEVEL 1.2: INSTALLATION-PROCS USED.     @C@@@#      * LEVECY
)@@G@@L 2.0: SEC-TAPES MADE MSAM (WAS SEQ)@]@@@#      *     @ @@@#       ENVIRCZ
)@@G@@ONMENT DIVISION.  @ @@@#       CONFIGURATION SECTION. @A@@@#       SOURCDA
)@@G@@E-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@A@@@#       OBJECT-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@ @@@#DB

)@@G@@           IF TDATE-DUMP-D = TDATE-D@ @@@#               GO TO BA-500.  KZ
)@@G@@@ @@@#           IF J-OPT NOT = 0   @ @@@#               GO TO BA-500.  LA
)@@G@@@@@@@#@E@@@#      * 'MFDFIL' NOT CATALOGUED ON SAME DAY AS THIS RUN     LB
)@@G@@@@@@@#@E@@@#           SUBTRACT DAYC-CAT FROM DAYC-RUN GIVING SUB1.     LC
)@@G@@@^@@@#           IF SUB1 > 1  @ @@@#               GO TO BA-200.  @@@@@#LD
)@@G@@@G@@@#      * 'MFDFIL' WAS CATALOGUED THE PREVIOUS DAY.  CALCULATE NO.SELE
)@@G@@CONDS @F@@@#      * BETWEEN CATALOG TIME AND NOW      [ 24*60*60 = 86400LF
)@@G@@ ]    @@@@@#@E@@@#           SUBTRACT TDATE-DUMP-T FROM 86400 GIVING SUBLG
)@@G@@1.    @@@@@#@C@@@#      * ADD SECONDS SINCE MIDNIGHT FOR THIS RUN @@@@@#LH
)@@G@@@A@@@#           ADD TDATE-T TO SUB1.     @@@@@#@F@@@#      * IF 'MFDFILLI
)@@G@@' IS MORE THAN 6 HOURS (6*60*60=21600) OLD,     @D@@@#      * DON'T USE LJ

)@@G@@00    @ @@@#               GO TO BA-500.  @G@@@#           MOVE '**WARNILL

)@@G@@PREC. @ @@@#           WRITE PREC AFTER 3.@ @@@#           IF J-OPT NOT LN
)@@G@@= 0   @ @@@#               GO TO BA-500.  @@@@@#@#@@@#       BA-200.    LO

)@@G@@           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@A@@@#           ADD 1 TO ERROR-COUNT.    LQ
)@@G@@@@@@@#@#@@@#       BA-500.    @B@@@#           MOVE DRD-F-CYCLE TO FILE-LR
)@@G@@CYCLE.@A@@@#           MOVE SPACES TO PDUMP.    @D@@@#           STRING LS
)@@G@@'MFDFIL('         DELIMITED BY SIZE @E@@@#                  FILE-CYCLE  LT

)@@G@@       BA-900.    @G@@@#           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BA-000: INVALILY
)@@G@@D KEY' SEC-FILE-KEY     @^@@@#               F-STATUS.@A@@@#           ALZ

)@@G@@@ @@@#           IF REMOVABLE-DISK  @ @@@#               GO TO BD-100.  MR

)@@G@@EY.   @C@@@#           MOVE BACKUP-REEL-2 TO BACKUP-REEL-1. @B@@@#      RH
)@@G@@     PERFORM BH-200 THRU BH-500.    @B@@@#           MOVE TAPE-KEY TO WSRI
)@@G@@-DT2-KEY.   @F@@@#           ADD 1 TO TAPE-H-DOUBLE-COUNT NEW-DOUBLE-TAPRJ
)@@G@@E-COUNT     @ @@@#               TAPE-H-TOP-KEY.@D@@@#           MOVE TARK
)@@G@@PE-H-TOP-KEY TO WS-DT-KEY TAPE-KEY. @D@@@#           WRITE TAPE-RECORD FRL
)@@G@@ROM WS-DOUBLE-TAPE-REC  @B@@@#               INVALID KEY GO TO BH-920.  RM
)@@G@@@E@@@#*TEMP      EXHIBIT NAMED 'BH-000' TAPE-KEY TAPE-RECORD.     @^@@@#RN
)@@G@@           GO TO BH-999.@@@@@#@@@@@#@#@@@#       BH-200.    @@@@@#@ @@@#RO
)@@G@@      * SINGLE TAPE PROCESSING@@@@@#@D@@@#           IF BACKUP-REEL-1-1 RP
)@@G@@= 'SEC' OR 'REM' OR     @A@@@#              BACKUP-REEL-1  NUMERIC@ @@@#RQ
)@@G@@               GO TO BH-300   @#@@@#           ELSE   @ @@@#            RR

)@@G@@TO NEW-TAPE-FLAG. @C@@@#           MOVE BACKUP-REEL-1 TO TAPE-NAME.     RT
)@@G@@@ @@@#           READ SEC-TAPES     @A@@@#               KEY IS TAPE-NAMRU
)@@G@@E     @B@@@#               INVALID KEY GO TO BH-400.  @B@@@#           IRV
)@@G@@F TAPE-DT-FLAG NOT = SPACES   @G@@@#               EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERRORRW
)@@G@@* BH-500 FIRST FIND IS DOUBLE TAPE' @A@@@#                   TAPE-RECORDRX
)@@G@@.     @@@@@#@H@@@#      * DOUBLE TAPE RECORDS ARE PLACED IN SEC-TAPES AFRY
)@@G@@TER THE 2 SINGLE TAPE   @G@@@#      * RECORDS HAVE BEEN FOUND OR ENTEREDRZ

)@@G@@E RECORD FIRST    @@@@@#@B@@@#           IF JULIAN-CNT < TAPE-JULIAN    SB

)@@G@@   GO TO BH-999.  @^@@@#           GO TO BH-500.@@@@@#@#@@@#       BH-40SE
)@@G@@0.    @A@@@#           IF T-STATUS NOT = '23'   @ @@@#               GO SF
)@@G@@TO BH-905.  @@@@@#@E@@@#      * TAPE NAME NOT FOUND - MAKE A NEW ENTRY ISG
)@@G@@N SEC-TAPES @@@@@#@F@^@#           ADD 1 TO TAPE-H-TOP-KEY NEW-TAPE-FLAGSH
)@@G@@ NEW-TAPE-COUNT.  @F@@@^           ADD 1 TO TAPE-H-TOP-KEY NEW-TAPE-FLAGSI

)@@G@@0.    @@@@@#@F@@@#      * ZERO IN TAPE-PBDATE IS A FLAG FOR NEW ENTRIES SL
)@@G@@TO BR-200   @H@@@#      * THE NEW SETTINGS ARE ENTERED IN BR-250 AFTER LSM

)@@G@@@B@@@#           MOVE SPACES TO TAPE-DT-FLAG.   @C@@@#           IF NEW-SO
)@@G@@TAPE-FLAG = 0 AND T-OPT = 0   @F@A@#*TEMP          EXHIBIT NAMED 'BH-500SP

)@@G@@= 0   @G@@@#              EXHIBIT NAMED 'BH-500' NEW-TAPE-FLAG TAPE-KEY SU
)@@G@@TAPE-RECORD.@@@@@#@#@@@#       BH-600.    @^@@@#           GO TO BH-999.SV
)@@G@@@@@@@#@#@@@#       BH-905.    @D@@@#           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BHSW

)@@G@@@@@@@#@#@@@#       BH-920.    @G@@@#           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BHTC

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@@       IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.     @A@@@@       PROGRXV
)@@G@@AM-ID.  SECTAPECHECK.   @@@@@@@G@@@@      *    THIS PROGRAM CHECKS THE DXW
)@@G@@ATE OF USE OF THE SEC/REM SERIES OF @I@@@@      *    TAPES AS STORED IN XX
)@@G@@FILE SEC-TAPES.   EACH TAPE DATE IS COMPARED WITH     @H@@@@      *    TXY
)@@G@@HE DATE IT WAS LAST WRITTEN TO, AS TRAPPED FROM LOG-TAPE MESSAGES @I@@@@XZ
)@@G@@      *    BY THE TMS SYSTEM.   SEC-TAPES IS UPDATED BY 'SECUPDATE' BUT YA
)@@G@@IF TAPES    @H@@@@      *    ARE USED FOR OTHER PURPOSES (E.G. DIRECTORYYB
)@@G@@ SAVES, PACK UNLOADS,   @H@@@@      *    ROLOUTS) THE BACKUP DATA ON THEYC
)@@G@@ TAPE WILL NO LONGER BE ACCESSIBLE. @I@@@@      *    THE OUTPUT OF THIS YD

)@@G@@TION. @ @@@@      ************************@@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-000.    CB

)@@G@@       BD-100.    @C@@@@           READ TMS-PRINT  AT END GO TO BD-500. CH

)@@G@@= 'NUMBER'  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-150.  @@@@@@@D@@@@      * 'TAPCP

)@@G@@WORD1 = 'TAPE N'  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-100.  @C@@@@           RCR

)@@G@@@ @@@@               GO TO BD-310.  @@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-350.    @ @@@@DB

)@@G@@PE-DT-FLAG TO WS-DT-FLAG.     @ @@@@           MOVE 'X' TO WS-DT2.@C@@@@DE

)@@G@@ FA-200 THRU FA-299.    @A@R@NSH-IN      MOVE 'SHR' TO FILE-HOST. @B@R@NAY

)@@G@@LE SEC-FILES TABLE HAS BEEN ENTERED MAX. OR     @F@@@N      * MORE THAN BL

)@@G@@               MOVE '    (+1)' TO TEXTA   @#@@@G           ELSE   @B@@@GKS
)@@G@@               MOVE 'EXISTING' TO TEXTA.  @G@@@G           DISPLAY TEXTAKT
)@@G@@ ' CYCLE OF SEC-USERS INITIALISED' UPON PRINTER.@^@@@G           GO TO AKU
)@@G@@A-50. @@@@@G@#@@@G       AA-30.     @F@@@G           DISPLAY 'NO HEADER KV
)@@G@@RECORD IN SEC-USERS' UPON PRINTER.  @^@@@G           GO TO AA-50. @@@@@GKW
)@@G@@@#@@@G       AA-40.     @F@@@G           EXHIBIT NAMED 'AA-40  INVALID 'KX
)@@G@@ SEC-USERS-KEY U-STATUS.@^@@@G           GO TO AA-50. @#@@@G       AA-50KY
)@@G@@.     @^@@@G           IF T-OPT = 0 @ @@@G               GO TO AA-130.  KZ
)@@G@@@@@@@G@@@@@G@B@@@G      *    SEC-TAPES FILE INITIALISATION  @B@@@G      LA
)@@G@@*    *****************************  @@@@@G@^@@@G           IF X-OPT = 0 LB
)@@G@@@F@@@G               MOVE '@CAT,P SEC-TAPES(+1)/X/X. .' TO CSF-MESSAGE  LC
)@@G@@@D@@@G               CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MESSAGE@A@@@G      LD
)@@G@@         IF CSF-STATUS NOT = 0@B@@@G                   PERFORM AX-CSF-FALE
)@@G@@ILURE.@E@@@G           MOVE '@ASG,AIX SEC-TAPES/X/X. .' TO CSF-MESSAGE. LF
)@@G@@@D@@@G           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MESSAGE.   @A@@@G      LG
)@@G@@     IF CSF-STATUS NOT = 0    @B@@@G               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURLH
)@@G@@E.    @A@@@G           OPEN OUTPUT SEC-TAPES.   @@@@@G@^@@@G      *    HLI
)@@G@@EADER RECORD@@@@@G@D@@@G           MOVE LOW-VALUES TO TAPE-HEADER-RECORDLJ
)@@G@@.     @B@H@G           MOVE ' HEAD ' TO TAPE-HEADER.  @B@@@H           MLK
)@@G@@OVE ' HEAD ' TO TAPE-H-HEADER.@ @H@G           MOVE 0 TO TAPE-KEY @A@@@HLL
)@@G@@           MOVE 0 TO TAPE-H-KEY     @D@@@G           WRITE TAPE-RECORD FLM
)@@G@@ROM TAPE-HEADER-RECORD  @B@@@G               INVALID KEY GO TO AA-129.  LN
)@@G@@@D@@@I*          EXHIBIT NAMED 'WROTE' TAPE-RECORD TAPE-KEY.@ @@@G      LO
)@@G@@     CLOSE SEC-TAPES.   @^@@@G           IF X-OPT = 0 @B@@@G            LP
)@@G@@   MOVE '    (+1)' TO TEXTA   @#@@@G           ELSE   @B@@@G            LQ
)@@G@@   MOVE 'EXISTING' TO TEXTA.  @G@@@G           DISPLAY TEXTA ' CYCLE OF LR
)@@G@@SEC-TAPES INITIALISED' UPON PRINTER.@^@@@K           GO TO AA-130.@@@@@KLS
)@@G@@@#@@@K       AA-129.    @E@@@K           EXHIBIT NAMED 'INVALID KEY' T-SLT
)@@G@@TATUS TAPE-NAME.  @@@@@K@A@J@I*          OPEN INPUT SEC-TAPES.    @ @J@ILU
)@@G@@*          MOVE 0 TO TAPE-KEY.@B@J@I*          READ SEC-TAPES INVALID KELV
)@@G@@Y     @D@J@I*              EXHIBIT NAMED TAPE-KEY GO TO AA-129.   @D@J@ILW
)@@G@@*          EXHIBIT NAMED 'VALID' TAPE-KEY TAPE-RECORD.@^@J@G           GLX
)@@G@@O TO AA-130.@@@J@G@#@J@G       AA-129.    @E@J@G           EXHIBIT NAMEDLY
)@@G@@ 'INVALID KEY' T-STATUS TAPE-NAME.  @#@@@G       AA-130.    @ @J@I*     LZ
)@@G@@     CLOSE SEC-TAPES.   @^@@@G           IF F-OPT = 0 @ @@@G            MA
)@@G@@   GO TO AA-300.  @]@@@G      /     @A@@@G      *    SEC-FILES INITIALISMB
)@@G@@ATION @A@@@G      *    ************************ @@@@@G@^@@@G           IMC
)@@G@@F X-OPT = 0 @G@@@G              MOVE '@CAT,P SEC-FILES(+1)/X/X.,F///5000MD
)@@G@@ .' TO CSF-MESSAGE@D@@@G              CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MEME
)@@G@@SSAGE @A@@@G              IF CSF-STATUS NOT = 0 @B@@@G                  MF
)@@G@@PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE. @E@@@G           MOVE '@ASG,AIX SEC-FILES/X/X. .MG
)@@G@@' TO CSF-MESSAGE. @D@@@G           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MESSAMH
)@@G@@GE.   @A@@@G           IF CSF-STATUS NOT = 0    @B@@@G               PERMI
)@@G@@FORM AX-CSF-FAILURE.    @A@@@G           MOVE SPACES TO FILE-HOST.@ @@@GMJ
)@@G@@           IF M-OPT NOT = 0   @ @@@G               GO TO AA-150.  @A@@@GMK
)@@G@@           OPEN OUTPUT SEC-FILES.   @C@@@G           MOVE 0 TO HEADER-UPML
)@@G@@DATE-ERROR-FLAG   @B@@@G                     HEADER-TOTAL-FILES   @C@@@GMM
)@@G@@                     HEADER-DELETED-RECORDS.    @B@@@G           MOVE '@MN
)@@G@@@HEAD' TO HEADER-KEY.   @E@@@G**         EXHIBIT NAMED HEADER-OCCURS SECMO
)@@G@@-FILE-HEADER.     @D@@@G           WRITE SEC-FILE-REC FROM SEC-FILE-HEADMP
)@@G@@ER    @B@@@G               INVALID KEY GO TO AA-200.  @^@@@G           GMQ
)@@G@@O TO AA-190.@@@@@G@#@@@G       AA-150.    @@@@@G@B@@@G      * RESTRUCTURMR
)@@G@@E THE HEADER RECORD     @@@@@G@ @@@G           OPEN I-O SEC-FILES.@B@@@GMS
)@@G@@           MOVE '@@HEAD' TO SEC-FILE-KEY. @D@@@G           READ SEC-FILEMT
)@@G@@S INTO SEC-FILE-OLD-HEADER    @A@@@G               KEY IS SEC-FILE-KEY  MU
)@@G@@@B@@@G               INVALID KEY GO TO AA-200.  @E@@@G           MOVE OHMV
)@@G@@EADER-KEY               TO HEADER-KEY.    @F@@@G           MOVE OHEADER-MW
)@@G@@TOTAL-FILES       TO HEADER-TOTAL-FILES.  @G@@@G           MOVE OHEADER-MX
)@@G@@DELETED-RECORDS   TO HEADER-DELETED-RECORDS.    @F@@@G           MOVE ZEMY
)@@G@@RO                      TO HEADER-DELETED-ITEMS @G@@@G                  MZ
)@@G@@                           HEADER-UPDATE-ERROR-FLAG.  @C@@@G           ENA
)@@G@@XHIBIT NAMED SEC-FILE-OLD-HEADER.   @E@@@G           DELETE SEC-FILES RENB
)@@G@@CORD INVALID KEY GO TO AA-200.@C@@@G           EXHIBIT NAMED 'OLD HEADERNC
)@@G@@ DELETED'.  @D@@@G           WRITE SEC-FILE-REC FROM SEC-FILE-HEADER    ND
)@@G@@@B@@@G               INVALID KEY GO TO AA-200.  @B@@@G           EXHIBITNE
)@@G@@ NAMED SEC-FILE-HEADER. @@@@@G@B@@@G           MOVE '@@HEAD' TO SEC-FILENF
)@@G@@-KEY. @C@@@G           EXHIBIT NAMED 'REREADNEW HEADER'.    @C@@@G      NG
)@@G@@     READ SEC-FILES KEY IS SEC-FILE-KEY   @B@@@G               INVALID KNH
)@@G@@EY GO TO AA-200.  @C@@@G           MOVE SEC-FILE-REC TO SEC-FILE-HEADER.NI
)@@G@@@C@@@G           EXHIBIT NAMED HEADER-DELETED-ITEMS.  @#@@@G       AA-19NJ
)@@G@@0.    @ @@@G           CLOSE SEC-FILES.   @^@@@G           IF X-OPT = 0 NK
)@@G@@@B@@@G               MOVE '    (+1)' TO TEXTA   @#@@@G           ELSE   NL
)@@G@@@B@@@G               MOVE 'EXISTING' TO TEXTA.  @G@@@G           DISPLAYNM
)@@G@@ TEXTA ' CYCLE OF SEC-FILES INITIALISED' UPON PRINTER.@^@@@G           GNN
)@@G@@O TO AA-300.@@@@@G@#@@@G       AA-200.    @F@@@G           EXHIBIT NAMEDNO
)@@G@@ 'INVALID KEY ON SEC-FILES' SEC-FILE-KEY. @#@@@G       AA-300.    @^@@@GNP
)@@G@@           IF H-OPT = 0 @ @@@G               GO TO AA-999.  @]@@@G      NQ
)@@G@@/     @A@@@G      *    SEC-HIST INITIALISATION  @A@@@G      *    *******NR
)@@G@@***************** @@@@@G@^@@@G           IF X-OPT = 0 @F@@@G            NS
)@@G@@   MOVE '@CAT,P SEC-HIST(+1)/X/X. .' TO CSF-MESSAGE   @D@@@G            NT
)@@G@@   CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MESSAGE@A@@@G               IF CSF-STNU
)@@G@@ATUS NOT = 0@B@@@G                   PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE.@E@@@G      NV
)@@G@@     MOVE '@ASG,AIX SEC-HIST/X/X. .' TO CSF-MESSAGE.  @D@@@G           CNW
)@@G@@ALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSF-MESSAGE.   @A@@@G           IF CSF-STATUSNX
)@@G@@ NOT = 0    @B@@@G               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE.    @A@@@G      NY
)@@G@@     OPEN OUTPUT SEC-HIST.    @ @@@G           CLOSE SEC-HIST.    @E@@@GNZ
)@@G@@           CALL 'RPCIOSHDR' USING 'SEC-HIST' PCIOS-HDR.     @C@@@G**    OA
)@@G@@     EXHIBIT NAMED LARGEST-KEY-ALLOWED.   @C@@@G**         EXHIBIT NAMEDOB
)@@G@@ LARGEST-KEY-WRITTEN.   @ @@@G           OPEN I-O SEC-HIST. @E@@@G      OC
)@@G@@     MOVE LARGEST-KEY-ALLOWED TO WS-HIST-LAST-KEY.    @D@@@G           MOD
)@@G@@OVE 1 TO SEC-HIST-KEY WS-HIST-CURR-KEY.   @E@@@G           WRITE SEC-HISOE
)@@G@@T-RECORD FROM WS-HISTORY-HEADER     @G@@@G               INVALID KEY DISOF
)@@G@@PLAY 'AA-300 WRITE ERROR' UPON PRINTER.   @ @@@G           CLOSE SEC-HISOG
)@@G@@T.    @^@@@G           IF X-OPT = 0 @B@@@G               MOVE '    (+1)'OH
)@@G@@ TO TEXTA   @#@@@G           ELSE   @B@@@G               MOVE 'EXISTING'OI
)@@G@@ TO TEXTA.  @G@@@G           DISPLAY TEXTA ' CYCLE OF SEC-HIST INITIALISOJ
)@@G@@ED' UPON PRINTER. @@@@@G@#@@@G       AA-999.    @^@@@G           STOP RUOK
)@@G@@N.    @]@@@G      /     @ @@@G       AX-CSF-FAILURE SECTION.@A@@@G      OL
)@@G@@*************************     @@@@@G@^@@@G           COPY CSF-PD. _@@@@@OM
)@@G@@ IS NOT INITIALISED, SO WE HAVE TO DELETE ALL RECORDS.@@@@@G@ @@@G      ON
)@@G@@     IF G-OPT NOT = 0   *[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@        IDENTIFICATION DIVISIONOO
)@@G@@.     @ @@@        PROGRAM-ID. SECLOADMSG.@@@@@ @F@@@       *    WRITTENOP
)@@G@@ BY RICHARD STRANGE - SDC/ISI RTP FEBRUARY 1981 @@@@@ @H@@@       *    TOQ
)@@G@@HIS PROGRAM READS THE PRINT-FILE PRODUCED BY SECRUN.  IT PICKS    @G@@@ OR
)@@G@@      *    UP THE LOAD/ERROR MESSAGES PUT OUT BY SECURE AND READER AND  OS
)@@G@@@D@@@       *    INSERTS THESE MESSAGES IN THE HISTORY FILE.@@@@@ @G@@@ OT
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 3.0 - READS KEY SECTION AFTER @PRT,F - FROM SECRUN 3.2    OU
)@@G@@@E@@@       * LEVEL 3.1 - PRINTS SUMMARY OF PHASE 2 PRINT-FILE    @C@@@ OV
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 4.0 - COMPATIBLE WITH SECRUN 4.0  @F@@@       * LEVEL 4.1 OW
)@@G@@- SAVES SECRUNPR/STARTFILE CYCLES IN SEC-HIST   @F@@@       *           OX
)@@G@@  TABLE-F-DATA OCCURS 100 (WAS 25 CAUSING IGDM) @C@@@       * LEVEL 4.2 OY
)@@G@@- INSTALLATION-PROCS USED     @@@@@ @ @@@        ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.  OZ
)@@G@@@ @@@        CONFIGURATION SECTION. @A@@@        SOURCE-COMPUTER. UNIVACPA
)@@G@@-1110.@A@@@        OBJECT-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@ @@@        INPUT-OUTPUPB
)@@G@@T SECTION.  @^@@@        FILE-CONTROL.    @C@@@            SELECT PFILE PC
)@@G@@    ASSIGN TO PRINTER.  @D@@@            SELECT BRKPRT    ASSIGN TO DISCPD
)@@G@@ BRKFILE.   @D@@@            SELECT SEC-HIST  ASSIGN TO DISC SEC-HIST   PE
)@@G@@@B@@@                ORGANIZATION IS RELATIVE   @B@@@                ACCPF
)@@G@@ESS MODE IS DYNAMIC     @C@@@                RELATIVE KEY IS SEC-HIST-KEPG
)@@G@@Y     @B@@@                FILE STATUS IS H-STATUS.   @^@@@        DATA PH

)@@G@@**    @@@@@ @^@@@        FD  SEC-HIST     @B@@@            LABEL RECORDSPJ
)@@G@@ ARE OMITTED.     @C@@@        01  SEC-HIST-RECORD        PIC X(108).   PK
)@@G@@@@@@@ @#@@@        FD  PFILE  @A@@@            LABEL RECORDS OMITTED.   PL
)@@G@@@ @@@        01  PREC USAGE DISP-1. @^@@@            03  PRECA.   @C@@@ PM

)@@G@@NE1.  @C@@@                05  BRK-WORD-1     PIC X(6).     @C@@@       QD
)@@G@@         05  BRK-WORD-2     PIC X(6).     @C@@@                05  BRK-WQE
)@@G@@ORD-3     PIC X(6).     @C@@@                05  FILLER         PIC X(13QF

)@@G@@PRT-KEY-FLAG REDEFINES BRKPRT-LINE1.@C@@@                05  FILLER     QI

)@@G@@   05  BRKPRT-LOADER  PIC X(6).     @C@@@                05  FILLER     QR

)@@G@@BRKPRT-LINE1.     @C@@@                05  BRK-CAT-FILE   PIC X(36).    QT

)@@G@@D   PIC X(30).    @C@@@                05  BRK-WORD-5     PIC X(6).     RD
)@@G@@@C@@@                05  FILLER         PIC X(84).    @@@@@ @D@@@       RE

)@@G@@C X(12).    @C@@@                05  FILLER         PIC X(90).    @]@@@ RH
)@@G@@      /     @A@@@        WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.     @B@@@       ******RI
)@@G@@*************************     @@@@@ @C@@@        01  ABS-DATE           RJ
)@@G@@    PIC X(42).    @@@@@ @^@@@        01  COND-WORD.   @C@@@            0RK
)@@G@@3  FILLER             PIC 1(30).    @C@@@            03  COND-S6        RL
)@@G@@    PIC 1(6).     @@@@@ @^@@@        01  CSF-MESSAGE. @A@@@            CRM
)@@G@@OPY SECLOADMSG-SYM.     @C@@@        01  CSF-STATUS             PIC X(6)RN
)@@G@@.     @@@@@ @^@@@        01  SWITCHES.    @D@@@            03  SECURE-CNRO
)@@G@@T         PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @D@@@            03  READER-CNT         PIRP

)@@G@@           03  KEYS-FOUND         PIC H9(10) VALUE 1. @D@@@            0RS
)@@G@@3 PRINT-FOUND         PIC H9(10) VALUE 1. @@@@@ @C@@@        01  END-SWIRT
)@@G@@TCH             PIC H9(10).   @B@@@        01  F-CYCLE                PIRU
)@@G@@C XXX.@C@@@        01  USPNT                  PIC H9(10).   @D@@@       RV
)@@G@@ 01  TABLE-CNT              PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @D@@@        01  LINE-CNRW
)@@G@@T               PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @B@@@        01  SAVE-CNT           RX
)@@G@@    PIC 999.@C@@@        01  FILE-NAME              PIC X(30).    @C@@@ RY
)@@G@@       01  DUMP                   PIC X(30).    @C@@@        01  READER-RZ
)@@G@@RESULT          PIC X(6).     @@@@@ @F@@@        01  TITLE              SA
)@@G@@    PIC X(18) VALUE '     ERRORED'. @@@@@ @^@@@        01  TABLE-FILES. SB
)@@G@@@C@@@            03  TABLE-F-DATA       OCCURS 100    @E@@@             SC
)@@G@@                      INDEXED BY TABLE-INDEX.   @C@@@                05 SD
)@@G@@ TABLE-FNAME    PIC X(30).    @C@@@                05  TABLE-FILE-KEY PISE
)@@G@@C H9(10).   @C@@@                05  TABLE-LOAD-KEY PIC H9(10).   @B@@@ SF
)@@G@@               05  TABLE-LINE-NO  PIC ZZ9.@C@@@                05  TABLESG
)@@G@@-LOADER   PIC X(6).     @C@@@                05  TABLE-MSG      PIC X(72SH
)@@G@@).    @C@@@                05  TABLE-LFLAG    PIC H9(10).   @C@@@       SI
)@@G@@         05  TABLE-HFLAG    PIC H9(10).   @@@@@ @@@@@ @C@@@        01  DSJ
)@@G@@ATE-WORD              PIC X(12).    @C@@@        01  TIME-WORD          SK
)@@G@@    PIC X(12).    @@@@@ @C@@@        01  WS-HISTORY-RECORD.  COPY SEC-HWSL
)@@G@@S.    @]@@@       /     @ @@@        PROCEDURE DIVISION.    @ @@@       SM
)@@G@@*********************   @@@@@ @A@@@        AA-CONTROL-SECTION SECTION.  SN
)@@G@@@A@@@       ****************************  @@@@@ @#@@@        AA-000.    SO
)@@G@@@B@@@            CALL 'ABSDAT' USING ABS-DATE.  @D@@@            CALL 'DSP
)@@G@@ATE' USING DATE-WORD TIME-WORD.     @E@@@            DISPLAY 'SECLOADMSGSQ
)@@G@@ 4.2 ' ABS-DATE ': RUN AT '   @D@@@                TIME-WORD ' ' DATE-WOSR
)@@G@@RD UPON PRINTER.  @ @@@            MOVE 1 TO COND-S6. @B@@@            CSS
)@@G@@ALL 'SETC' USING COND-WORD.   @B@B@            CALL 'SETC' USING COND-WOST
)@@G@@RD.   @ @@@            OPEN INPUT BRKPRT  @ @@@                 OUTPUT PSU
)@@G@@FILE. @@@@@ @#@@@        AA-50.     @C@@@            READ BRKPRT  AT ENDSV
)@@G@@ GO TO AA-900.    @ @@@            ADD 1 TO LINE-CNT. @B@@@            ISW
)@@G@@F BRK-WORD-1 NOT = '@ .  S'   @ @@@                GO TO AA-50.   @B@@@ SX
)@@G@@           MOVE BRK-SECRUN-PRT TO CSF-SYM.@@@@@ @#@@@        AA-100.    SY
)@@G@@@@@@@ @C@@@       * FIND PRINT-FILE AND START-FILE DATA     @@@@@ @C@@@ SZ
)@@G@@           READ BRKPRT  AT END GO TO AA-900.    @ @@@            ADD 1 TTA
)@@G@@O LINE-CNT. @B@@@            IF BRK-WORD-1 NOT = '@PRT,F'   @ @@@       TB
)@@G@@         GO TO AA-100.  @B@@@            PERFORM BB-PRINT-FILE-DATA.    TC
)@@G@@@ @@@            IF END-SWITCH = 0  @A@@@                MOVE 0 TO PRINTTD
)@@G@@-FOUND@#@@@            ELSE   @ @@@                GO TO AA-900.  @@@@@ TE
)@@G@@@#@@@        AA-200.    @@@@@ @A@@@       * FIND HISTORY KEYS SECTION   TF
)@@G@@@@@@@ @C@@@            READ BRKPRT  AT END GO TO AA-900.    @ @@@       TG
)@@G@@     ADD 1 TO LINE-CNT. @B@@@            IF BRK-KEY-START NOT = '******'TH
)@@G@@@ @@@                GO TO AA-200.  @A@@@            PERFORM BA-FILE-KEYTI
)@@G@@S.    @@@@@ @#@@@        AA-300.    @ @@@            IF SECURE-CNT = 0  TJ
)@@G@@@ @@@                GO TO AA-400.  @A@@@            MOVE SPACES TO PRECTK
)@@G@@.     @E@@@            MOVE 'FILES LOADED BY ''SECURE''' TO PRECC1.     TL
)@@G@@@ @@@            WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@E@@@            MOVE '=============TM
)@@G@@==========='   TO PRECC1.     @^@@@            WRITE PREC.  @A@@@       TN
)@@G@@     MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @^@@@            WRITE PREC.  @@@@@ @E@@@ TO
)@@G@@           PERFORM BC-SECURE-DATA UNTIL END-SWITCH NOT = 0. @@@@@ @#@@@ TP
)@@G@@       AA-400.    @ @@@            IF READER-CNT = 0  @ @@@             TQ
)@@G@@   GO TO AA-800.  @@@@@ @A@@@            MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @E@@@ TR
)@@G@@           MOVE 'FILES LOADED BY ''READER''' TO PRECC1.     @ @@@       TS
)@@G@@     WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@E@@@            MOVE '========================'TT
)@@G@@   TO PRECC1.     @^@@@            WRITE PREC.  @A@@@            MOVE SPTU
)@@G@@ACES TO PREC.     @^@@@            WRITE PREC.  @@@@@ @A@@@            ITV
)@@G@@F END-SWITCH NOT = 0    @ @@@                CLOSE BRKPRT   @A@@@       TW
)@@G@@         OPEN INPUT BRKPRT.   @A@@@            MOVE 0 TO END-SWITCH.    TX
)@@G@@@E@@@            PERFORM BD-READER-DATA UNTIL END-SWITCH NOT = 0. @@@@@ TY
)@@G@@@#@@@        AA-800.    @A@@@            PERFORM BE-STORE-DATA.   @@@@@ TZ
)@@G@@@#@@@        AA-900.    @A@@@            IF SWITCHES = LOW-VALUES @A@@@ UA
)@@G@@               MOVE 0 TO COND-S6    @#@@@            ELSE   @B@@@       UB
)@@G@@         PERFORM BG-PRINT-ERRORS.   @@@@@ @#@@@        AA-999.    @B@@@ UC
)@@G@@           CALL 'SETC' USING COND-WORD.   @^@@@            STOP RUN.    UD
)@@G@@@]@@@       /     @ @@@        BA-FILE-KEYS SECTION.  @A@@@       ******UE
)@@G@@*********************   @@@@@ @#@@@        BA-000.    @A@@@            MUF
)@@G@@OVE 0 TO KEYS-FOUND.    @A@@@            SET TABLE-INDEX TO 1.    @@@@@ UG

)@@G@@KEY-START = '******'    @ @@@                GO TO BA-999.  @E@@@       UK
)@@G@@     MOVE BRK-KEY-FILE TO TABLE-FNAME(TABLE-INDEX).   @E@@@            MUL
)@@G@@OVE BRKPRT-KEY  TO TABLE-FILE-KEY(TABLE-INDEX). @E@@@            MOVE BRUM
)@@G@@KPRT-LOADER TO TABLE-LOADER(TABLE-INDEX). @C@@@            MOVE 1 TO TABUN

)@@G@@               BRKPRT-LOADER. @A@@@            MOVE 1 TO KEYS-FOUND.    UU
)@@G@@@^@@@            GO TO BA-999.@@@@@ @#@@@        BA-500.    @A@@@       UV

)@@G@@@ @@@                GO TO BA-100.  @E@@@            DISPLAY '*ERROR* BAUX

)@@G@@VE 1 TO END-SWITCH@ @@@                GO TO BB-999.  @ @@@            AVL

)@@G@@@#@@@B       BA-000.    @D@@@B           CALL 'DATE' USING DATE-WORD TIMGJ
