)@@G@@     COPY BB-TTBL-SETUP.@]@@@B      /     @B@@@B       BC-WRITE-NEW-SEC-GN
)@@G@@TAPES SECTION.    @B@@@B      ********************************    @@@@@BGO
)@@G@@@G@@@B      * WRITE OUT THE NEW HEADER, THEN EACH ENTRY OF THE MAIN TABLGP
)@@G@@E     @@@@@B@@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-100.    @A@@@B           OPEN OUTPUT SGQ
)@@G@@EC-NEWT.    @B@@@B           MOVE SPACES TO TAPE-DT-FLAG.   @ @@@B      GR
)@@G@@     MOVE 0 TO SUB.     @A@@@B           SET TTBL-INDEX TO 1.     @C@@@BGS
)@@G@@           PERFORM BC-200 TTBL-COUNT TIMES.     @^@@@B           GO TO BGT
)@@G@@C-500.@@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-200.    @D@@@B           IF TTBL-NAME2(TTBL-GU
)@@G@@INDEX) NOT = LOW-VALUES @ @@@B               PERFORM BC-800.@A@@@B      GV
)@@G@@     SET TTBL-INDEX UP BY 1.  @@@@@B@A@@@B      ************************GW
)@@G@@***   @@@@@B@D@@@B      * WRITE OUT THE DOUBLE-TAPE SECTION OF THE TABLEGX
)@@G@@@@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-500.    @A@@@B           IF DOUBLE-TAPE-COUNT = 0 GY
)@@G@@@ @@@B               GO TO BC-990.  @B@@@B           MOVE 'DT ' TO TAPE-GZ
)@@G@@DT-FLAG.    @C@@@B           SET TTBL-INDEX TO DOUBLE-TAPE-FIRST. @D@@@BHA
)@@G@@           PERFORM BC-600 DOUBLE-TAPE-COUNT TIMES.    @^@@@B           GHB
)@@G@@O TO BC-990.@@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-600.    @E@@@D           SET TTBL-INDEHC
)@@G@@X2 TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).     @G@@@D           MOVE TTBL-NEW-INDEXHD
)@@G@@(TTBL-INDEX2) TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).@E@@@D           SET TTBL-INDEHE
)@@G@@X2 TO TTBL-2-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).     @G@@@D           MOVE TTBL-NEW-INDEXHF
)@@G@@(TTBL-INDEX2) TO TTBL-2-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).@ @@@B           PERFORM BC-80HG
)@@G@@0.    @A@@@B           SET TTBL-INDEX UP BY 1.  @@@@@B@A@@@B      ******HH
)@@G@@*********************   @@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-800.    @D@@@B           MHI
)@@G@@OVE TTBL-NAME1(TTBL-INDEX) TO TAPE-NAME.  @D@@@B           MOVE TTBL-DATHJ
)@@G@@E(TTBL-INDEX) TO TAPE-DATE.   @E@@@B           MOVE TTBL-PBDATE(TTBL-INDHK
)@@G@@EX) TO TAPE-PBDATE.     @E@@@B           MOVE TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) TOHL
)@@G@@ TAPE-JULIAN.     @^@@@B           ADD 1 TO SUB.@E@@@B           MOVE SUHM
)@@G@@B TO TAPE-KEY TTBL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX). @E@@@B           WRITE TAPE-REHN
)@@G@@CORD  INVALID KEY GO TO BC-900.     @@@@@B@A@@@B      ******************HO
)@@G@@*********   @@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-900.    @D@@@B           EXHIBIT NAMEDHP
)@@G@@ '*ERROR* BC-900 INVALID KEY' @C@@@B               T-STATUS TAPE-KEY TAPHQ
)@@G@@E-RECORD.   @@@@@B@#@@@B       BC-990.    @B@@@B           MOVE ' HEAD 'HR
)@@G@@ TO TAPE-H-HEADER.@B@@@B           MOVE TTBL-H-DATE TO TAPE-H-DATE@E@@@BHS
)@@G@@           MOVE DOUBLE-TAPE-COUNT TO TAPE-H-DOUBLE-COUNT.   @B@@@B      HT
)@@G@@     MOVE SUB TO TAPE-H-TOP-KEY.    @C@@@C           SUBTRACT TAPE-H-DOUHU
)@@G@@BLE-COUNT FROM SUB@B@@@C               GIVING TAPE-H-SINGLE-COUNT.@A@@@BHV
)@@G@@           MOVE 0 TO TAPE-H-KEY.    @D@@@B           WRITE TAPE-RECORD FHW
)@@G@@ROM TAPE-HEADER-RECORD  @B@@@B               INVALID KEY PERFORM BC-900.HX
)@@G@@@ @@@B           CLOSE SEC-NEWT.    @D@@@B           EXHIBIT NAMED 'BC-9HY
)@@G@@90' TAPE-H-TOP-KEY.     @]@@@B      /     @B@@@B       BD-WRITE-NEW-SEC-HZ
)@@G@@FILES SECTION.    @B@@@B      *******************************     @@@@@BIA
)@@G@@@#@@@B       BD-000.    @A@@@B           OPEN  INPUT SEC-FILES    @A@@@BIB
)@@G@@                OUTPUT SEC-NEWF.    @D@@@B           READ SEC-FILES INTOIC
)@@G@@ OLD-SEC-FILE-HEADER    @A@@@B               AT END GO TO BD-950. @B@@@BID
)@@G@@           MOVE OLDHDR-KEY TO HEADER-KEY. @C@@@B           MOVE OLDHDR-OIE
)@@G@@CCURS TO HEADER-OCCURS. @G@@@B           MOVE OLDHDR-UPDATE-ERROR-FLAG TIF
)@@G@@O HEADER-UPDATE-ERROR-FLAG.   @E@@@B           MOVE OLDHDR-TOTAL-FILES TIG
)@@G@@O HEADER-TOTAL-FILES.   @F@@@B           MOVE OLDHDR-DELETED-RECORDS TO IH
)@@G@@HEADER-DELETED-RECORDS. @F@@@B           MOVE OLDHDR-DELETED-ITEMS TO HEII
)@@G@@ADER-DELETED-ITEMS.     @D@@@B           WRITE NEW-FILE-REC FROM SEC-FILIJ
)@@G@@E-HEADER    @B@@@B               INVALID KEY PERFORM BD-900.@@@@@B@#@@@BIK
)@@G@@       BD-100.    @C@@@B           READ SEC-FILES AT END GO TO BD-950.  IL
)@@G@@@C@@@B           MOVE SEC-FILE-KEY TO NEW-FILE-KEY.   @B@@@B           MIM
)@@G@@OVE LAST-INDEX TO NEW-L-INDEX.@C@@@B           MOVE NUM-OCCURS TO NEW-N-IN
)@@G@@OCCURS.     @B@@@B           SET OLD-INDEX NEW-INDEX TO 1.  @D@@@B      IO
)@@G@@     PERFORM BD-200-COPY-DATA NUM-OCCURS TIMES. @E@@@B           WRITE NIP
)@@G@@EW-FILE-REC  INVALID KEY PERFORM BD-900.  @^@@@B           GO TO BD-100.IQ
)@@G@@@@@@@B@^@@@B       BD-200-COPY-DATA.@D@@@B           SET TTBL-INDEX TO TIR
)@@G@@APE-INDEX(OLD-INDEX).   @G@@@B           MOVE TTBL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX)IS
)@@G@@ TO TAPE-INDEX(OLD-INDEX).    @E@@@B           MOVE F-DATA(OLD-INDEX) TOIT
)@@G@@ NEW-DATA(NEW-INDEX).   @C@@@B           SET OLD-INDEX NEW-INDEX UP BY 1IU
)@@G@@.     @@@@@B@#@@@B       BD-900.    @D@@@B           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERRIV
)@@G@@OR* BD-900: INVALID KEY'@A@@@B               N-STATUS NEW-Q-FNAME.@@@@@BIW
)@@G@@@#@@@B       BD-950.    @A@@@B           CLOSE SEC-FILES SEC-NEWF._@@@@@IX

)@@G@@TION. @ @@@1      *********************** @@@@@1@#@@@1       BC-000.    BO
)@@G@@@A@@@1           OPEN INPUT SEC-TAPES.    @B@@@1           MOVE 0 TO TAPBP
)@@G@@E-KEY NEW-KEY.    @D@@@1           READ SEC-TAPES INTO TAPE-HEADER-RECORBQ
)@@G@@D     @B@@@1               INVALID KEY GO TO BC-900.  @C@@@1           MBR
)@@G@@OVE TAPE-H-TOP-KEY TO TTBL-TOP-KEY. @C@@@1           MOVE TAPE-H-SINGLE-BS

)@@G@@' TO PTEXT. @^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @F@@@1           MOVE 0 TO TAPBW
)@@G@@E-H-SINGLE-COUNT TAPE-H-DOUBLE-COUNT.     @A@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEBX

)@@G@@S NEXT INTO TTBL-ITEM(TTBL-INDEX)   @A@@@1               AT END GO TO BCBZ
)@@G@@-999. @B@@@3           IF TAPE-KEY NOT = TTBL-INDEX   @ @@@3            CA
)@@G@@   GO TO BC-910.  @D@3@1*TEMP**    EXHIBIT NAMED 'BC-100' TAPE-KEY TTBL-CB
)@@G@@INDEX @ @3@1*TEMP**        TAPE-RECORD.   @C@@@1           MOVE 0 TO TTBCC
)@@G@@L-FCOUNT(TTBL-INDEX).   @@@@@1@F@@@1      * RECORDS TO BE DELETED HAVE TCD
)@@G@@APE-PBDATE SET TO ZERO BY THE @H@@@1      * PREVIOUS EXECUTION OF SECPACCE
)@@G@@K, OR AN EXECUTION OF SECUPDATE,SECTAPEMOD@H@@@1      * [NB.  IF YOU ADDCF
)@@G@@ CODE WHICH DOES A 'READ' USING THE HEADER-RECORD KEY @G@@@1      *     CG
)@@G@@  OF ' HEAD ' FOLLOWED BY 'READ NEXT' VERBS, THE RECORDS    @H@@@1      CH
)@@G@@*       WITH SPACES IN THE TAPE-NAME WILL NOT BE REACHED AS THEY ARE    CI
)@@G@@@D@@@1      *       BEFORE ' HEAD ' IN THE SORTING SEQUENCE]@@@@@1@ @@@1CJ
)@@G@@           IF TAPE-PBDATE = 0 @A@@@1               GO TO BC-300-DELETE. CK
)@@G@@@A@@@1           IF TAPE-DT-FLAG = SPACES @C@@@1               ADD 1 TO CL
)@@G@@TAPE-H-SINGLE-COUNT     @A@@@1               GO TO BC-200-KEEP.   @@@@@1CM
)@@G@@@H@@@1      * CHECK DOUBLE-TAPE ENTRIES: THE DATE OF USE MUST MATCH THE CN
)@@G@@DATE OF     @G@@@1      * USE FOR EACH TAPE OF THE PAIR.  IF IT DOES NOTCO
)@@G@@, THE DOUBLE TAPE @G@@@1      * COMBINATION IS NO LONGER VALID AS ONE ORCP
)@@G@@ BOTH OF THE TAPES HAS  @^@@@1      * BEEN RE-USED.   @G@@@1      * THISCQ
)@@G@@ SECTION SHOULD BE REDUNDANT AS SECUPDATE AND SECTAPEMOD    @G@@@1      CR
)@@G@@* BOTH DO CHECKS FOR DOUBLE-TAPE INVALIDATION - BUT LEAVE IT IN   @B@@@1CS
)@@G@@      * IN CASE, IT DOESN'T TAKE MUCH TIME@@@@@1@A@@@1           MOVE 0 CT
)@@G@@TO DELETE-FLAG.   @E@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEX2 TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-CU
)@@G@@INDEX).     @G@@@1           IF TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) NOT = TTBL-JULIACV
)@@G@@N(TTBL-INDEX2)    @A@@@1               MOVE 1 TO DELETE-FLAG@ @@@1      CW
)@@G@@         GO TO BC-120.  @E@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEX2 TO TTBL-2-INDEXCX
)@@G@@(TTBL-INDEX).     @G@@@1           IF TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) NOT = TTBLCY
)@@G@@-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX2)    @B@@@1               MOVE 1 TO DELETE-FLAG.     CZ
)@@G@@@@@@@1@#@@@1       BC-120.    @A@@@1           IF DELETE-FLAG NOT = 0   DA
)@@G@@@A@@@1               GO TO BC-300-DELETE  @#@@@1           ELSE   @C@@@1DB
)@@G@@               ADD 1 TO TAPE-H-DOUBLE-COUNT.    @@@@@1@^@@@1       BC-20DC
)@@G@@0-KEEP.     @ @@@1           ADD 1 TO NEW-KEY.  @D@@@1           MOVE NEDD
)@@G@@W-KEY TO TTBL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).@C@3@1*TEMP**    EXHIBIT NAMED 'BC-2DE
)@@G@@00-KEEP' NEW-KEY. @^@@@1           GO TO BC-400.@@@@@1@^@@@1       BC-30DF
)@@G@@0-DELETE.   @D@3@1*TEMP**    EXHIBIT NAMED 'BC-300-DELETE' TAPE-RECORD. DG
)@@G@@@G@@@1           MOVE 0 TO TTBL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX) TTBL-PBDATE(TTBL-IDH
)@@G@@NDEX).@@@@@1@#@@@1       BC-400.    @A@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEX UP BDI
)@@G@@Y 1.  @B@@@1           IF TTBL-INDEX > TAPE-H-TOP-KEY @ @@@1            DJ
)@@G@@   GO TO BC-999.  @A@@@1           IF TTBL-INDEX > TTBL-MAX @ @@@1      DK
)@@G@@         GO TO BC-930   @#@@@1           ELSE   @ @@@1               GO DL
)@@G@@TO BC-100.  @@@@@1@@@@@1@#@@@1       BC-900.    @D@@@1           EXHIBITDM
)@@G@@ NAMED '*ERROR* BC-900: INVALID KEY'@C@@@1               T-STATUS TAPE-KDN
)@@G@@EY TAPE-RECORD.   @A@@@1           ADD 1 TO ERROR-COUNT.    @^@@@1      DO
)@@G@@     GO TO BC-999.@@@@@1@#@@@3       BC-910.    @G@@@3           EXHIBITDP
)@@G@@ NAMED '*ERROR* BC-910: KEY AND CORE-INDEX MISMATCH'  @C@@@3            DQ
)@@G@@   TAPE-KEY TTBL-INDEX TAPE-RECORD. @A@@@3           ADD 1 TO ERROR-COUNDR
)@@G@@T.    @^@@@3           GO TO BC-999.@@@@@3@#@@@1       BC-930.    @E@4@1DS
)@@G@@           DISPLAY '*ERROR* BC-400: RECOMPILE WITH BIGGER ' @G@@@4      DT
)@@G@@     EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BC-400: RECOMPILE WITH BIGGER TABLE'  @B@4@1DU
)@@G@@               'TTBL-MAX' UPON PRINTER.   @B@5@4               TTBL-MAX DV

)@@G@@DUNDANT-REC-REMOVAL SECTION.  @B@@@1      ******************************DZ

)@@G@@ABLE PREC.  @ @@@1           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@D@2@1*SUPS      MOVE 'AEB
)@@G@@FTER FIRST TAPE PASS' TO SUP-TEXT.  @F@2@1*SUPS      CALL 'SUPDISPLAY' UEC
)@@G@@SING SUP-TABLE SUP-TYPE SUP-TEXT.   @A@@@1           OPEN OUTPUT SEC-NEWED
)@@G@@F     @A@@@1                 INPUT SEC-FILES.   @ @@@1           SET BF-EE
)@@G@@INDEX TO 1. @C@@@1           READ SEC-FILES INTO SEC-FILE-HEADER  @A@@@1EF
)@@G@@               AT END GO TO BD-950. @C@@@1           MOVE HEADER-DELETEDEG
)@@G@@-RECORDS TO PVAL. @E@@@1           MOVE 'DELETED RECORDS IN SEC-FILES' TEH
)@@G@@O PTEXT.    @ @@@1           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@C@@@1           MOVE HEEI
)@@G@@ADER-DELETED-ITEMS TO PVAL.   @F@@@1           MOVE 'DELETED RECORD ITEMEJ
)@@G@@S IN SEC-FILES' TO PTEXT.     @^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @F@@@1      EK
)@@G@@     MOVE 0 TO HEADER-DELETED-RECORDS HEADER-DELETED-ITEMS. @D@@@1      EL
)@@G@@     WRITE NEW-FILE-REC FROM SEC-FILE-HEADER    @B@@@1               INVEM
)@@G@@ALID KEY PERFORM BD-900.@@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-100.    @B@2@1*SUPS      CEN
)@@G@@ALL 'SUPS' USING SUP-TABLE.   @B@2@1*SUPS      DIVIDE SUPS(5) BY 60 GIVIEO
)@@G@@NG SUB@ @2@1*SUPS          REMAINDER REM. @^@2@1*SUPS      IF REM = 0   EP
)@@G@@@E@2@1*SUPS          EXHIBIT NAMED 'I/O MINS=' SUB NUM-RECORDS    @ @2@1EQ
)@@G@@*SUPS            QUAL-FNAME.  @C@@@1           READ SEC-FILES AT END GO ER
)@@G@@TO BD-950.  @A@@@1           ADD 1 TO NUM-RECORDS.    @F@@@1           MES
)@@G@@OVE 0 TO SUB LAST-JULIAN SORT-REQD DUPLICATES-FOUND.  @B@@@1           AET
)@@G@@DD NUM-OCCURS TO NUM-ITEMS.   @ @@@1           SET WS-INDEX TO 1. @@@@@1EU
)@@G@@@B@@@1      * START OF VALIDITY-TESTING LOOP    @@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-20EV
)@@G@@0.    @ @@@1           IF SUB = NUM-OCCURS@ @@@1               GO TO BD-EW
)@@G@@400.  @^@@@1           ADD 1 TO SUB.@C@@@1           IF NUM-OCCURS NOT =EX
)@@G@@ MAX-FILE-ITEM    @A@@@1               SET OLD-INDEX TO SUB @ @@@1      EY
)@@G@@         GO TO BD-300.  @@@@@1@F@@@1      * THE VARIABLE SEC-FILES TABLEEZ
)@@G@@ HAS BEEN ENTERED MAX. OR     @F@@@1      * MORE THAN MAX. TIMES, I.E. IFA
)@@G@@T IS RE-USING OLD SPACE, SO   @F@@@1      * THE EARLIEST ENTRY IS THE INFB
)@@G@@DEX 1 HIGHER THAN THE LATEST  @#@@@1      * ENTRY.    @@@@@1@C@@@1      FC
)@@G@@     ADD LAST-INDEX SUB GIVING NEXT-INDEX.@B@@@1           IF NEXT-INDEXFD
)@@G@@ > MAX-FILE-ITEM  @D@@@1               SUBTRACT MAX-FILE-ITEM FROM NEXT-FE
)@@G@@INDEX.@B@@@1           SET OLD-INDEX TO NEXT-INDEX.   @@@@@1@#@@@1      FF
)@@G@@ BD-300.    @D@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEX TO TAPE-INDEX(OLD-INDEX).   FG
)@@G@@@@@@@1@A@@@1      * TEST FOR VALIDITY OF TAPES  @@@@@1@F@@@1           IFH
)@@G@@F TTBL-PBDATE(TTBL-INDEX) NOT = FILE-PBDATE(OLD-INDEX)@B@@@1            FI
)@@G@@   ADD 1 TO NUM-INVALID-ITEMS @ @@@1               GO TO BD-200.  @@@@@1FJ
)@@G@@@C@@@1      * SAVE VALID FILE-ENTRY DATA IN WORK-SPACE@@@@@1@G@@@1      FK
)@@G@@     MOVE TTBL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX) TO TAPE-INDEX(OLD-INDEX).    @E@@@1FL
)@@G@@           ADD 1 TO NUM-VALID-ITEMS TTBL-FCOUNT(TTBL-INDEX).@E@@@1      FM
)@@G@@     MOVE F-DATA(OLD-INDEX) TO WS-F-DATA(WS-INDEX).   @F@@@1           MFN
)@@G@@OVE TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) TO WS-JULIAN(WS-INDEX).   @@@@@1@G@@@1      FO
)@@G@@* IF DATES ARE NOT IS ASCENDING NUMERIC ORDER, THE ENTRIES ARE    @G@@@1FP
)@@G@@      * DUPLICATED AND/OR REQUIRE SORTING: SET SWITCH FOR SORT BELOW    FQ
)@@G@@@@@@@1@D@@@1           IF TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) > LAST-JULIAN   @E@@@1FR
)@@G@@               MOVE TTBL-JULIAN(TTBL-INDEX) TO LAST-JULIAN  @#@@@1      FS
)@@G@@     ELSE   @A@@@1               MOVE 1 TO SORT-REQD. @@@@@1@G@@@1      FT
)@@G@@* IF THIS IS A DOUBLE-TAPE, BUMP UP THE FCOUNT FOR EACH OF THE    @^@@@1FU
)@@G@@      * INDIVIDUAL TAPES@@@@@1@C@@@1           IF TTBL-DT-FLAG(TTBL-INDEFV
)@@G@@X) = SPACES @ @@@1               GO TO BD-350.  @E@@@1           SET TTBFW
)@@G@@L-INDEX2 TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).     @C@@@1           ADD 1 TO TTBLFX
)@@G@@-FCOUNT(TTBL-INDEX2).   @E@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEX2 TO TTBL-2-INDEXFY
)@@G@@(TTBL-INDEX).     @C@@@1           ADD 1 TO TTBL-FCOUNT(TTBL-INDEX2).   FZ
)@@G@@@@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-350.    @A@@@1           SET WS-INDEX UP BY 1.    GA
)@@G@@@^@@@1           GO TO BD-200.@@@@@1@A@@@1      * END OF VALIDITY-TESTINGB
)@@G@@G LOOP@@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-400.    @A@@@1           SET WS-INDEX DOWN BGC
)@@G@@Y 1.  @ @@@1           IF WS-INDEX = 0    @C@@@1               ADD 1 TO GD
)@@G@@NUM-INVALID-RECORDS     @F@3@1*TEMP**        EXHIBIT NAMED 'BD-400 INVALGE
)@@G@@ID RECORD' QUAL-FNAME   @ @@@1               GO TO BD-100.  @B@@@1      GF
)@@G@@     ADD 1 TO NUM-VALID-RECORDS.    @D@@@1           SET NEW-N-OCCURS NEGG
)@@G@@W-L-INDEX TO WS-INDEX.  @@@@@1@ @@@1           IF SORT-REQD = 0   @ @@@1GH
)@@G@@               GO TO BD-800.  @@@@@1@E@@@1      * SORT WORK-SPACE TABLE GI
)@@G@@INTO ASCENDING DATE ORDER     @@@@@1@ @@@1           MOVE 2 TO SUB.     GJ
)@@G@@@A@@@1           SET WS-CURRENT TO 1.     @#@@@1       BD-450.    @B@@@1GK
)@@G@@           IF WS-CURRENT = NEW-N-OCCURS   @ @@@1               GO TO BD-GL
)@@G@@700.  @B@@@1           MOVE 99999 TO SMALLEST-VALUE.  @C@@@1           PGM
)@@G@@ERFORM BD-500-GET-SMALLEST-LEFT     @C@@@1               VARYING WS-INDEGN
)@@G@@X FROM SUB BY 1   @C@@@1               UNTIL   WS-INDEX > NEW-N-OCCURS. GO
)@@G@@@D@@@1           IF WS-JULIAN(WS-CURRENT) > SMALLEST-VALUE  @E@@@1      GP
)@@G@@         MOVE WS-ITEM(WS-CURRENT)  TO WS-SAVE-ITEM    @F@@@1            GQ
)@@G@@   MOVE WS-ITEM(WS-SMALLEST) TO WS-ITEM(WS-CURRENT)   @F@@@1            GR
)@@G@@   MOVE WS-SAVE-ITEM         TO WS-ITEM(WS-SMALLEST). @^@@@1           AGS
)@@G@@DD 1 TO SUB.@A@@@1           SET WS-CURRENT UP BY 1.  @^@@@1           GGT
)@@G@@O TO BD-450.@@@@@1@A@@@1       BD-500-GET-SMALLEST-LEFT.    @D@@@1      GU
)@@G@@     IF WS-JULIAN(WS-INDEX) < SMALLEST-VALUE    @E@@@1               MOVGV
)@@G@@E WS-JULIAN(WS-INDEX) TO SMALLEST-VALUE   @C@@@1               SET WS-SMGW
)@@G@@ALLEST TO WS-INDEX.     @@@@@1@A@@@1      * NOW CHECK FOR DUPLICATES    GX
)@@G@@@@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-700.    @C@@@1           MOVE WS-F-DATA(1) TO NEW-GY
)@@G@@DATA(1).    @B@@@1           SET WS-INDEX NEW-INDEX TO 1.   @#@@@1      GZ
)@@G@@ BD-710.    @A@@@1           SET WS-INDEX UP BY 1.    @B@@@1           IHA
)@@G@@F WS-INDEX > NEW-N-OCCURS     @ @@@1               GO TO BD-790.  @E@@@1HB
)@@G@@           IF WS-F-DATA(WS-INDEX) NOT = NEW-DATA(NEW-INDEX) @A@@@1      HC
)@@G@@         SET NEW-INDEX UP BY 1@F@@@1               MOVE WS-F-DATA(WS-INDHD
)@@G@@EX) TO NEW-DATA(NEW-INDEX)    @#@@@1           ELSE   @B@@@1            HE
)@@G@@   MOVE 1 TO DUPLICATES-FOUND.@^@@@1           GO TO BD-710.@@@@@1@#@@@1HF
)@@G@@       BD-790.    @D@@@1           SET NEW-N-OCCURS NEW-L-INDEX TO NEW-IHG
)@@G@@NDEX. @@@@@1@ @@@1      * WRITE OUT NEW RECORD  @@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-80HH
)@@G@@0.    @C@@@1           MOVE SEC-FILE-KEY TO NEW-FILE-KEY.   @ @@@1      HI
)@@G@@     IF SORT-REQD = 0   @B@@@1               SET WS-INDEX NEW-INDEX TO 1HJ
)@@G@@@D@@@1               PERFORM BD-850-COPY NEW-N-OCCURS TIMES.@E@@@1      HK
)@@G@@     WRITE NEW-FILE-REC  INVALID KEY PERFORM BD-900.  @F@@@1           IHL
)@@G@@F TTBL-PBDATE(TTBL-INDEX) NOT = FILE-PBDATE(OLD-INDEX)@C@@@1            HM
)@@G@@   PERFORM BF-DISPLAY-INVALID-LASTS @D@@@1               ADD 1 TO NUM-VAHN
)@@G@@LID-NON-LAST-RECORDS.   @B@@@1           IF DUPLICATES-FOUND NOT = 0    HO
)@@G@@@B@@@1               ADD 1 TO NUM-DUPLICATES.   @A@@@1           IF SORTHP
)@@G@@-REQD NOT = 0     @A@@@1               ADD 1 TO NUM-SORTS.  @^@@@1      HQ
)@@G@@     GO TO BD-100.@@@@@1@^@@@1       BD-850-COPY.     @E@@@1           MHR
)@@G@@OVE WS-F-DATA(WS-INDEX) TO NEW-DATA(NEW-INDEX). @B@@@1           SET WS-HS
)@@G@@INDEX NEW-INDEX UP BY 1.@@@@@1@#@@@1       BD-900.    @D@@@1           EHT
)@@G@@XHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BD-900: INVALID KEY'@A@@@1               N-STATUS HU
)@@G@@NEW-Q-FNAME.@A@@@1           ADD 1 TO ERROR-COUNT.    @@@@@1@#@@@1      HV
)@@G@@ BD-950.    @ @@@1           IF BF-INDEX = 1    @ @@@1               GO HW
)@@G@@TO BD-999.  @#@@@1       BD-960.    @C@@@1           MOVE SPACES TO BF-IHX
)@@G@@TEM(BF-INDEX).    @ @@@1           IF BF-INDEX < 4    @A@@@1            HY
)@@G@@   SET BF-INDEX UP BY 1 @ @@@1               GO TO BD-960.  @B@@@1      HZ
)@@G@@     DISPLAY BF-TABLE UPON PRINTER. @^@@@1           GO TO BD-999.@@@@@1IA
)@@G@@@#@@@1       BD-999.    @A@@@1           CLOSE SEC-NEWF SEC-FILES.@]@@@1IB
)@@G@@      /     @B@@@1       BF-DISPLAY-INVALID-LASTS SECTION.  @B@@@1      IC
)@@G@@*********************************** @@@@@1@#@@@1       BF-000.    @C@@@1ID
)@@G@@           MOVE QUAL-FNAME TO BF-ITEM(BF-INDEX).@ @@@1           IF BF-IIE
)@@G@@NDEX < 4    @A@@@1               SET BF-INDEX UP BY 1 @ @@@1            IF
)@@G@@   GO TO BF-999.  @@@@@1@^@@@1           IF BF-HDG = 0@A@@@1            IG
)@@G@@   MOVE 1 TO BF-HDG     @G@@@1               MOVE 'LAST ITEM INVALID BUTIH
)@@G@@ OTHERS VALID FOR:' TO PLINE  @A@@@1               WRITE PREC AFTER 3   II
)@@G@@@A@@@1               MOVE SPACES TO PREC  @A@@@1               WRITE PREIJ
)@@G@@C BEFORE 2. @B@@@1           DISPLAY BF-TABLE UPON PRINTER. @ @@@1      IK
)@@G@@     SET BF-INDEX TO 1. @@@@@1@#@@@1       BF-999.    @#@@@1           EIL
)@@G@@XIT.  @]@@@1      /     @A@@@1       BK-PACK-STATISTICS SECTION.  @A@@@1IM
)@@G@@      ***************************** @@@@@1@#@@@1       BK-000.    @A@@@1IN
)@@G@@           MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @ @@@1           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.IO
)@@G@@@D@2@1*SUPS      MOVE 'AFTER SEC-FILES PACK' TO SUP-TEXT.   @F@2@1*SUPS IP
)@@G@@     CALL 'SUPDISPLAY' USING SUP-TABLE SUP-TYPE SUP-TEXT.   @ @@@1      IQ
)@@G@@     OPEN I-O SEC-NEWF. @C@@@1           READ SEC-NEWF INTO SEC-FILE-HEAIR
)@@G@@DER   @A@@@1               AT END GO TO BD-999. @E@@@1           MOVE NUIS
)@@G@@M-VALID-RECORDS TO HEADER-TOTAL-FILES.    @D@@@1           REWRITE NEW-FIT
)@@G@@ILE-REC FROM SEC-FILE-HEADER  @B@@@1               INVALID KEY PERFORM BIU
)@@G@@D-900.@ @@@1           CLOSE SEC-NEWF.    @@@@@1@D@@@1           ADD NUMIV
)@@G@@-INVALID-ITEMS HEADER-DELETED-ITEMS @C@@@1               GIVING SUM-INVAIW
)@@G@@LID-DELETED-ITEMS.@E@@@1           MOVE 'PACK STATISTICS FOR SEC-FILES' IX
)@@G@@TO PTEXT.   @ @@@1           WRITE PREC AFTER 3.@A@@@1           MOVE NUIY
)@@G@@M-RECORDS TO PVAL.@C@@@1           MOVE 'RECORDS IN THE FILE' TO PTEXT. IZ
)@@G@@@ @@@1           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@B@@@1           MOVE NUM-VALID-RECOJA
)@@G@@RDS TO PVAL.@B@@@1           MOVE 'VALID RECORDS' TO PTEXT. @^@@@1      JB
)@@G@@     WRITE PREC.  @C@@@1           MOVE NUM-INVALID-RECORDS TO PVAL.    JC
)@@G@@@C@@@1           MOVE 'INVALID RECORDS' TO PTEXT.     @^@@@1           WJD
)@@G@@RITE PREC.  @A@@@1           MOVE NUM-ITEMS TO PVAL.  @C@@@1           MJE
)@@G@@OVE 'ITEMS IN THE FILE' TO PTEXT.   @^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @B@@@1JF
)@@G@@           MOVE NUM-VALID-ITEMS TO PVAL.  @B@@@1           MOVE 'VALID IJG
)@@G@@TEMS' TO PTEXT.   @^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @B@@@1           MOVE NUJH
)@@G@@M-INVALID-ITEMS TO PVAL.@B@@@1           MOVE 'INVALID ITEMS' TO PTEXT. JI
)@@G@@@^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @A@@@1           MOVE NUM-SORTS TO PVAL.  JJ
)@@G@@@F@@@1           MOVE 'RECORDS NEEDED SORT INTO DATE-ORDER' TO PTEXT.   JK
)@@G@@@^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @B@@@1           MOVE NUM-DUPLICATES TO PVJL
)@@G@@AL.   @E@@@1           MOVE 'RECORDS HAD DUPLICATE ENTRIES' TO PTEXT.   JM
)@@G@@@^@@@1           WRITE PREC.  @D@@@1           MOVE NUM-VALID-NON-LAST-RJN
)@@G@@ECORDS TO PVAL.   @F@@@1           MOVE 'RECORDS HAD INVALID LAST+VALID JO
)@@G@@NON-LAST ENTRIES' @^@@@1               TO PTEXT.@^@@@1           WRITE PJP
)@@G@@REC.  @@@@@1@A@@@1           MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @E@@@1           MJQ
)@@G@@OVE 'PACK STATISTICS FOR SEC-TAPES' TO PTEXT.   @ @@@1           WRITE PJR
)@@G@@REC AFTER 3.@C@@@1           MOVE TAPE-H-SINGLE-COUNT TO PVAL.    @D@@@1JS
)@@G@@           MOVE 'SINGLE TAPES IN SEC-TAPES' TO PTEXT. @ @@@1           WJT

)@@G@@@D@@@1           MOVE 'DOUBLE TAPES IN SEC-TAPES' TO PTEXT. @^@@@1      JV
)@@G@@     WRITE PREC.  @]@@@1      /     @A@@@1       BT-WRITE-SEC-TAPES SECTJW
)@@G@@ION.  @A@@@1      ***************************** @@@@@1@#@@@1       BT-00JX
)@@G@@0.    @A@@@1           OPEN OUTPUT SEC-NEWT.    @B@@@1           MOVE 0 JY
)@@G@@TO NEWT-KEY BF-HDG.     @B@@@1           MOVE ' HEAD ' TO TAPE-H-HEADER.JZ
)@@G@@@ @@@1           MOVE DW-YY TO D-YY.@ @@@1           MOVE DW-MM TO D-MM.KA

)@@G@@   PERFORM BT-600 @ @@@1               GO TO BT-190.  @B@@@1           IKH

)@@G@@AG(TTBL-INDEX) = SPACES @ @@@1               PERFORM BT-500 @ @@@1      KM
)@@G@@         GO TO BT-190.  @@@@@1@H@@@1      * REPLACE OLD BY NEW INDICES FKN
)@@G@@OR THE INDIVIDUAL TAPES IN DOUBLE-TAPE    @E@@@1      * RECORDS (I.E. THKO
)@@G@@E POSITION IN THE PACKED DOWN FILE) @@@@@1@E@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEKP
)@@G@@X2 TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).     @G@@@1           MOVE TTBL-NEW-INDEXKQ
)@@G@@(TTBL-INDEX2) TO TTBL-1-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX).@E@@@1           SET TTBL-INDEKR

)@@G@@0.    @@@@@1@#@@@1       BT-190.    @B@@@1           IF TTBL-INDEX = TTBKU
)@@G@@L-TOP-KEY   @ @@@1               GO TO BT-999   @#@@@1           ELSE   KV
)@@G@@@B@@@1               SET TTBL-INDEX UP BY 1     @ @@@1               GO KW
)@@G@@TO BT-100.  @@@@@1@@@@@1@#@@@1       BT-500.    @E@@@1           MOVE TTKX
)@@G@@BL-NEW-INDEX(TTBL-INDEX) TO NEWT-KEY.     @D@@@1           WRITE NEWT-REKY

)@@G@@900.  @D@3@1*TEMP**    EXHIBIT NAMED 'BT-500' NEWT-KEY NEWT-REC.  @@@@@1LA

)@@G@@@F@@@@      *    WRITTEN BY RICHARD STRANGE - SDC/ISI RTP NOVEMBER 1980 LZ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@G@@@@      *    THIS PROGRAM READS THE FILE SEC-USERS CONTAINING MA
)@@G@@BACKED UP   @G@@@@      *    REQUESTS FROM THE USER COMMUNITY FOR FILE RMB
)@@G@@ECOVERY.  THE     @H@@@@      *    PROGRAM BUILDS AND @STARTS A SECURE RMC
)@@G@@UNSTREAM TO CARRY OUT THE     @G@@@@      *    RECOVERY.   IT ALSO LISTSMD
)@@G@@ DATA ABOUT THE USERS MAKING THE    @H@@@@      *    REQUESTS AND THE FIME
)@@G@@LES THEY REQUESTED.   FINALLY THE SEC-USERS     @A@@@@      *    FILE ISMF
)@@G@@ RE-INITIALIZED.  @@@@@@@A@@@@      * LEVEL 1.1: FIRST RELEASE    @G@@@@MG
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 1.2: JAN 30,1981 - HANDLES MORE THAN 50 (CURRENT MAX-FILESMH
)@@G@@@H@@@@      *            SETTING) FILES IN SEC-USERS BY STARTING ANOTHERMI
)@@G@@ SECRUN TO  @D@@@@      *            CARRY ON FROM FILE 51, AND SO ON.  MJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@      * LEVEL 1.3: FEB 6, 1981 - WRITE RECORDS TO SEC-HIST FILE   MK
)@@G@@@H@@@@      * LEVEL 2.0: MARCH 1981 - DOUBLE TAPES, RECOVERY OF PHASE 2 ML
)@@G@@(@ADD OF    @D@@@@      *            SECURE ECL) LOST IN MACHINE-CRASH  MM
)@@G@@@C@@@@      * LEVEL 3.0: MAY 1981 - MUFS COMPATIBLE   @C@@@@      * LEVEMN
)@@G@@L 2.1: REMOVES TEMP CODE LEFT IN 2.0@G@@@@      * LEVEL 2.2: MAKES FILE-MO
)@@G@@CYCLE ZZ9 (AS CYCLE 009=OCTAL=ILLEGAL)    @H@@@@      * LEVEL 3.0: GENERMP
)@@G@@ATES ECL COMPATIBLE WITH MUFS VERSIONS OF @SECURE     @H@@@@      * LEVEMQ
)@@G@@L 3.1: DOES @START FROM DATA-FILE 'USER*SECRUN' (RUNS WERE LOST   @I@@@@MR
)@@G@@      *            DUE TO @PACK OF PF USER*RUNSTREAM WHICH CONTAINED SECMS
)@@G@@RUN ELT)    @I@@@@      * LEVEL 3.2: NO START OF RECOVERY RUN (45FILZ) FMT
)@@G@@ROM CONTINUATION RUN (45FIL1) @I@@@@      *            HISTORY KEYS IN SMU
)@@G@@TART-FILE (FOR 45FILZ) INSTEAD OF PRINT-FILE    @H@@@@      * LEVEL 3.3:MV
)@@G@@ PHASE 2 ADD-FILE CYCLES KEPT IN HEADER-2: RECOVERY/REMOVAL @H@@@@      MW
)@@G@@             DONE BY CYCLE NUMBERS IN CASE MORE THAN ONE INCOMPLETE.    MX
)@@G@@@H@@@@                   LOAD LOCAL+SHARED FILES IN ONE SECURE XQT IF SAMY
)@@G@@ME TAPE     @H@@@@      * LEVEL 4.0: SORT SEC-USERS FIRST INTO TAPE-ORDEMZ
)@@G@@R.  ONE RUN GENERATED   @G@@@@      *            FOR EACH @SECURE/READERNA
)@@G@@ EXECUTION. @SECURE WITH UP TO@H@@@@      *            3 TAPES GIVEN TO NB
)@@G@@GET MULTI-ACTIVITY LOADING.  THESE MODS   @I@@@@      *            SHOULNC
)@@G@@D SPEED FILE LOADS, ESPECIALLY WHEN THERE ARE MANY FILES    @F@@@@      ND
)@@G@@*            STACKED UP IN SEC-USERS ON DIFFERENT TAPES.    @G@@@@      NE
)@@G@@* LEVEL 4.1: REWRITES SEC-HIST HEADER WHEN ZERO LOAD REQUESTS     @H@@@@NF
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 4.2: IGNORES TWO ADJACENT, IDENTICAL FILENAMES ON 'LOAD FING
)@@G@@LE..' @G@@@@      *            CARD (THE SECOND IS A 'FILE NOT FOUND' INNH
)@@G@@ SECURE 21) @D@@@@      * LEVEL 4.3: ADDED BC-456 LABEL FOR SPNT>77     NI
)@@G@@@D@@@@      *            SEPARATED FATAL+WARNING ERRORS     @@@@@@@ @@@@NJ
)@@G@@       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.  @ @@@@       CONFIGURATION SECTION. @A@@@@NK
)@@G@@       SOURCE-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@A@@@@       OBJECT-COMPUTER. UNIVACNL
)@@G@@-1110.@ @@@@       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.  @^@@@@       FILE-CONTROL.    NM
)@@G@@@E@@@@           SELECT START-FILE ASSIGN TO PRINTER START-FILE.  @C@@@@NN
)@@G@@           SELECT PRINT-FILE ASSIGN TO PRINTER. @D@@@@           SELECT NO
)@@G@@INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO CARD-READER.   @C@@@@           SELECT SORT-IN ASSINP
)@@G@@GN TO DISC XA.    @D@@@@           SELECT SEC-USERS  ASSIGN TO DISC SEC-NQ
)@@G@@USERS @B@@@@               ORGANIZATION IS RELATIVE   @B@@@@            NR
)@@G@@   ACCESS MODE IS DYNAMIC     @C@@@@               RELATIVE KEY IS SEC-UNS
)@@G@@SERS-KEY    @B@@@@               FILE STATUS IS U-STATUS.   @D@@@@      NT

)@@G@@ANIZATION IS RELATIVE   @B@@@@               ACCESS MODE IS DYNAMIC     NV
)@@G@@@C@@@@               RELATIVE KEY IS SEC-HIST-KEY     @B@@@@            NW
)@@G@@   FILE STATUS IS H-STATUS.   @D@@@@           SELECT WORK-FILE ASSIGN TNX
)@@G@@O DISC WORK-FILE  @B@@@@               ORGANIZATION IS RELATIVE   @B@@@@NY

)@@G@@KEY IS WORK-KEY   @B@@@@               FILE STATUS IS W-STATUS.   @^@@@@OA

)@@G@@@C@@@@       01  WS-LAST-FILE           PIC X(30).    @@@@@@@^@@@@      UG
)@@G@@ 01  WS-SREC.     @C@@@@           03  WS-SREC-COMMAND    PIC X(18).    UH

)@@G@@3  FILLER             PIC X(24) VALUE SPACES.   @@@@@@@D@@@@       01  WUJ
)@@G@@S-TAPES-THIS-RUN      PIC H9(10) VALUE 0. @C@@@@       01  WS-TYPE2-KEY UK
)@@G@@          PIC H9(10).   @]@@@@      /     @ @@@@       PROCEDURE DIVISIOUL
)@@G@@N.    @ @@@@      *********************   @@@@@@@A@@@@       AA-CONTROL-UM
)@@G@@SECTION SECTION.  @A@@@@      ****************************  @@@@@@@#@@@@UN
)@@G@@       AA-000.    @C@@@@           CALL 'ORIGIN' USING SUB HOST-ID.     UO
)@@G@@@@@@@@@G@@@@      * SET S6 OF CONDITION-WORD = ERROR-FLAG UNTIL CLEARED UP
)@@G@@IN AA-900   @@@@@@@ @@@@           MOVE 1 TO COND-S6. @B@@@@           CUQ
)@@G@@ALL 'SETC' USING COND-WORD.   @B@@@@           CALL 'ABSDAT' USING ABS-DUR
)@@G@@ATE.  @F@@@@           CALL 'DATE' USING DATE-WORD TIME-WORD DAY-OF-WEEKUS
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@           DISPLAY 'SECRUN 4.3 ' ABS-DATE ': RUN AT ' TIME-WUT
)@@G@@ORD   @E@@@@               ' ' DATE-WORD ' ON ' HOST-ID UPON PRINTER.   UU
)@@G@@@C@@@@           CALL 'OPTION' USING OPTION-WORD.     @C@@@@           MUV
)@@G@@OVE 'BRKFILE' TO FITEM-INT-FNAME.   @ @@@@           PERFORM AY-FITEM.  UW
)@@G@@@C@@@@           MOVE FITEM-STRING TO PRINT-FILENAME. @@@@@@@G@@@@      UX
)@@G@@* A-OPTION = SET SAVED @ADD-FILE NAME (IN HEADER RECORD 2) BACK TO@H@@@@UY
)@@G@@      *            SPACES, THEN STOP.   SEE BM-..SECTION FOR FULL EXPLANUZ
)@@G@@ATION @@@@@@@A@@@@           OPEN OUTPUT PRINT-FILE.  @ @@@@           IVA
)@@G@@F A-OPT NOT = 0   @C@@@@               PERFORM BN-REMOVE-ADD-RECOVER    VB
)@@G@@@ @@@@               GO TO AA-910.  @@@@@@@G@@@@      * T-OPTION = TESTIVC
)@@G@@NG, I.E. NO @ADD/@START OF GENERATED SECURE     @@@@@@@ @@@@           IVD
)@@G@@F T-OPT NOT = 0   @C@@@@               ACCEPT TIME-WORD FROM CARD-READERVE
)@@G@@@C@@@@               ACCEPT DATE-WORD FROM CARD-READER@D@@@@            VF
)@@G@@   ACCEPT DAY-OF-WEEK FROM CARD-READER    @F@@@@               EXHIBIT NVG
)@@G@@AMED 'T-OPT USING' TIME-WORD DATE-WORD    @A@@@@                   DAY-OVH
)@@G@@F-WEEK.     @@@@@@@C@@@@           PERFORM BA-PRINT-SEC-USERS-HEADERS.  VI
)@@G@@@B@@@@           IF SEC-USERS-NUM-FILES = 0     @ @@@@               GO VJ
)@@G@@TO AA-900.  @@@@@@@D@@@@           MOVE SEC-USERS-NUM-FILES TO SORTF-NUMVK
)@@G@@-RECS.@E@@@@           CALL 'SORTF' USING SORTF-NUM-RECS SORTF-SIZE     VL
)@@G@@@E@@@@                              SORTF-RETURN   SORTF-OPTION.  @@@@@@VM
)@@G@@@G@@@@      * SORT-ORDER EXPLANATION: (1) SORT-OFILE - TO SEPARATE SECURVN
)@@G@@E AND @G@@@@      * READER LOADS: IF OFILE NOT LOW-VALUES, READER WILL BVO
)@@G@@E USED TO   @C@@@@      * LOAD THE FILE INTO THE NAMED OUTPUT AREA@H@@@@VP
)@@G@@      * (2) TAPE1 - TO GET ALL FILES ON THE SAME TAPE TOGETHER SO WE GENVQ
)@@G@@ERATE @F@@@@      * ONE SECURE/READER EXECUTION ONLY (I.E. RUN) FOR EACHVR
)@@G@@ TAPE @I@@@@      * (3) TAPE2 - SO THAT DOUBLE TAPE LOADS COME AFTER ALLVS
)@@G@@ SINGLE TAPE ENTRIES    @H@@@@      * FOR A GIVEN TAPE1 (I.E. IF WE HAD VT
)@@G@@SEC123,SEC123+SEC124,SEC123 THIS    @H@@@@      * MUST BE SORTED TO SEC1VU
)@@G@@23,SEC123,SEC123+SEC124 SINCE THE DOUBLE TAPE   @I@@@@      * GETS ITS OVV
)@@G@@WN RUN AND WITHOUT THE SORT THERE WOULD BE 3 RUNS INSTEAD OF 2    @H@@@@VW
)@@G@@      * AFTER THE SORT - RUN1=THE 2 FILES ON SEC123 ALONE,RUN2=SEC123+SEVX
)@@G@@C124) @H@@@@      * (4) FILENAME - SO THAT IF A FILE IS ENTERED TWICE WIVY
)@@G@@TH THE SAME TAPE  @G@@@@      * THE DUPLICATION CAN BE ELIMINATED (IN BCVZ
)@@G@@-455) THUS AVOIDING     @G@@@@      * THE 'FILE NOT FOUND' ERROR WHEN 'SWA
)@@G@@ECURE' TRIES TO FIND THE FILE @A@@@@      * FURTHER DOWN THE SAME TAPE  WB
)@@G@@@@@@@@@B@@@@           SORT SORT-IN ASCENDING KEY     @F@@@@            WC
)@@G@@   SORT-OFILE SORT-TAPE1 SORT-TAPE2 SORT-FILENAME     @E@@@@            WD
)@@G@@   INPUT  PROCEDURE IS BB-PRINT-USER-REQUESTS   @D@@@@               OUTWE
)@@G@@PUT PROCEDURE IS BC-GENERATE-RUNS.  @@@@@@@C@@@@           IF ERRORS-FATWF
)@@G@@AL = 0 AND S-OPT = 0    @B@@@@               PERFORM BR-RESET-SEC-USERS.WG
)@@G@@@#@@@@       AA-900.    @B@@@@           PERFORM BS-START-NEXT-SECRUN.  WH
)@@G@@@@@@@@@#@@@@       AA-910.    @A@@@@           MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     WI
)@@G@@@ @@@@           WRITE PREC AFTER 3.@B@@@@           IF ERROR-COUNT = LOWJ
)@@G@@W-VALUES    @A@@@@               MOVE 0 TO COND-S6    @B@@@@            WK
)@@G@@   CALL 'SETC' USING COND-WORD@D@@@@               MOVE 'END SECRUN: 0 EWL
)@@G@@RRORS' TO PREC    @ @@@@               WRITE PREC     @ @@@@            WM
)@@G@@   GO TO AA-999.  @ @@@@           IF T-OPT NOT = 0   @ @@@@            WN
)@@G@@   GO TO AA-999.  @B@@@@           MOVE ERRORS-FATAL TO VAL1.     @B@@@@WO
)@@G@@           MOVE ERRORS-WARNING TO VAL2.   @A@@@@           MOVE SPACES TWP
)@@G@@O PDUMP.    @D@@@@           STRING 'END SECRUN:'     DELIMITED BY SIZE WQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@                  VAL1              DELIMITED BY SIZE @D@@@@      WR
)@@G@@            ' FATAL ERRORS'   DELIMITED BY SIZE @D@@@@                  WS
)@@G@@VAL2              DELIMITED BY SIZE @D@@@@                  ' WARNING ERWT
)@@G@@RORS' DELIMITED BY SIZE @ @@@@                  INTO PDUMP. @A@@@@      WU
)@@G@@     WRITE PREC FROM PDUMP.   @^@[@@           IF TW-HH > 16@D@@@[      WV
)@@G@@     IF TW-HH > 16  OR  DAY-OF-WEEK = 'SAT'     @ @@@@               GO WW

)@@G@@0-LOAD-CARD.@C@@@@           READ WORK-FILE INTO USER-FILE-RECORD @B@@@@GK

)@@G@@ENAME WS-LAST-FILE.     @B@]@@           IF USER-FILENAME = WS-LAST-FILEGW
)@@G@@@ @]@@               GO TO BC-459.  @C@]@@           MOVE USER-FILENAME GX
)@@G@@TO WS-LAST-FILE.  @#@@@@       BC-456.    @D@@@@           STRING USER-FGY
)@@G@@ILENAME DELIMITED BY SPACE    @A@@@@               ',' DELIMITED BY SIZEGZ
)@@G@@@^@@@@               INTO SREC@ @@@@               POINTER SPNT.  @^@@@@HA
)@@G@@           IF SPNT > 77 @B@@@@               MOVE SAVE-SPNT TO SPNT     HB

)@@G@@@A@@@@                   POINTER SPNT     @ @@@@               WRITE SREHE
)@@G@@C     @A@@@@               MOVE SPACES TO SREC  @ @@@@               MOVHF

)@@G@@8.    @B@@@@           MOVE WORK-TAPE TO IBACKUP-NO.  @#@@@@       BC-45HH

)@@G@@***************************************** @@@@@@@^@@@@       BC-460-LOADHJ
)@@G@@-FILE.@A@@@@           IF USER-FILE-HOST = 'SHR'@C@@@@               MOVHK

)@@G@@' TO WS-SREC-COMMAND.   @A@@@@           WRITE SREC FROM WS-SREC. @@@@@@IO

)@@G@@@A@@@@      ***************************** @@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-000.    LA
)@@G@@@C@@@@           MOVE SPACES          TO CSF-MESSAGE. @C@@@@           MLB
)@@G@@OVE '@ASG,UP'       TO CSF-COMMAND. @C@@@@           MOVE '(+1). ' TO STLC
)@@G@@ART-FILE-CYCLE.   @D@@@@           MOVE START-FILE-STRING TO CSF-STARTFILD

)@@G@@           IF REQUEST-ACCEPTED-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@@               PERFORM ALF

)@@G@@CEPTED-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@@               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE     @C@@@@LJ
)@@G@@               PERFORM AB-ERROR-TERMINATION.    @B@@@@           MOVE  'LK
)@@G@@.'  TO START-FILE-CYCLE.@C@@@@           MOVE 'START-FILE' TO FITEM-INT-LL
)@@G@@FNAME.@ @@@@           PERFORM AY-FITEM.  @A@@@@           OPEN OUTPUT SLM
)@@G@@TART-FILE.  @B@@@@           MOVE 1 TO START-FILE-OPEN.     @B@@@@      LN

)@@G@@CLE(SEC-USERS-ADD-INDEX) = SPACES   @A@@@@                   NEXT SENTENLR

)@@G@@ADD-INDEX). @^@@@@           GO TO BD-300.@#@@@@       BD-200.    @G@@@@LT

)@@G@@22095USER,USER/USERP,10,100'  @^@@@@               TO SREC. @^@@@@      LX

)@@G@@DD-RECOVER SECTION.     @B@@@@      ********************************    OC
)@@G@@@@@@@@@E@@@@      * THIS SECTION IS CALLED BY AN A-OPTION EXECUTION     OD
)@@G@@@G@@@@      * IT REMOVES AN @START-FILE CYCLE ONCE THE RUN HAS COMPLETEDOE
)@@G@@ ITS  @A@@@@      * SECURE/READER LOAD ECL.     @@@@@@@#@@@@       BN-00OF
)@@G@@0.    @ @@@@           OPEN I-O SEC-USERS.@A@@@@           MOVE 2 TO SECOG
)@@G@@-USERS-KEY. @C@@@@           READ SEC-USERS INTO SEC-USERS-FHEAD2 @B@@@@OH

)@@G@@PUT-FILE.   @@@@@@@#@@@@       BN-100.    @C@@@@           READ INPUT-FIOJ
)@@G@@LE  AT END GO TO BN-500.@B@@@@           SET SEC-USERS-ADD-INDEX TO 1.  OK
)@@G@@@B@@@@           SEARCH SEC-USERS-ADD-CYCLE     @B@@@@               VAROL
)@@G@@YING SEC-USERS-ADD-INDEX@A@@@@               AT END GO TO BN-400  @F@@@@OM

)@@G@@@B@@@@               INPUT-CYCLE UPON PRINTER.  @^@@@@           GO TO BOR

)@@G@@EWRITE SEC-USERS-RECORD FROM SEC-USERS-FHEAD2   @B@@@@               INVOW

)@@G@@@A@@@@           ADD 1 TO SEC-USERS-KEY.  @A@@@@           DELETE SEC-USPQ
)@@G@@ERS RECORD  @B@@@@               INVALID KEY GO TO BR-999.  @ @@@@      PR
)@@G@@     IF U-STATUS = '00' @ @@@@               GO TO BR-100   @#@@@@      PS
)@@G@@     ELSE   @ @@@@               GO TO BR-999.  @@@@@@@#@@@@       BR-90PT
)@@G@@0.    @F@@@@           EXHIBIT NAMED '*FATAL ERROR* BR-900: INVALID KEY PU
)@@G@@'     @B@@@@               SEC-USERS-KEY U-STATUS.    @A@@@@           APV
)@@G@@DD 1 TO ERRORS-FATAL.   @@@@@@@#@@@@       BR-999.    @ @@@@           CPW

)@@G@@CTION.@A@@@@      ******************************@@@@@@@#@@@@       BS-00PY
)@@G@@0.    @ @@@@           IF N-OPT NOT = 0   @ @@@@               GO TO BS-PZ
)@@G@@999.  @@@@@@@H@@@@      * BIT 31 OF THE RUN'S CONDITION WORD IS SET IF TQA
)@@G@@HIS RUN IS A RESTART    @F@@@@      * AFTER A SYSTEM CRASH, I.E. DUE TO QB
)@@G@@THE @RUN R-SUBOPTION.   @G@@@@      * WE MUST MAKE AN ASSUMPTION AS TO WQC
)@@G@@HETHER THE RUN CAUGHT IN THE  @H@@@@      * CRASH HAD OR HAD NOT DONE THQD
)@@G@@E @START IN THIS PARAGRAPH BEFORE THE     @G@@@@      * CRASH.   AS SECRQE
)@@G@@UN EXECUTION IS ALMOST ALWAYS SHORTER THAN THE  @G@@@@      * PHASE 2 SEQF
)@@G@@CURE ECL, IT IS MORE PROBABLE THAT THE @START WAS     @F@@@@      * DONEQG
)@@G@@.  SO IF THIS IS A RESTART, DON'T DO ANOTHER @START.  @@@@@@@B@@@@      QH
)@@G@@     CALL 'COND' USING COND-WORD.   @B@@@@           IF COND-RESTART-BITQI
)@@G@@ NOT = 0    @ @@@@               GO TO BS-999.  @@@@@@@A@@@@           IQJ
)@@G@@F DAY-OF-WEEK = 'SAT'   @ @@@@               GO TO BS-300.  @@@@@@@G@@@@QK
)@@G@@      * MONDAY THRU FRIDAY: RUNS 8 A.M. TO 11 P.M. THEN START NEXT DAY  QL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@^@@@@           IF TW-HH < 23@D@@@@               ADD 1 TW-HH GIVQM
)@@G@@ING SECRUN-START-TIME   @#@@@@           ELSE   @C@@@@               MOVQN
)@@G@@E 8 TO SECRUN-START-TIME.     @^@@@@           GO TO BS-400.@@@@@@@D@@@@QO
)@@G@@      * SATURDAY: RUNS 8 A.M. TO 4 P.M. THEN DIES.    @@@@@@@#@@@@      QP
)@@G@@ BS-300.    @^@@@@           IF TW-HH < 16@D@@@@               ADD 1 TW-QQ
)@@G@@HH GIVING SECRUN-START-TIME   @ @@@@               GO TO BS-400   @#@@@@QR
)@@G@@           ELSE   @ @@@@               GO TO BS-999.  @@@@@@@#@@@@      QS
)@@G@@ BS-400.    @ @@@@           IF T-OPT NOT = 0   @E@@@@               EXHQT
)@@G@@IBIT NAMED TIME-WORD SECRUN-STARTCARD     @ @@@@               GO TO BS-QU
)@@G@@999.  @E@@@@           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS SECRUN-STARTCARD.    QV
)@@G@@@A@@@@           IF CSF-STATUS NOT = 0    @A@@@@               ADD 1 TO QW
)@@G@@ERRORS-FATAL@B@@@@               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE.    @@@@@@@#@@@@QX
)@@G@@       BS-999.    @#@@@@           EXIT.  _@@@@@CEPTED-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@@QY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@A@@@4       IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.     @ @@@4       PROGRQZ
)@@G@@AM-ID. SECRUN.    @@@@@4@F@@@4      *    WRITTEN BY RICHARD STRANGE - SDRA
)@@G@@C/ISI RTP NOVEMBER 1980 @@@@@4@G@@@4      *    THIS PROGRAM READS THE FIRB
)@@G@@LE SEC-USERS CONTAINING BACKED UP   @G@@@4      *    REQUESTS FROM THE URC
)@@G@@SER COMMUNITY FOR FILE RECOVERY.  THE     @H@@@4      *    PROGRAM BUILDRD
)@@G@@S AND @STARTS A SECURE RUNSTREAM TO CARRY OUT THE     @G@@@4      *    RRE
)@@G@@ECOVERY.   IT ALSO LISTS DATA ABOUT THE USERS MAKING THE    @H@@@4      RF
)@@G@@*    REQUESTS AND THE FILES THEY REQUESTED.   FINALLY THE SEC-USERS     RG
)@@G@@@A@@@4      *    FILE IS RE-INITIALIZED.  @@@@@4@A@@@4      * LEVEL 1.1:RH
)@@G@@ FIRST RELEASE    @G@@@4      * LEVEL 1.2: JAN 30,1981 - HANDLES MORE THRI
)@@G@@AN 50 (CURRENT MAX-FILES@H@@@4      *            SETTING) FILES IN SEC-URJ
)@@G@@SERS BY STARTING ANOTHER SECRUN TO  @D@@@4      *            CARRY ON FRRK
)@@G@@OM FILE 51, AND SO ON.  @F@@@4      * LEVEL 1.3: FEB 6, 1981 - WRITE RECRL
)@@G@@ORDS TO SEC-HIST FILE   @H@@@4      * LEVEL 2.0: MARCH 1981 - DOUBLE TAPRM
)@@G@@ES, RECOVERY OF PHASE 2 (@ADD OF    @D@@@4      *            SECURE ECL)RN
)@@G@@ LOST IN MACHINE-CRASH  @C@@@4      * LEVEL 3.0: MAY 1981 - MUFS COMPATIRO
)@@G@@BLE   @C@@@4      * LEVEL 2.1: REMOVES TEMP CODE LEFT IN 2.0@G@@@4      RP
)@@G@@* LEVEL 2.2: MAKES FILE-CYCLE ZZ9 (AS CYCLE 009=OCTAL=ILLEGAL)    @G@@@4RQ
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 3.0: GENERATES ECL COMPATIBLE WITH MUFS VERSIONS OF SECURERR
)@@G@@@H@@@4      * LEVEL 3.1: DOES @START FROM DATA-FILE 'USER*SECRUN' (RUNS RS
)@@G@@WERE LOST   @I@@@4      *            DUE TO @PACK OF PF USER*RUNSTREAM WRT
)@@G@@HICH CONTAINED SECRUN ELT)    @I@@@4      * LEVEL 3.2: NO START OF RECOVRU
)@@G@@ERY RUN (45FILZ) FROM CONTINUATION RUN (45FIL1) @I@@@4      *           RV
)@@G@@ HISTORY KEYS IN START-FILE (FOR 45FILZ) INSTEAD OF PRINT-FILE    @H@@@4RW
)@@G@@      * LEVEL 3.3: PHASE 2 ADD-FILE CYCLES KEPT IN HEADER-2: RECOVERY/RERX
)@@G@@MOVAL @H@@@4                   DONE BY CYCLE NUMBERS IN CASE MORE THAN ORY
)@@G@@NE INCOMPLETE.    @H@@@4                   LOAD LOCAL+SHARED FILES IN ONRZ
)@@G@@E SECURE XQT IF SAME TAPE     @H@@@4      * LEVEL 4.0: SORT SEC-USERS FISA
)@@G@@RST INTO TAPE-ORDER.  ONE RUN GENERATED   @H@@@4      *            FOR ESB
)@@G@@ACH SECURE/READER EXECUTION. @RELOAD.SECURE WITH UP TO@H@@@4      *     SC
)@@G@@       3 TAPES GIVEN TO GET MULTI-ACTIVITY LOADING.  THESE MODS   @I@@@4SD
)@@G@@      *            SHOULD SPEED FILE LOADS, ESPECIALLY WHEN THERE ARE MASE
)@@G@@NY FILES    @F@@@4      *            STACKED UP IN SEC-USERS ON DIFFERENSF
)@@G@@T TAPES.    @G@@@4      * LEVEL 4.1: REWRITES SEC-HIST HEADER WHEN ZERO SG
)@@G@@LOAD REQUESTS     @H@@@4      * LEVEL 4.2: IGNORES TWO ADJACENT, IDENTICSH
)@@G@@AL FILENAMES ON 'LOAD FILE..' @G@@@4      *            CARD (THE SECOND SI
)@@G@@IS A 'FILE NOT FOUND' IN SECURE 21) @D@@@4      * LEVEL 4.3: ADDED BC-45SJ
)@@G@@6 LABEL FOR SPNT>77     @D@@@4      *            SEPARATED FATAL+WARNINGSK
)@@G@@ ERRORS     @H@@@4      * LEVEL 4.4: DUPLICATE FILE SKIPPING CODE CORRECSL
)@@G@@TED(BC-455 TO BC-100)   @I@@@4      *            SPACES BEFORE 'STRING' SM
)@@G@@IN BC-550/'FTITLE' REFERENCES REMOVED     @F@@@4      *            NO MSSN
)@@G@@G TO CONSOLE ON SATURDAYS IF RUN ERRORS   @E@@@4      *            SYS$*SO
)@@G@@DLOC$ LEFT ASSIGNED IN GENERATED ECL@G@@@4      * LEVEL 4.5: ADDED PRINTSP
)@@G@@ER LISTING OF START-FILE NAMES AND USER   @G@@@4      *            FILESSQ
)@@G@@ LOADED IN THEM; 'SHARED <FILE> TO LOCAL' IN ECL@C@@@4      * LEVEL 4.6:SR
)@@G@@ FILE-HOST CHANGED TO PIC XX  @F@@@4      *            TAPE/SECURE/READESS
)@@G@@R COUNTS WRITTEN TO SEC-HIST  @I@@@4      *            CLOSE SEC-HIST INST
)@@G@@ AA-000 TO GET HEADER INFO WRITTEN IN PCIOS 4R1 @E@@@4      * LEVEL 4.7:SU
)@@G@@ COUNTS READER RUNS CORRECTLY (IN BC-700) @H@@@4      * LEVEL 4.8: PRINTSV
)@@G@@S BUT SKIPS DUPLICATE FILES FLAGGED BY RELOAD(CT-)    @@@@@4@G@@@4      SW
)@@G@@* LEVEL 4.8: SEC-HIST DATE-TABLE HOLDS DATES AS E.G. '820321'     @E@@@4SX
)@@G@@      *            SEC-HIST NOT OPENED IF NO FILES TO LOAD  @B@@@4      SY
)@@G@@* LEVEL 4.9: INSTALLATION-PROCS USED@D@@@4      *            INCOMPLETE SZ
)@@G@@CYCLES REMOVED IN BM-100@G@@@4      * LEVEL 4.10: PRINT-FILES FOR LOAD RTA
)@@G@@UNS CATALOGED IN BD-.. SO CAN @F@@@4      *             BE ENTERED IN SETB
)@@G@@C-HIST (WAS CAT.IN RUN ITSELF)@ @@@4       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.  @ @@@4TC
)@@G@@       CONFIGURATION SECTION. @A@@@4       SOURCE-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.TD
)@@G@@@A@@@4       OBJECT-COMPUTER. UNIVAC-1110.@ @@@4       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTTE
)@@G@@ION.  @^@@@4       FILE-CONTROL.    @E@@@4           SELECT START-FILE ATF

)@@G@@UNPR-FILENAME.    @D@@@4           MOVE FILE-CYCLE TO SECRUN-PRINT-CYCLEBA

)@@G@@@ @@@4               GO TO AA-900.  @@@@@4@D@@@4           MOVE SEC-USERBN
)@@G@@S-NUM-FILES TO SORTF-NUM-RECS.@E@@@4           CALL 'SORTF' USING SORTF-BO
)@@G@@NUM-RECS SORTF-SIZE     @E@@@4                              SORTF-RETURNBP
)@@G@@   SORTF-OPTION.  @@@@@4@G@@@4      * SORT-ORDER EXPLANATION: (1) SORT-OBQ
)@@G@@FILE - TO SEPARATE SECURE AND @G@@@4      * READER LOADS: IF OFILE NOT LBR
)@@G@@OW-VALUES, READER WILL BE USED TO   @C@@@4      * LOAD THE FILE INTO THEBS
)@@G@@ NAMED OUTPUT AREA@H@@@4      * (2) TAPE1 - TO GET ALL FILES ON THE SAMEBT
)@@G@@ TAPE TOGETHER SO WE GENERATE @F@@@4      * ONE SECURE/READER EXECUTION BU
)@@G@@ONLY (I.E. RUN) FOR EACH TAPE @I@@@4      * (3) TAPE2 - SO THAT DOUBLE TBV
)@@G@@APE LOADS COME AFTER ALL SINGLE TAPE ENTRIES    @H@@@4      * FOR A GIVEBW
)@@G@@N TAPE1 (I.E. IF WE HAD SEC123,SEC123+SEC124,SEC123 THIS    @H@@@4      BX
)@@G@@* MUST BE SORTED TO SEC123,SEC123,SEC123+SEC124 SINCE THE DOUBLE TAPE   BY
)@@G@@@I@@@4      * GETS ITS OWN RUN AND WITHOUT THE SORT THERE WOULD BE 3 RUNBZ
)@@G@@S INSTEAD OF 2    @H@@@4      * AFTER THE SORT - RUN1=THE 2 FILES ON SECCA
)@@G@@123 ALONE,RUN2=SEC123+SEC124) @H@@@4      * (4) FILENAME - SO THAT IF A CB
)@@G@@FILE IS ENTERED TWICE WITH THE SAME TAPE  @G@@@4      * THE DUPLICATION CC
)@@G@@CAN BE ELIMINATED (IN BC-100) THUS AVOIDING     @G@@@4      * THE 'FILE CD

)@@G@@USERS.@#@@@4       AA-900.    @B@@@4           PERFORM BS-START-NEXT-SECCK

)@@G@@@A@@@4           COPY SECRUN-SHARE-3.     @E@@@4           IF USER-TAPE-IG

)@@G@@               ADD 1 TO WS-TAPES-THIS-RUN.@^@@@4           WRITE SREC.  RN
)@@G@@@A@@@4           MOVE SPACES TO SREC.     @ @@@4           COPY SECRUN-RRO
)@@G@@EADER.@^@@@4           WRITE SREC.  @B@@@4           MOVE '@FREE,S T.' TRP
)@@G@@O SREC.     @^@@@4           WRITE SREC.  @C@@@4           MOVE USER-OFNRQ
)@@G@@AME TO USER-FILENAME.   @B@@@4           MOVE SPACES TO WS-SREC-FILE.   RR
)@@G@@@C@@@4           STRING USER-OFNAME DELIMITED BY SPACE@C@@@4            RS

)@@G@@0-CHGREF-CODE.    @C@@@4           PERFORM BC-800-CYCLES-TO-SEC-HIST.   RW
)@@G@@@B@@@4           PERFORM BJ-COMPLETE-STARTFILE. @@@5@4@]@@@5      /     RX
)@@G@@@G@@@4      ************************************************************RY
)@@G@@***** @@@@@4@A@@@4       BC-800-CYCLES-TO-SEC-HIST.   @A@@@5      ******RZ
)@@G@@*********************   @@@@@4@H@@@4      * STORE DATA ABOUT THE FILES TSA
)@@G@@O BE RELOADED IN SEC-HIST FOR 'SECDUMP'   @@@@@4@D@@@4           MOVE USSB
)@@G@@ER-FILE-LOAD-KEY TO SEC-HIST-KEY.   @C@@@4           READ SEC-HIST INTO SC
)@@G@@WS-HISTORY-RECORD @B@@@4               INVALID KEY PERFORM BC-930.@E@@@4SD
)@@G@@           MOVE SECRUN-PRINT-CYCLE TO WS-HIST-SECRUN-CYCLE. @E@@@4      SE
)@@G@@     MOVE START-FILE-CYCLE   TO WS-HIST-START-CYCLE.  @E@@@4           MSF

)@@G@@ SEC-HIST-RECORD FROM WS-HISTORY-RECORD   @B@@@4               INVALID KSH
)@@G@@EY PERFORM BC-930.@@@@@4@G@@@4      ************************************SI
)@@G@@***************************** @@@@@4@#@@@4       BC-900.    @E@@@4      SJ
)@@G@@     EXHIBIT NAMED '*FATAL ERROR* BC-900: INVALID KEY'@D@@@4            SK
)@@G@@   WORK-KEY W-STATUS USER-FILE-RECORD.    @A@@@4           ADD 1 TO ERROSL
)@@G@@RS-FATAL.   @^@@@4           GO TO BC-950.@#@@@4       BC-910.    @G@@@4SM
)@@G@@           EXHIBIT NAMED '*FATAL ERROR* BC-910: INVALID KEY ON READ'    SN
)@@G@@@A@@@4               WORK-KEY W-STATUS.   @A@@@4           ADD 1 TO ERROSO
)@@G@@RS-FATAL.   @^@@@4           GO TO BC-950.@@@@@4@#@@@4       BC-930.    SP
)@@G@@@F@@@4           EXHIBIT NAMED '*WARNING ERROR* BC-930: INVALID KEY '   SQ
)@@G@@@E@@@4               ' ON READ/REWRITE' SEC-HIST-KEY H-STATUS.    @A@@@4SR
)@@G@@           ADD 1 TO ERRORS-WARNING. @@@@@4@#@@@4       BC-950.    @C@@@4SS
)@@G@@           MOVE WS-TYPE2-KEY TO SEC-HIST-KEY.   @E@@@4           MOVE WSST
)@@G@@-TAPES-THIS-RUN TO WS-HIST-TAPE-COUNT.    @E@@@4           MOVE WS-NUM-SSU
)@@G@@ECURE-RUNS TO WS-HIST-SECURE-RUNS.  @E@@@4           MOVE WS-NUM-READER-SV
)@@G@@RUNS TO WS-HIST-READER-RUNS.  @C@@@4           MOVE DATE-WORD TO WS-HISTSW
)@@G@@-RUN-DATE.  @C@@@4           MOVE TIME-WORD TO WS-HIST-RUN-TIME.  @A@@@4SX
)@@G@@           MOVE 2 TO WS-HIST-TYPE.  @E@@@4           WRITE SEC-HIST-RECOSY
)@@G@@RD FROM WS-HISTORY-RECORD     @F@@@4               INVALID KEY EXHIBIT NSZ

)@@G@@@ @@@4           CLOSE SEC-HIST.    @]@@@4      /     @A@@@4       BD-SETC
)@@G@@TUP-STARTFILE SECTION.  @A@@@4      ***************************** @@@@@4TD
)@@G@@@#@@@4       BD-000.    @@@@@4@D@@@4      * CATALOG A FILE TO CONTAIN FITE
)@@G@@LE LOADING ECL    @@@@@4@C@@@4           MOVE SPACES          TO CSF-MESTF
)@@G@@SAGE. @C@@@4           MOVE '@ASG,UP'       TO CSF-COMMAND. @C@@@4      TG
)@@G@@     MOVE '(+1). ' TO START-FILE-RCYCLE.  @D@@@4           MOVE START-FITH
)@@G@@LE-STRING TO CSF-STARTFILE.   @D@@@4           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATTI
)@@G@@US CSF-MESSAGE.   @B@@@4           IF REQUEST-ACCEPTED-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@4TJ
)@@G@@               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE     @C@@@4               PERFORM ATK
)@@G@@B-ERROR-TERMINATION.    @@@@@4@G@@@4      * GIVE THE FILE THE INTERNAL NTL

)@@G@@         PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE     @C@@@4               PERFORM AB-ERROTP
)@@G@@R-TERMINATION.    @C@@@4           MOVE 'START-FILE' TO FITEM-INT-FNAME.TQ
)@@G@@@ @@@4           PERFORM AY-FITEM.  @C@@@4           MOVE FILE-CYCLE TO TR
)@@G@@START-FILE-CYCLE. @A@@@4           MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @A@@@4      TS
)@@G@@     MOVE '****' TO PSTART1.  @D@@@4           MOVE FITEM-STRING TO PSTATT
)@@G@@RT2 SAVE-STRING.  @ @6@4           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@A@6@4           MTU
)@@G@@OVE SPACES TO PREC.     @^@6@4           WRITE PREC.  @A@@@4           OTV
)@@G@@PEN OUTPUT START-FILE.  @B@@@4           MOVE 1 TO START-FILE-OPEN.     TW
)@@G@@@@@@@4@F@@@4      * PUT THE START-FILE CYCLE IN SEC-USERS HEADER-2 RECORTX
)@@G@@D     @G@@@4      * IF THE RUN COMPLETES NORMALLY, THE '@XQT,A SECRUN' WTY
)@@G@@ILL REMOVE  @F@@@4      * THIS CYCLE ENTRY (BY CALLING BN-REMOVE-LOADECLTZ
)@@G@@-CYCLE)     @G@@@4      * IF NOT REMOVED, BM-LIST-INCOMPLETE-RUNS IN NEXUA
)@@G@@T @XQT OF SECRUN  @E@@@4      * WILL LIST THE INCOMPLETE FILE-LOADING RUUB

)@@G@@                   NEXT SENTENCE.   @G@@@4           MOVE FILE-CYCLE TO UG
)@@G@@SEC-USERS-ADD-CYCLE(SEC-USERS-ADD-INDEX). @@@@@4@G@@@4      * CATALOG THUH
)@@G@@E PRINT-FILE FOR THE LOADING RUN.  DONE HERE SO THE   @D@@@4      * CYCLUI
)@@G@@E CAN BE PUT INTO SEC-HIST FOR 'SECDUMP'  @@@@@4@B@@@4           MOVE SPUJ
)@@G@@ACES TO CSF-MESSAGE.    @C@@@4           MOVE '@ASG,UP'       TO CSF-COMUK

)@@G@@-BIT NOT = 0@B@@@4               PERFORM AX-CSF-FAILURE     @C@@@4      UO
)@@G@@         PERFORM AB-ERROR-TERMINATION.    @C@@@4           MOVE '@USE   UP
)@@G@@FITEM-FILE,' TO CSF-USE.@D@@@4           CALL 'CSF' USING CSF-STATUS CSFUQ

)@@G@@@ @@@4               UPON PRINTER.  @A@@@4           ADD 1 TO ERRORS-WARVA

)@@G@@HEADER-RECORD     @B@@@@               INVALID KEY GO TO BC-900.  @F@@@]NA

)@@G@@@ @@@@      ********************    @@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-000.    @G@@@@NV
)@@G@@           DISPLAY 'ENTER SINGLE TAPES AS E.G. ''SEC123''' UPON PRINTER.NW

)@@G@@           READ INPUT-FILE  AT END GO TO BD-999.@C@@@@           MOVE INOB
)@@G@@PUT-WORD1 TO INPUT-TAPE1.     @B@@@@           IF INPUT-HYPHEN NOT = SPAOC
)@@G@@CE    @ @@@@               GO TO BD-200.  @@@@@@@ @@@@      * SINGLE TAPOD
)@@G@@E ENTERED   @@@@@@@A@@@@           PERFORM BE-GET-RECORD.   @A@@@@      OE
)@@G@@     IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-100.  @B@@@@OF
)@@G@@           PERFORM BF-DISPLAY-CURRENT.    @A@@@@           PERFORM BH-GEOG
)@@G@@T-NEW-DATA. @A@@@@           IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@            OH
)@@G@@   GO TO BD-100.  @A@@@@           PERFORM BJ-CHANGE-ENTRY. @A@@@@      OI
)@@G@@     PERFORM BK-CHECK-DOUBLES.@^@@@@           GO TO BD-100.@@@@@@@#@@@@OJ
)@@G@@       BD-200.    @@@@@@@ @@@@      *  TAPE-RANGE ENTERED   @@@@@@@B@@@@OK
)@@G@@           COPY SECTAPEMOD-TAPE-NAMES.    @B@@@@           MOVE INPUT-TAOL
)@@G@@PE1 TO FIRST-TAPE.@A@@@@           PERFORM BE-GET-RECORD.   @A@@@@      OM
)@@G@@     IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-100.  @B@@@@ON
)@@G@@           PERFORM BF-DISPLAY-CURRENT.    @C@@@@           MOVE INPUT-TAOO
)@@G@@PE2 TO INPUT-TAPE1.     @A@@@@           PERFORM BE-GET-RECORD.   @A@@@@OP
)@@G@@           IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-100.  OQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@           PERFORM BF-DISPLAY-CURRENT.    @A@@@@           PERFORMOR
)@@G@@ BH-GET-NEW-DATA. @A@@@@           IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@      OS
)@@G@@         GO TO BD-100.  @@@@@@@B@@@@      *  LOOP TO MODIFY TAPES WITHINOT
)@@G@@ RANGE@@@@@@@A@@@@           PERFORM BE-GET-RECORD.   @ @@@@           IOU
)@@G@@F ERROR-SWITCH = 0@ @@@@               GO TO BD-400.  @ @@@@           IOV
)@@G@@F LIST-SWITCH = 0 @ @@@@               GO TO BD-100   @#@@@@           EOW
)@@G@@LSE   @ @@@@               GO TO BD-600.  @@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-400.    OX
)@@G@@@A@@@@           IF LIST-SWITCH NOT = 0   @B@@@@               PERFORM BOY
)@@G@@F-DISPLAY-CURRENT @ @@@@               GO TO BD-600.  @A@@@@           MOZ
)@@G@@OVE 0 TO ERROR-SWITCH.  @A@@@@           PERFORM BJ-CHANGE-ENTRY. @A@@@@PA
)@@G@@           IF ERROR-SWITCH NOT = 0  @ @@@@               GO TO BD-600.  PB
)@@G@@@B@@@@           IF TAPE-H-DOUBLE-COUNT NOT = 0 @B@@@@               PERPC
)@@G@@FORM BK-CHECK-DOUBLES.  @#@@@[       BD-600.    @A@@@@           SUBTRACPD
)@@G@@T 1 FROM RANGE.   @^@@@@           IF RANGE < 0 @ @@@@               GO PE
)@@G@@TO BD-100   @#@@@@           ELSE   @A@@@@               ADD 1 TO INPUT-PF
)@@G@@T19   @ @@@@               GO TO BD-400.  @@@@@@@ @@@@      **** END OF PG
)@@G@@LOOP ****   @@@@@@@#@@@@       BD-999.    @B@@@@           CLOSE INPUT-FPH
)@@G@@ILE SEC-TAPES.    @]@@@@      /     @ @@@@       BE-GET-RECORD SECTION. PI
)@@G@@@ @@@@      ************************@@@@@@@#@@@@       BE-100.    @B@@@@PJ

)@@G@@ALID KEY GO TO BE-200.  @^@@@@           GO TO BE-999.@#@@@@       BE-20PM

)@@G@@@A@@@@           MOVE 1 TO ERROR-SWITCH.  @@@@@@@#@@@@       BE-999.    PO
)@@G@@@#@@@@           EXIT.  @@@@@@@@@@@@@A@@@@       BF-DISPLAY-CURRENT SECTPP
)@@G@@ION.  @A@@@@      ***************************** @@@@@@@#@@@@       BF-10PQ
)@@G@@0.    @A@@@@           MOVE TAPE-YY TO WS-T-YY. @A@@@@           MOVE TAPR
)@@G@@PE-MM TO WS-T-MM. @A@@@@           MOVE TAPE-DD TO WS-T-DD. @A@@@@      PS

)@@G@@* CODE TO GET NEW DATE AND TIME     @@@@@@@#@@@@       BH-100.    @A@@@@QI

)@@G@@@@@@@@@A@@@@       BI-CALCULATE-JULIAN SECTION. @A@@@@      ************RG
)@@G@@***************** @@@@@@@#@@@@       BI-100.    @@@@@@@B@@@@      * CALCRH
)@@G@@ULATE PBDATE AND JULIAN-CNT   @@@@@@@ @@@@           MOVE 28 TO FEB.    RI
)@@G@@@A@@@@           MOVE WS-P-MM TO RD-MM.   @A@@@@           MOVE WS-P-DD RJ
)@@G@@TO RD-DD.   @A@@@@           MOVE WS-P-YY TO RD-YY.   @A@@@@           MRK
)@@G@@OVE WS-P-HR TO RD-HR.   @A@@@@           MOVE WS-P-MN TO RD-MN.   @A@@@@RL
)@@G@@           MOVE WS-P-SS TO RD-SS.   @@@@@@@E@@@@      *  CALCULATE THE YRM
)@@G@@EAR WITH MODULO 1964 (AS IN TDATE$) @@@@@@@C@@@@           SUBTRACT 64 FRN
)@@G@@ROM WS-P-YY GIVING SUB3.@E@@@@      * CHECK FOR LEAP-YEAR: IF SO, INCREMRO
)@@G@@ENT FEB DAYS.     @@@@@@@F@@@@           DIVIDE 4 INTO SUB3 GIVING LEAP-RP
)@@G@@CNT REMAINDER SUB2.     @^@@@@           IF SUB2 = 0  @ @@@@            RQ
)@@G@@   ADD 1 TO FEB.  @@@@@@@G@@@@      * IF RUN STARTED AFTER MIDNIGHT BUT RR
)@@G@@BEFORE PRIME-SHIFT (0700 HRS) @A@@@@      * DATE AS THE PREVIOUS DAY    RS
)@@G@@@@@@@@@ @@@@           IF WS-P-HR > 7     @ @@@@               GO TO BI-RT
)@@G@@200.  @A@@@@           SUBTRACT 1 FROM WS-P-DD. @ @@@@           IF WS-PRU
)@@G@@-DD NOT = 0 @ @@@@               GO TO BI-200.  @A@@@@           SUBTRACRV
)@@G@@T 1 FROM WS-P-MM. @ @@@@           IF WS-P-MM = 0     @B@@@@            RW
)@@G@@   MOVE 12 TO WS-P-MM SUB1    @C@@@@               SUBTRACT 1 FROM WS-P-RX
)@@G@@YY SUB3     @#@@@@           ELSE   @A@@@@               MOVE WS-P-MM TORY
)@@G@@ SUB1.@C@@@@           MOVE MONTH-DAYS(SUB1) TO WS-P-DD.    @@@@@@@#@@@@RZ
)@@G@@       BI-200.    @A@@@@           MOVE WS-P-MM TO SUB1.    @@@@@@@G@@@@SA
)@@G@@      * CALCULATE NO. OF DAYS SINCE 1/1/64, ALLOWING FOR LEAP-YEARS     SB
)@@G@@@@@@@@@D@@@@           COMPUTE JULIAN-CNT = SUB3 * 365 + LEAP-CNT @F@@@@SC
)@@G@@                                 + JULIAN-DAYS(SUB1) + WS-P-DD.   @@@@@@SD
)@@G@@@I@@@@      * IF THIS IS A LEAP-YEAR (SUB2=0) AND WE ARE PAST FEBRUARY (SE
)@@G@@SUB1>2),ADD 1     @@@@@@@A@@@@           IF SUB2 = 0 AND SUB1 > 2 @A@@@@SF
)@@G@@               ADD 1 TO JULIAN-CNT. @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@A@@@@       BJ-CHSG

)@@G@@       AA-MAIN SECTION 1.     @^@@@U      ******************@#@@@U      AR

)@@G@@@ @@@U           PERFORM BD-UPDATE. @B@@@U           PERFORM BM-RUN-STATAV

)@@G@@ITIATE SECTION 51.@ @@@U      **********************  @@@@@U@#@@@U      AZ
)@@G@@ BA-000.    @C@@@U           CALL 'ORIGIN' USING SUB1 HOST-ID.    @A@@@UBA
)@@G@@           MOVE 1 TO COND-WORD.     @B@@@U           CALL 'SETC' USING CBB
)@@G@@OND-WORD.   @ @@@U           OPEN OUTPUT PFILE. @D@@@U           CALL 'DBC
)@@G@@ATE' USING DATE-WORD TIME-WORD.     @E@@@U           DISPLAY 'SECUPDATE BD
)@@G@@5.0 ' TIME-WORD ' ' DATE-WORD @C@@@U               ' ON ' HOST-ID UPON PBE
)@@G@@RINTER.     @C@@@U*TEMP*     ACCEPT HOST-ID FROM CARD-READER.     @D@@@UBF
)@@G@@*TEMP*     DISPLAY 'TEMPORARY:BA-000 HOST-ID=' HOST-ID@ @@@U*TEMP*      BG
)@@G@@   UPON PRINTER.  @@@@@U@B@@@U           CALL 'FITEM' USING FITEM-PKT.  BH
)@@G@@@B@@@U           MOVE FITEM-CYCLE TO FILE-CYCLE.@D@@@U           STRING BI
)@@G@@FITEM-QUALIFIER DELIMITED BY SPACE  @D@@@U                  '*'         BJ
)@@G@@    DELIMITED BY SIZE   @D@@@U                  FITEM-EXT-FNAME DELIMITEBK
)@@G@@D BY SPACE  @D@@@U                  '('             DELIMITED BY SIZE   BL
)@@G@@@D@@@U                  FILE-CYCLE      DELIMITED BY SIZE   @D@@@U      BM
)@@G@@            ') ***'         DELIMITED BY SIZE   @A@@@U                  BN
)@@G@@INTO PRTCN-FILE.  @D@@@U           CALL 'PRTCN' USING PRTCN-LENGTH PRTCNBO
)@@G@@-PKT. @]@@@U      /     @A@@@U       BB-TAPE-SETUP SECTION 51.    @ @@@UBP
)@@G@@      ************************@@@@@U@#@@@U       BB-000.    @ @@@U      BQ
)@@G@@     OPEN I-O SEC-TAPES.@ @@@U           MOVE 0 TO TAPE-KEY.@D@@@U      BR
)@@G@@     READ SEC-TAPES INTO TAPE-HEADER-RECORD     @A@@@U               KEYBS
)@@G@@ IS TAPE-KEYX     @B@@@U               INVALID KEY GO TO BB-800.  @^@@@UBT
)@@G@@           GO TO BB-900.@@@@@U@#@@@U       BB-800.    @D@@@U           EBU
)@@G@@XHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BB-000: INVALID KEY'@A@@@U               T-STATUS BV
)@@G@@TAPE-KEY.   @@@@@U@#@@@U       BB-900.    @B@@@U           MOVE LOW-VALUBW
)@@G@@ES TO TAPE-RECORD.@@@@@U@@@@@U@@@@@U@A@@@U       BC-START-UPDATE SECTIONBX
)@@G@@ 52.  @A@@@U      **************************    @@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-00BY
)@@G@@0.    @ @@@U           OPEN I-O SEC-FILES.@B@@@U           MOVE 0 TO SECBZ
)@@G@@-PRT-CNT SAVE-CNT.@A@@@U           SET D-TAPE-INDEX TO 1.   @C@@@U      CA
)@@G@@     ACCEPT SECURE-ID FROM CARD-READER.   @@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-100.    CB
)@@G@@@A@@@U           PERFORM BC-800-READ.     @C@@@U           IF LINE-WORD1CC
)@@G@@ NOT = SECURE-ID-1 OR   @B@@@U              LINE-WORD2 NOT = SECURE-ID-2CD
)@@G@@@ @@@U               GO TO BC-100.  @ @@@U           MOVE 1 TO USPNT.   CE
)@@G@@@ @@@U           UNSTRING LINE1     @A@@@U               DELIMITED BY '/CF
)@@G@@'     @^@@@U               INTO DUMP@ @@@U               DELIMITER DELIMCG
)@@G@@@ @@@U               POINTER USPNT. @ @@@U           IF DELIM NOT = '/' CH
)@@G@@@ @@@U               GO TO BC-910.  @A@@@U           SUBTRACT 3 FROM USPCI
)@@G@@NT.   @ @@@U           UNSTRING LINE1     @A@@@U               DELIMITEDCJ
)@@G@@ BY SPACE   @ @@@U               INTO RUN-DATE  @ @@@U               POICK
)@@G@@NTER USPNT. @ @@@U           UNSTRING LINE1     @A@@@U               DELCL
)@@G@@IMITED BY ':'     @^@@@U               INTO DUMP@ @@@U               DELCM
)@@G@@IMITER DELIM@ @@@U               POINTER USPNT. @ @@@U           IF DELICN
)@@G@@M NOT = ':' @ @@@U               GO TO BC-910.  @A@@@U           SUBTRACCO
)@@G@@T 3 FROM USPNT.   @ @@@U           UNSTRING LINE1     @A@@@U            CP
)@@G@@   DELIMITED BY SPACE   @ @@@U               INTO RUN-TIME  @ @@@U      CQ
)@@G@@         POINTER USPNT. @A@@@U           MOVE RUN-MM TO RD-MM.    @A@@@UCR
)@@G@@           MOVE RUN-DD TO RD-DD.    @A@@@U           MOVE RUN-YY TO RD-YCS
)@@G@@Y.    @A@@@U           MOVE RUN-HR TO RD-HR.    @A@@@U           MOVE RUCT
)@@G@@N-MN TO RD-MN.    @@@@@U@E@@@U      *  CALCULATE THE YEAR WITH MODULO 19CU
)@@G@@64 (AS IN TDATE$) @@@@@U@C@@@U           SUBTRACT 64 FROM RUN-YY GIVING CV
)@@G@@SUB3. @E@@@U      * CHECK FOR LEAP-YEAR: IF SO, INCREMENT FEB DAYS.     CW
)@@G@@@@@@@U@F@@@U           DIVIDE 4 INTO SUB3 GIVING LEAP-CNT REMAINDER SUB2CX
)@@G@@.     @^@@@U           IF SUB2 = 0  @ @@@U               ADD 1 TO FEB.  CY
)@@G@@@@@@@U@G@@@U      * IF RUN STARTED AFTER MIDNIGHT BUT BEFORE PRIME-SHIFTCZ
)@@G@@ (0700 HRS) @A@@@U      * DATE AS THE PREVIOUS DAY    @@@@@U@^@@@U      DA
)@@G@@     IF RUN-HR > 7@ @@@U               GO TO BC-200.  @A@@@U           SDB
)@@G@@UBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-DD.  @ @@@U           IF RUN-DD NOT = 0  @ @@@U      DC
)@@G@@         GO TO BC-200.  @A@@@U           SUBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-MM.  @^@@@UDD
)@@G@@           IF RUN-MM = 0@B@@@U               MOVE 12 TO RUN-MM SUB1     DE
)@@G@@@B@@@U               SUBTRACT 1 FROM RUN-YY SUB3@#@@@U           ELSE   DF
)@@G@@@A@@@U               MOVE RUN-MM TO SUB1. @C@@@U           MOVE MONTH-DADG
)@@G@@YS(SUB1) TO RUN-DD.     @@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-200.    @A@@@U           MDH
)@@G@@OVE RUN-MM TO SUB1.     @@@@@U@G@@@U      * CALCULATE NO. OF DAYS SINCE DI
)@@G@@1/1/64, ALLOWING FOR LEAP-YEARS     @@@@@U@D@@@U           COMPUTE JULIADJ
)@@G@@N-CNT = SUB3 * 365 + LEAP-CNT @F@@@U                                 + JDK
)@@G@@ULIAN-DAYS(SUB1) + RUN-DD.    @@@@@U@I@@@U      * IF THIS IS A LEAP-YEARDL
)@@G@@ (SUB2=0) AND WE ARE PAST FEBRUARY (SUB1>2),ADD 1     @@@@@U@A@@@U      DM
)@@G@@     IF SUB2 = 0 AND SUB1 > 2 @A@@@U               ADD 1 TO JULIAN-CNT. DN
)@@G@@@@@@@U@G@@@U      * CALCULATE PSEUDO-BINARY DATE (MMDD -PIC 9999- HELD ADO
)@@G@@S BINARY)   @@@@@U@A@@@U           MOVE RUN-MM TO RUN-M.    @A@@@U      DP
)@@G@@     MOVE RUN-DD TO RUN-D.    @B@@@U           MOVE RUN-DATE2 TO PB-DATEDQ
)@@G@@.     @A@@@U           MOVE RUN-YY TO RUN-Y.    @B@@@U           MOVE RUDR
)@@G@@N-MDY-9 TO TAPE-H-DATE. @@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-300.    @B@@@U           MDS
)@@G@@OVE '@@HEAD' TO SEC-FILE-KEY. @C@@@U           READ SEC-FILES INTO SEC-FDT
)@@G@@ILE-HEADER  @A@@@U               KEY IS SEC-FILE-KEY  @B@@@U            DU
)@@G@@   INVALID KEY PERFORM BC-940.@C@@@U           IF HEADER-UPDATE-ERROR-FLDV
)@@G@@AG NOT = 0  @F@@@U*TEMP*         EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BC-300: ERROR-FLDW
)@@G@@AG SET'     @ @@@U               GO TO BC-999   @#@@@U           ELSE   DX
)@@G@@@D@@@U               MOVE 1 TO HEADER-UPDATE-ERROR-FLAG     @C@@@U      DY
)@@G@@         MOVE '@@HEAD' TO SEC-FILE-KEY    @E@@@U               REWRITE SDZ
)@@G@@EC-FILE-REC FROM SEC-FILE-HEADER    @C@@@U                   INVALID KEYEA
)@@G@@ PERFORM BC-950.  @@@@@U@ @@@U      * FIND SECURE COMMANDS  @@@@@U@#@@@UEB
)@@G@@       BC-400.    @A@@@U           PERFORM BC-800-READ.     @B@@@U      EC
)@@G@@     IF LINE-WORD1 NOT = '    1.'   @ @@@U               GO TO BC-400.  ED
)@@G@@@ @@@U           UNSTRING SEC-REC   @C@@@U               DELIMITED BY 'SEE
)@@G@@AVE' OR 'ARCH'    @^@@@U               INTO DUMP@A@@@U               DELEF
)@@G@@IMITER DELIM4,    @^@@@U               DUMP4.   @ @@@U           IF DELIEG
)@@G@@M4 = 'ARCH' @C@@@U               MOVE 'RM' TO SECURE-RUN-TYPE     @ @@@UEH
)@@G@@               GO TO BC-999.  @ @@@U           IF DELIM4 = 'SAVE' @A@@@UEI
)@@G@@               IF DUMP4 = ' ALL'    @C@@@U                   MOVE 'SA' TEJ
)@@G@@O SECURE-RUN-TYPE @A@@@U                   GO TO BC-999     @^@@@U      EK
)@@G@@         ELSE     @C@@@U                   MOVE 'SV' TO SECURE-RUN-TYPE EL
)@@G@@@A@@@U                   GO TO BC-999.    @^@@@U           GO TO BC-900.EM
)@@G@@@@@@@U@^@@@U       BC-800-READ.     @F@@@U           ENTER FORTRAN 'RDSPEN
)@@G@@RT' USING SEC-REC SEC-PRT-IOSTAT.   @A@@@U           IF SEC-PRT-IOSTAT NEO
)@@G@@OT = 0@ @@@U               GO TO BC-900.  @A@@@U           MOVE SKIP-PRTEP
)@@G@@1 TO PREC-1.@D@@@U           MOVE ' ** SECURE PRINT DATA **' TO PREC-2. EQ
)@@G@@@^@@@U           WRITE PREC.  @A@@@U           ADD 1 TO SEC-PRT-CNT.    ER
)@@G@@@@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-900.    @G@@@U           DISPLAY '*ERROR* BC-900: ES
)@@G@@SECURE PRINT-FILE FORMAT ERROR'     @ @@@U               UPON PRINTER.  ET
)@@G@@@^@@@U           GO TO BC-990.@@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-910.    @G@@@U      EU
)@@G@@     DISPLAY '*ERROR* BC-910: DIDN''T FIND DATE-TIME ID-LINE'     @ @@@UEV
)@@G@@               UPON PRINTER.  @C@@@U           WRITE PREC FROM FORMAT-MSEW
)@@G@@G AFTER 3.  @^@@@U           GO TO BC-990.@@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-940.    EX
)@@G@@@F@@@U           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERROR* BC-300: INVALID HEADER KEY-READ'EY
)@@G@@@B@@@U               SEC-FILE-KEY F-STATUS.     @^@@@U           GO TO BEZ
)@@G@@C-990.@@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-950.    @G@@@U           EXHIBIT NAMED '*ERRFA
)@@G@@OR* BC-300: INVALID HEADER KEY-REWRITE'   @B@@@U               SEC-FILE-FB

)@@G@@0.    @A@@@U           ADD 1 TO ERROR-COUNT.    @@@@@U@#@@@U       BC-99FD
)@@G@@9.    @#@@@U           EXIT.  @]@@@U      /     @ @@@U       BD-UPDATE SFE
)@@G@@ECTION 52.  @ @@@U      ********************    @@@@@U@#@@@U       BD-10FF
)@@G@@0.    @@@@@U@E@@@U      * SKIP ALL LINES EXCEPT 'SAVED' OR 'ARCHIVED' LIFG

)@@G@@150.  @A@@@U           IF ACTION-FLD = ' *TAPE' @A@@@U               ADDFL
)@@G@@ 1 TO SKIP-CNT1   @ @@@U               GO TO BD-100.  @@@@@U@#@@@U      FM
)@@G@@ BD-120.    @A@@@U           MOVE SKIP-PRT1 TO PREC-1.@E@@@U           MFN

)@@G@@REC.  @ @@@U           IF FLD1 = 'PMD'    @E@@@U               DISPLAY 'FP

)@@G@@   PERFORM BD-900 THRU BD-902 @ @@@U               GO TO BD-120   @#@@@UFT
)@@G@@           ELSE   @ @@@U               GO TO BD-100.  @@@@@U@#@@@U      FU
)@@G@@ BD-150.    @@@@@U@H@@@U      * WHEN FILE-POSITION ON SECURE-TAPE HAS >3FV
)@@G@@ DIGITS,LINE IS SHIFTED OVER  @@@@@U@ @@@U           IF FILE-D4 = SPACE FW
)@@G@@@C@@@U               MOVE TAPE-FLD-A TO WS-TAPE-NAMES @#@@@U           EFX
)@@G@@LSE   @C@@@U               MOVE TAPE-FLD-B TO WS-TAPE-NAMES.@@@@@U@ @@@UFY
)@@G@@           ADD 1 TO SAVE-CNT. @A@@@U           IF WS-COMMA NOT = ','    FZ
)@@G@@@B@@@U               MOVE 0 TO DOUBLE-TAPE-SW   @#@@@U           ELSE   GA
)@@G@@@B@@@U               MOVE 1 TO DOUBLE-TAPE-SW.  @A@@@X           MOVE HOGB
)@@G@@ST TO FILE-HOST.  @@@@@U@B@@@U           COPY SECUPDATE-SHARE-CODE-1.   GC
)@@G@@@@@@@U@B@@@U           PERFORM BE-UPDATE-SEC-TAPES.   @A@@@Y           IGD
)@@G@@F ERROR-COUNT NOT = 0   @ @@@Y               GO TO BD-999.  @@@@@U@B@@@UGE
)@@G@@      * ENTER FILE-SAVE ITEM IN SEC-FILES @@@@@U@A@@@U           ADD 1 TGF
)@@G@@O FILES-PROCESSED.@B@@@U           MOVE SAVED-FILE TO QUAL-FNAME. @ @@@UGG
)@@G@@           READ SEC-FILES     @A@@@U               KEY IS SEC-FILE-KEY  GH
)@@G@@@B@@@U               INVALID KEY GO TO BD-400.  @@@@@U@E@@@U      * EXISGI
)@@G@@TING FILE HAS BEEN FOUND AND DATA IS TO BE ADDED@@@@@U@E@@@U           AGJ
)@@G@@DD 1 TO LAST-INDEX NUM-OCCURS OLD-FILE-COUNT.   @B@@@U           IF LASTGK
)@@G@@-INDEX > MAX-FILE-ITEM  @A@@@U               MOVE 1 TO LAST-INDEX.@B@@@UGL
)@@G@@           IF NUM-OCCURS > MAX-FILE-ITEM  @C@@@U               MOVE MAX-GM
)@@G@@FILE-ITEM TO NUM-OCCURS.@C@@@U           ADD NUM-OCCURS TO DELETED-ITEM-GN
)@@G@@COUNT.@D@@@U           MOVE TAPE-KEY TO TAPE-INDEX(LAST-INDEX).   @D@@@UGO
)@@G@@           MOVE PB-DATE TO FILE-PBDATE(LAST-INDEX).   @C@@@U           MGP
)@@G@@OVE SEC-FILE-REC TO WS-SAVE-RECORD. @A@@@U           DELETE SEC-FILES REGQ
)@@G@@CORD  @B@@@U               INVALID KEY GO TO BD-940.  @B@@@U           AGR
)@@G@@DD 1 TO DELETED-RECORD-COUNT. @D@@@U           WRITE SEC-FILE-REC FROM WGS
)@@G@@S-SAVE-RECORD     @B@@@U               INVALID KEY GO TO BD-940.  @^@@@UGT
)@@G@@           GO TO BD-100.@@@@@U@B@@@U      * INVALID KEY:  MAY BE NEW FILGU
)@@G@@E-NAME@@@@@U@#@@@U       BD-400.    @A@@@U           IF F-STATUS NOT = 'GV

)@@G@@-TYPE = 'RM' OR 'SA'    @A@@@U               MOVE SPACES TO PREC  @ @@@UGX
)@@G@@               WRITE PREC     @E@@@U               DISPLAY '*WARNING* BDGY
)@@G@@-400: NO ENTRY IN '     @E@@@U                  'SEC-FILES FOR ARCHIVED/GZ

)@@G@@@ @@@U               WRITE PREC.    @A@@@U           ADD 1 TO NEW-FILE-CHB
)@@G@@OUNT. @C@@@U           MOVE 1 TO LAST-INDEX NUM-OCCURS.     @B@@@U      HC
)@@G@@     MOVE TAPE-KEY TO TAPE-INDEX(1).@B@@@U           MOVE PB-DATE TO FILHD
)@@G@@E-PBDATE(1).@ @@@U           WRITE SEC-FILE-REC @B@@@U               INVHE
)@@G@@ALID KEY GO TO BD-960.  @^@@@U           GO TO BD-100.@]@@@U      /     HF
)@@G@@@^@@@U      * ERROR HANDLING *@@@@@U@#@@@U       BD-900.    @F@@@U      HG
)@@G@@     MOVE '** DUMP OUTPUT FROM SECURE SKIPPED **' TO PREC.  @ @@@U      HH
)@@G@@     WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@A@@@U           MOVE SPACES TO PREC.     @ @@@UHI
)@@G@@           WRITE PREC AFTER 2.@#@@@U       BD-902.    @F@@@U           EHJ

)@@G@@F SEC-PRT-IOSTAT NOT = 0@ @@@U               GO TO BD-999.  @A@@@U      HL

)@@G@@        .   @^@@@@$(1),SORTF*         AXR$@[@@@@  .   @B@@@@NREC$*    EQYL
)@@G@@UF      0,X8              .   @B@@@@STATU$*   EQUF      1,X8            YM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@REPLY$*   EQUF      2,X8              .   @B@@@@COMPK$*   EQYN

)@@G@@    EQUF      0103,X8   @ @@@@E$6*      EQUF      0112,X8   @ @@@@E$7*  YX

)@@G@@*   EQUF      0160,X8   @ @@@@XB$*      EQUF      0166,X8   @ @@@@AMT$* ZF
)@@G@@    EQUF      0167,X8   @ @@@@XA$*      EQUF      0170,X8   @ @@@@CORE$*ZG
)@@G@@    EQUF      0171,X8   @ @@@@RETUR$*   EQUF      0172,X8   @ @@@@TRK$* ZH
)@@G@@    EQUF      0173,X8   @ @@@@PO$*      EQUF      0174,X8   @ @@@@OUTPU$ZI
)@@G@@*   EQUF      0175,X8   @ @@@@DSKAS$*   EQUF      0176,X8   @ @@@@WCHPK$ZJ
)@@G@@*   EQUF      0206,X8   @ @@@@INF$*     EQUF      0207,X8   @^@@@@REGSAVZK
)@@G@@$*  EQUF      0251@ @@@@RC$*      EQUF      0277,X8   %[@@@@-55,55@B@@[@ZL
)@@G@@DKAMT$*   EQUF      0300,X8           .   @B@@[@FDKAMT$*  EQUF      0301ZM
)@@G@@,X8           .   @B@@[@DKPKT$*   EQUF      0302,X8           .   %@@@@[ZN
)@@G@@@ [@@@MTABL$*   EQUF      0310,X8   @ @@@@FATBL$*   EQUF      0315,X8   ZO
)@@G@@@C@@@@PX        PROC      1. PROC TO CLEAR DATA AREAS @B@@@@ZERO*     NAZP
)@@G@@ME      0                 .   @E@@@@          LR,U      R1,PX(1,2)      ZQ
)@@G@@  . GET REPEAT COUNT    @F@@@@          LXM,U     A1,ZEROES         . GEZR
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF WORD OF 0  @F@@@@          LXI,U     A1,0              . ZEZS
)@@G@@RO INCREMENT FOR BT     @H@@@@          LXM,U     A2,PX(1,1)        . BEZT
)@@G@@GINNING ADDRESS OF AREA T B CLEARED @F@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1      ZU
)@@G@@        . SET INCREMENT TO 1 FOR BT @H@@@@          BT        A2,0,*A1  ZV
)@@G@@        . ZERO OUT AREA BEGINNING AT PX(1,1) FOR@E@@@@          END     ZW
)@@G@@                    .    PX(1,2) WORDS    @C@@@@PZ        PROC      . PRZX
)@@G@@OC TO UPDATE PRINT COUNT@^@@@@PRTCNT*   NAME      0   @ @@@@          L,ZY
)@@G@@S3      A3,PRTVA$ @^@@@@          A,U       A3,1@ @@@@          S,S3    ZZ
)@@G@@  A3,PRTVA$ @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@     .@G@@@@. * * * * * * * * AA
)@@G@@* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@AB
)@@G@@.                       SORTF SUBROUTINE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PROCESSOR AC
)@@G@@MODIFIED TO SUBROUTINE BY JIM FLETCHER, ISI, JAN 78.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@AD
)@@G@@. THIS PROGRAM IS A MODIFICATION OF THE SORTF PROCESSOR WHICH     @F@@@@AE
)@@G@@. PERMITS COBOL USERS TO CALL SORTF FROM WITHIN A COBOL PROGRAM.  @E@@@@AF
)@@G@@. THE PROGRAM PRINTS THE SORT WORK ALLOCATIONS TO PRINT . IF@F@@@@. THE AG
)@@G@@SORT AREAS CAN NOT BE ALLOCATED THEN A RETURN CODE IS SET   @F@@@@. FOR AH
)@@G@@THE USERS PROGRAM TO INTEROGATE. IF THE INCORRECT NUMBER    @F@@@@. OF AAI
)@@G@@RGUMENTS IS PASSED TO THE ROUTINE THEN IT WILL ABORT WITH   @]@@@@. A MEAJ
)@@G@@SSAGE.@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CALLING SEQUENCE FROM COBOL:@F@@@@.     CALL 'AK
)@@G@@SORTF' USING NO-RECORDS,       . 01 LEVEL S9(10) COMP @F@@@@.           AL
)@@G@@             RECORD-SIZE,      . 01 LEV S9(10) COMP   @F@@@@.           AM
)@@G@@             RETUR$-CODE,      . 01 LEV S9(10) COMP   @H@@@@.           AN
)@@G@@             OPTION-LIST.      . 01 LEV S9(10) COMP (OPTIONAL)    @A@@@@AO
)@@G@@.     IF RETUR$-CODE NOT EQUAL ZERO @ @@@@.       THEN SORTF FAILED .   AP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE RECORD-SIZE IS IN ASCII CHARACTERS. FOR FIELDATAAQ
)@@G@@, SET OPTION-LIST @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. MODIFIED 12/79 TO NOTIFY CONSOLE IAR
)@@G@@F SPACE NOT AVAILABLE   @G@@@@. TO A VALUE OF ONE. IF ASCII CHAR THEN OPAS
)@@G@@TION-LIST IS NOT REQUIRED.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. * * * * * * * * * * * AT
)@@G@@* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@      AU
)@@G@@    LXI,H1    A0,0,A0           . GET DBANK ADDRESS   @B@@@@          SSAV
)@@G@@C       A0,18             .   @E@@@@         SX        X4,REGSAV$,A0    AW
)@@G@@   . SAVE REGISTER SET  @A@@@@         SX        X5,REGSAV$+1,A0  @A@@@@AX
)@@G@@         SX        X6,REGSAV$+2,A0  @A@@@@         SX        X7,REGSAV$+AY
)@@G@@3,A0  @A@@@@         SX        X8,REGSAV$+4,A0  @A@@@@         SX       AZ
)@@G@@ X9,REGSAV$+5,A0  @A@@@@         SX        X10,REGSAV$+6,A0 @A@@@@      BA
)@@G@@   SX        X11,REGSAV$+7,A0 @A@@@@         DS        A0,REGSAV$+8,A0  BB
)@@G@@@A@@@@         DS        A2,REGSAV$+10,A0 @A@@@@         DS        A4,REBC
)@@G@@GSAV$+12,A0 @A@@@@         DS        A6,REGSAV$+14,A0 @A@@@@         DS BD
)@@G@@       A8,REGSAV$+16,A0 @A@@@@         SR        R1,REGSAV$+18,A0 @A@@@@BE
)@@G@@         SR        R2,REGSAV$+19,A0 @A@@@@         SR        R3,REGSAV$+BF
)@@G@@20,A0 @A@@@@         SR        R4,REGSAV$+21,A0 @F@@@@          SSL     BG
)@@G@@  A0,18             . ELIMINATE DBANK ADDR IN A0@F@@@@          LXM,H1  BH
)@@G@@  X8,0,A0           . PUT DBANK ADDRESS IN X8   %[@@@@-123  @B@@[@      BI
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,060            .   @B@@[@          SA,S3     A1,PRTVA$ BJ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ZERO      NREC$,4           .   @B@@@@      BK
)@@G@@    ZERO      ARG$,3            .   @B@@@@          ZERO      ASGPK$+1,1BL
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ZERO      ASGPK$+3,3        .   @B@@@@      BM
)@@G@@    ZERO      ASGIM$,18         .   @B@@@@          ZERO      FXA$,8    BN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ZERO      XB$,45            .   @B@@@@      BO
)@@G@@    ZERO      RC$,1             .   @F@@@@          LA,H2     A4,0,A0   BP
)@@G@@       . GET NUMBER OF ARGUMENTS    @D@@@@          TE,U     A4,3       BQ
)@@G@@       . IS IT THREE?   @D@@@@          J     TRYFOUR              . NOPBR
)@@G@@E, TRY FOUR @ @@@@          J         STORERET  @E@@@@TRYFOUR    TE,U   BS
)@@G@@ A4,4                . HOW BOUT FOUR??    @F@@@@          J       BADCALBT
)@@G@@L             . WAS NEITHER, SAY BYE-BYE  @ @@@@STORERET  L         A0,LBU
)@@G@@FREXB @ @@@@          ER        CSF$.     @ @@@@          L         A0,LBV
)@@G@@FREXA @ @@@@          ER        CSF$.     @ @@@@          L         A0,LBW
)@@G@@FRECR @ @@@@          ER        CSF$.     %[@@@@-143  @B@@[@          L BX
)@@G@@        A0,LFREXC         .   @B@@[@          ER        CSF$            BY
)@@G@@  .   @B@@[@          L         A0,LFREXD         .   @B@@[@          ERBZ
)@@G@@        CSF$              .   @B@@[@          L         A0,LFREXE       CA
)@@G@@  .   @B@@[@          ER        CSF$              .   @B@@[@          L CB
)@@G@@        A0,LFREXF        .    @B@@[@          ER        CSF$            CC
)@@G@@  .   @B@@[@          L         A0,LFREXG         .   @B@@[@          ERCD
)@@G@@        CSF$              .   @A@@@@           LA      A0,REGSAV$+8,X8  CE
)@@G@@@B@@@@          SSL       A0,18             .   @F@@@@         LA       CF
)@@G@@ A1,*1,A0             . GET NUMBER OF RECORDS   @ @@@@         SA       CG
)@@G@@ A1,NREC$   @H@@@@         LA        A0,*2,A0             . GET RECORD LCH
)@@G@@ENGTH IN CHARACTERS     @ @@@@         SA        A0,RSIZE$  @ @@@@      CI
)@@G@@    DSL       A0,36     @G@@@@           TE,U    A4,4                . ICJ
)@@G@@F  NO OPTIONS SO DO ASCII     @^@@@@           J       ASCI @F@@@@      CK
)@@G@@     LA      A3,REGSAV$+8,X8     . GET ARG LIST ADDRESS BACK@B@@@@      CL
)@@G@@    SSL       A3,18             .   @E@@@@           LA      A4,*4,A3   CM
)@@G@@          . GET OPTIONS ARG   @D@@@@           TE,U    A4,1             CN
)@@G@@   . IS IT ASCII  @^@@@@           J       $+3  @D@@@@           DI,U   CO
)@@G@@ A0,6                . DIVIDE FOR FD@D@@@@           J       $+2        CP
)@@G@@         . AND SKIP ASCI@F@@@@ASCI      DI,U      A0,4            . DIVICQ
)@@G@@DE BY 4 CHARS FOR ASCII @E@@@@           TZ      A1                  . ACR
)@@G@@NY REMAINDER?     @C@@@@           AA,U    A0,1                . YEP!   CS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          L         A2,NREC$  @ @@@@          MSI       A0,A2     CT
)@@G@@@ @@@@          JN        A0,ERR1.  @G@@@@           SA      A0,AMT$    CU
)@@G@@         . SAVE TOTAL NUMBER WORDS NEEDED %[@@@@-166  @F@@[@          TGCV
)@@G@@        A0,MILLION        . IS VOL > 1000000 WORDS    @F@@[@          J CW
)@@G@@        DODISK            . YES, DO DISK MODULE ASGS  % @@@@-167,167  . CX
)@@G@@SORTF SUBROUTINE  @F@@[@          SSL       A0,2              . CALC 25%CY
